{"type":"message","id":"95226bb7","parentId":"0993adb1","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:49:08.624Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"El problema es claro: el archivo de configuración tiene `${TAVILY_API_KEY}` como string literal, pero el script no está expandiendo las variables de entorno. Necesito modificar la función `load_config` para expandir variables de entorno.\n\n**¿Quieres que corrija esto modificando el script para que expanda las variables de entorno, o prefieres que actualice el archivo de configuración con el valor real de la API key?**\n\n## 2. **Problema con Workspace Janitor - Script renombrado**\n\nEl script `janitor_scan.py` no existe. Voy a verificar qué scripts están disponibles y cuál es el script principal:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_2JmvHJfchrxn9kvO0nbQjEl6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/workspace-janitor/SKILL.md","limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":303,"output":223,"cacheRead":41536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42062,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773071335967}}
{"type":"message","id":"39d3085b","parentId":"95226bb7","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:49:08.636Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_2JmvHJfchrxn9kvO0nbQjEl6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: workspace-janitor\ndescription: Safe workspace maintenance skill that scans, classifies, and proposes cleanup of obsolete files with user authorization.\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: workspace-janitor\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\", \"python\"]\nsafety-level: high\n---\n\n# workspace-janitor\n\n## Purpose\nMaintain, clean, and organize the OpenClaw workspace directory with extreme safety hardening. The skill analyzes the entire `workspace/` directory, identifies unused/obsolete/temporary files, protects system files and active skills, maintains a deletion candidate registry, asks for explicit user authorization before deletion, and generates a clean workspace structure.\n\n## Safety Hardening (CRITICAL)\nThe janitor must NEVER delete automatically. Deletion requires:\n1. Candidate identification\n2. Logging\n3. User confirmation\n4. Safe removal\n\n**Protected zones (NEVER delete):**\n- `workspace/skills/`\n- `workspace/references/`\n- `workspace/memory/`\n- `workspace/.learnings/`\n- `AGENTS.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `USER.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`\n\nAny attempt to modify protected zones must trigger: `janitor|PROTECTED_PATH|blocked`\n\n## Cleanup Targets\nThe janitor may analyze and mark candidates inside:\n- `workspace/projects/`\n- `workspace/temp_refs/`\n- `workspace/*.tmp`\n- `workspace/temp_*`\n- Files matching patterns: `temp_process*`, `analysis_*.json`, `*_old.py`, `*_backup*`, `temp_*.md`\n\n## Expiration Policy\n- Project temporary files older than 30 days → cleanup candidates\n- Skill run artifacts older than 14 days → may be archived\n- Temporary debug files older than 7 days → deletion candidates\n- Policies must be configurable (via `janitor_config.json`)\n\n## Janitor Logbook\nMaintain `workspace/memory/janitor_log.md` with records:\n- Candidate file path\n- File type\n- Last modified date\n- Why considered obsolete\n\n[62 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773071348632}}
