{"type":"message","id":"39497035","parentId":"9c4d8ba0","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:49:58.597Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_SRtwowsgbaaJ2Mm4c4UC6nkq","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: vector-memory\ndescription: Vector-based memory system for semantic storage and retrieval of memories using embeddings. Supports PostgreSQL with pgvector, auto-curation of MEMORY.md, and integration with agent-watchdog for long-running operations.\ncategory: memory\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"python\", \"postgresql\", \"pgvector\"]\noptional_requires: [\"gemini-api-key\"]\nsafety-level: medium\nwrap-up-enabled: false\n---\n\n# vector-memory\n\n## Purpose\nA production-ready vector memory system that enables semantic storage and retrieval of memories using embeddings. The system provides:\n\n1. **Semantic Memory Storage**: Store memories with vector embeddings for semantic similarity search\n2. **Auto-Curation**: Automatically curate and consolidate MEMORY.md from daily notes\n3. **Memory Management**: Flush, forget, and search memories with semantic understanding\n4. **Watchdog Integration**: Long-running operations are monitored by agent-watchdog\n5. **Error Learning**: Incidents are emitted to error-learning-loop for system improvement\n\n## Core Components\n\n### 1. Memory Storage (`memory_store.py`)\nStore memories with vector embeddings using Gemini Embeddings API.\n\n```bash\n# Store a memory\npython scripts/memory_store.py \"Important decision about project architecture\" --label \"architecture\" --category \"decisions\"\n\n# Store with metadata\npython scripts/memory_store.py \"API key rotated on 2026-03-06\" --label \"security\" --category \"operations\" --meta '{\"priority\": \"high\", \"action_required\": false}'\n```\n\n### 2. Semantic Search (`memory_search.py`)\nSearch memories by semantic similarity.\n\n```bash\n# Search memories\npython scripts/memory_search.py \"project design decisions\" --limit 5 --min-score 0.4\n\n# Search within category\npython scripts/memory_search.py \"security incidents\" --category \"security\" --limit 3\n```\n\n### 3. Memory Auto-Curation (`memory_auto_curate.py`)\nAutomatically curate MEMORY.md by extracting insights from recent daily notes.\n\n\n[227 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773071398589}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e060d9b","parentId":"39497035","timestamp":"2026-03-09T15:50:16.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Veo que los scripts principales son `memory_store.py`, `memory_search.py`, `memory_auto_curate.py`, etc. No hay un `vector_status.py`. \n\n**¿Quieres que verifique qué script debería usarse para verificar el estado del vector memory, o prefieres que cree un script `vector_status.py`?**\n\n## 4. **Problema con Cron job de janitor - Error de entrega a Telegram**\n\nEl error es: `Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>`. Esto es porque el cron job está configurado con `\"delivery\": {\"mode\": \"announce\", \"channel\": \"last\"}` pero no tiene un chatId específico.\n\n**¿Quieres que corrija la configuración del cron job para que no intente entregar a Telegram, o prefieres configurar un chatId específico?**\n\n---\n\n**Resumen de preguntas para proceder con las correcciones:**\n\n1. **Tavily API Key**: ¿Corrijo el script para expandir variables de entorno o actualizo el archivo de configuración con el valor real?\n2. **Workspace Janitor**: ¿Creo un wrapper script `workspace-janitor` o actualizo la configuración del skill?\n3. **Vector Memory**: ¿Verifico qué script usar para status o creo `vector_status.py`?\n4. **Cron job Telegram**: ¿Configuro para no entregar a Telegram o configuro un chatId?\n\nUna vez que me confirmes cómo proceder con cada punto, puedo implementar las correcciones."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":487,"output":333,"cacheRead":43968,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44788,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773071398596}}
