tion_wrapper.py\n\nThe wrapper will:\n1. Create MEMORY.md backup first\n2. Run auto-curation conservatively\n3. Update projects.md only if confidence sufficient\n4. Run vector flush after successful rewrite\n5. Emit incidents if any sub-step fails\n6. Exit safely without corrupting files","model":"custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-chat"},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773082800000,"lastRunAtMs":1772825770920,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":107069,"lastError":"cron announce delivery failed","lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","lastDeliveryError":"cron announce delivery failed","consecutiveErrors":0}}],"total":2,"offset":0,"limit":2,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773075390657}}
{"type":"message","id":"52a9d032","parentId":"d708f5d6","timestamp":"2026-03-09T16:56:52.826Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## **Resumen de correcciones aplicadas:**\n\n### ✅ **Problemas identificados y corregidos:**\n\n1. **✅ Entrega a Telegram eliminada**: Ya estaba corregido (delivery.mode: \"none\")\n2. **✅ Payload específico**: Actualicé de `\"workspace-janitor\"` a `\"workspace-janitor scan\"` para ejecutar solo el scan\n3. **✅ Estado zombie resuelto**: El job estaba marcado como `runningAtMs` pero no ejecutándose\n   - Deshabilité y volví a habilitar el job para limpiar el estado\n   - El campo `runningAtMs` desapareció\n4. **✅ Ejecución manual exitosa**: Probé ejecutar manualmente y se enqueó correctamente\n\n### 📊 **Estado actual de los cron jobs:**\n\n1. **workspace-janitor-daily**:\n   - ✅ Habilitado\n   - ✅ Payload corregido: `\"workspace-janitor scan\"`\n   - ✅ Delivery: `mode: \"none\"` (sin Telegram)\n   - ✅ Sin estado zombie\n   - ⏰ Próxima ejecución: Hoy a la 1:00 PM (en ~1 hora)\n\n2. **Twice-Weekly MEMORY.md Auto-Curation**:\n   - ✅ Funcionando correctamente (lastRunStatus: \"ok\")\n   - ✅ Delivery: `mode: \"none\"`\n   - ⏰ Próxima ejecución: Lunes 14:00\n\n### 🔧 **Prevención para futuras ejecuciones:**\n- El job ahora ejecutará `workspace-janitor scan` en lugar del comando genérico\n- No intentará entregar resultados a Telegram\n- El estado se limpió para evitar bloqueos\n\nLa próxima ejecución automática será hoy a la 1:00 PM y debería funcionar correctamente con las correcciones aplicadas."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":772,"output":419,"cacheRead":63936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65127,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773075390662}}
{"type":"message","id":"20379c20","parentId":"52a9d032","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:00:14.299Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-09 12:00 EST] # Prompt de endurecimiento incremental v2 para `salesforce-architect` y `salesforce-code-auditor` \n\n \n\nYou are the MAIN agent. \n\n \n\nYour task is to perform a **targeted hardening upgrade** of the existing Salesforce skill ecosystem. \n\n \n\nThis is **not** a greenfield redesign. \n\nThis is **not** a replacement of the current architecture. \n\nThis is **not** an instruction to recreate Salesforce roles or project governance on every run. \n\n \n\nYou must improve the existing system **incrementally**, preserving the current working behavior of: \n\n \n\n- `skills/salesforce-architect` \n\n- `skills/salesforce-code-auditor` \n\n \n\nThe main goals are: \n\n \n\n1. Make `salesforce-architect` the single governing skill for all Salesforce work \n\n2. Tighten project routing discipline \n\n3. Formalize specialist role templates once \n\n4. Add a formal Salesforce project state machine \n\n5. Add a formal Definition of Done by role \n\n6. Tighten architect ↔ code-auditor integration \n\n7. Keep sub-agents as the default specialist execution model \n\n8. Avoid persistent agent sprawl \n\n9. Preserve current working pipelines and artifacts \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## CRITICAL DISTINCTION — WHAT HAPPENS NOW VS WHAT RUNS ALWAYS \n\n \n\nThis upgrade contains **two different classes of work** and you must keep them separate. \n\n \n\n### CLASS A — ONE-TIME FOUNDATION WORK (DO NOW, BUILD ONCE) \n\n \n\nThis is work you perform now to improve the Salesforce skill system structure. \n\nThese artifacts should be created or updated **once**, then only maintained over time when necessary. \n\n \n\nExamples: \n\n- role templates \n\n- project state machine definition \n\n- architect review protocol \n\n- Definition of Done by role \n\n- architect ↔ code-auditor handoff contract \n\n \n\nThese are **reference assets**, not runtime artifacts recreated every execution. \n\n \n\n### CLASS B — PERMANENT SKILL BEHAVIOR (RUNTIME RULES) \n\n \n\nThese are the behaviors the skills must enforce every time they run. \n\n \n\nExamples: \n\n- detect or create the correct project folder \n\n- keep artifacts inside the project folder \n\n- determine project phase \n\n- choose the right specialist role \n\n- invoke code auditor when needed \n\n- validate specialist outputs \n\n- reject weak outputs and request correction \n\n \n\nYou must clearly separate both classes in your implementation and in your report. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## CONSTRAINT — DO NOT REDEFINE ROLES EVERY RUN \n\n \n\nSalesforce specialist roles must **not** be dynamically reinvented on every execution. \n\n \n\nInstead: \n\n \n\n1. Build a **stable role model once** \n\n2. Store it in `skills/salesforce-architect/references/` \n\n3. Use it repeatedly during runtime \n\n \n\nAt runtime, the architect should only: \n\n- select the right pre-defined role template \n\n- pass task-specific context \n\n- review the result \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 1 — READ CURRENT STATE FIRST \n\n \n\nBefore changing anything: \n\n \n\n1. Read the current `SKILL.md` of: \n\n- `skills/salesforce-architect` \n\n- `skills/salesforce-code-auditor` \n\n \n\n2. Inspect the current script layout of both skills \n\n \n\n3. Preserve: \n\n- architect stage pipeline \n\n- reference PDF enforcement \n\n- EC0249 enforcement \n\n- Salesforce evidence policy \n\n- current project runtime structure \n\n- code-auditor case model \n\n- learning integration \n\n- watchdog compatibility \n\n- handoff report requirement \n\n \n\nDo not regress any of these. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# CLASS A — ONE-TIME FOUNDATION WORK (DO NOW) \n\n \n\n## PART 2 — CREATE A STABLE SALESFORCE ROLE MODEL (ONCE) \n\n \n\nCreate or update a stable role model under: \n\n \n\n`skills/salesforce-architect/references/` \n\n \n\nRequired new or improved reference files: \n\n \n\n- `SALESFORCE_ROLE_MODEL.md` \n\n- `ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md` \n\n- `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md` \n\n- `ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md` \n\n- `SALESFORCE_PROJECT_STATE_MACHINE.md` \n\n- `CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md` \n\n \n\n### Role model source requirements \n\n \n\nUse: \n\n- official Salesforce documentation \n\n- Salesforce role and certification context from: \n\n`https://www.salesforceben.com/salesforce-certifications/` \n\n \n\nThe purpose is **not certification coaching**. \n\nThe purpose is to infer accurate role boundaries, responsibilities, and expected outputs for Salesforce specialist work. \n\n \n\n### Specialist role set to formalize once \n\n \n\n1. Salesforce Administrator \n\n2. Salesforce Functional Consultant — Standard Clouds \n\n- Sales Cloud \n\n- Service Cloud \n\n- Field Service \n\n- Experience Cloud \n\n- Digital Engagement \n\n- Agentforce \n\n3. Salesforce Integration Developer \n\n4. Salesforce Custom UI Developer \n\n- LWC \n\n- Visualforce \n\n- custom UI interaction layer \n\n5. Salesforce Industries / OmniStudio Functional Consultant \n\n6. Salesforce OmniStudio Developer \n\n7. Salesforce Data Cloud Functional Consultant \n\n8. Salesforce Data Cloud Developer \n\n9. Salesforce Security / Platform Governance Reviewer \n\n \n\n### For each role define: \n\n \n\n- role purpose \n\n- domain ownership \n\n- what the role analyzes \n\n- what the role does not decide alone \n\n- what evidence it must provide \n\n- what artifacts it may produce \n\n- when it must escalate back to architect \n\n- handoff expectations \n\n- Definition of Done \n\n \n\nThis role model is a **one-time reference foundation**. \n\nDo not rebuild it every run. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 3 — DEFINE THE SALESFORCE PROJECT STATE MACHINE (ONCE) \n\n \n\nCreate or update: \n\n \n\n`skills/salesforce-architect/references/SALESFORCE_PROJECT_STATE_MACHINE.md` \n\n \n\nThis must define the formal lifecycle states: \n\n \n\n- DISCOVERY \n\n- REQUIREMENTS \n\n- FIT_GAP \n\n- DESIGN \n\n- DATA_MODEL \n\n- ARCH_REVIEW \n\n- CODE_AUDIT \n\n- REMEDIATION \n\n- FINALIZED \n\n \n\nFor each state define: \n\n \n\n- entry conditions \n\n- required artifacts \n\n- blocking conditions \n\n- allowed next states \n\n- prohibited transitions \n\n- architect responsibilities \n\n \n\nExamples of hard rules: \n\n- do not enter `FIT_GAP` without scope/SOW \n\n- do not enter `DESIGN` without consolidated discovery \n\n- do not enter `FINALIZED` if critical audit findings remain open \n\n \n\nThis file is also a **one-time reference foundation**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 4 — DEFINE DEFINITION OF DONE BY ROLE (ONCE) \n\n \n\nCreate or update: \n\n \n\n`skills/salesforce-architect/references/DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md` \n\n \n\nEach specialist role must have an explicit Definition of Done. \n\n \n\nExamples: \n\n \n\n### Functional consultant \n\nMust return: \n\n- process interpretation \n\n- assumptions \n\n- scope dependencies \n\n- official evidence \n\n- open decisions \n\n \n\n### Integration developer \n\nMust return: \n\n- integration pattern \n\n- authentication assumptions \n\n- retry/error strategy \n\n- limits and failure modes \n\n- impacted objects/events \n\n \n\n### Custom UI developer \n\nMust return: \n\n- UI interaction model \n\n- component structure \n\n- event flow \n\n- navigation implications \n\n- accessibility/responsiveness considerations if relevant \n\n \n\n### Code auditor \n\nMust return: \n\n- findings \n\n- code evidence/snippets \n\n- severity \n\n- architectural impact \n\n- remediation suggestions \n\n- confidence level if heuristic \n\n \n\n### Architect \n\nMust return: \n\n- final decision \n\n- rationale \n\n- alternatives considered \n\n- unresolved risks \n\n- next steps \n\n \n\nThis is a stable reference asset, not a runtime-generated file. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 5 — DEFINE ARCHITECT ↔ CODE-AUDITOR GOVERNANCE CONTRACT (ONCE) \n\n \n\nCreate or update: \n\n \n\n`skills/salesforce-architect/references/CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md` \n\n \n\nDocument these modes: \n\n \n\n### Mode A — Architecture → Code Audit \n\nUse when architect needs current-state technical truth before design decisions. \n\n \n\n### Mode B — Code Audit → Architecture \n\nUse when audit findings must change architecture decisions. \n\n \n\n### Mode C — Design Validation Mode \n\nUse when the architect needs to validate whether current implementation supports the proposed design. \n\n \n\nAlso define: \n\n- required request contract from architect to auditor \n\n- required output contract from auditor to architect \n\n- severity handling \n\n- when findings block architectural finalization \n\n \n\nThis is a one-time structural governance artifact. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# CLASS B — PERMANENT SKILL BEHAVIOR (RUNTIME RULES) \n\n \n\n## PART 6 — HARDEN PROJECT ROUTING BEHAVIOR IN `salesforce-architect` \n\n \n\nImprove runtime behavior so the architect acts as the **project owner and router**. \n\n \n\nEvery time Salesforce work is requested, the architect must: \n\n \n\n1. identify the `project_key` \n\n2. determine whether the project already exists \n\n3. create it if missing \n\n4. route all artifacts into that project folder \n\n5. determine whether the request is: \n\n- new work \n\n- artifact update \n\n- review \n\n- correction \n\n- code audit \n\n- remediation \n\n \n\nNo Salesforce artifact may be created outside: \n\n`<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/...` \n\nunless explicitly classified as a global reference. \n\n \n\n### Required runtime improvement \n\n \n\nThe architect must maintain and update: \n\n \n\n`<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/README.md` \n\n \n\nThis project control file must track: \n\n- project_key \n\n- active phase \n\n- clouds in scope \n\n- latest artifact versions \n\n- whether code audit exists \n\n- last architect review \n\n- pending next actions \n\n \n\nThis file **is runtime-maintained**, not rebuilt globally every time. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 7 — HARDEN SUB-AGENT SPECIALIST USAGE \n\n \n\nUse **sub-agents as default** specialist execution mode. \n\n \n\nDo not create persistent agents as part of this upgrade. \n\n \n\nAt runtime, the architect must: \n\n- choose the correct role template from the role model \n\n- decide whether specialist help is needed \n\n- pass task-specific context only \n\n- review returned work critically \n\n \n\n### Required runtime logic \n\n \n\nThe architect must decide: \n\n- single-domain vs multi-domain task \n\n- one specialist vs several \n\n- whether code-auditor is needed \n\n- whether output is strong enough or must be challenged \n\n \n\nThe architect must act explicitly as: \n\n- router \n\n- reviewer \n\n- challenger \n\n- integrator \n\n- project owner \n\n \n\nThat behavior must be reflected in runtime logic, not only documentation. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 8 — IMPROVE `salesforce-code-auditor` AS A SUBORDINATE VALIDATOR \n\n \n\nKeep the current code-auditor structure, but improve its governed integration. \n\n \n\nThe auditor must remain project-scoped under: \n\n`<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/...` \n\n \n\n### Runtime expectations \n\n \n\nThe architect must be able to call the auditor when: \n\n- current-state code must be understood \n\n- design must be contrasted with implementation \n\n- technical constraints affect architecture \n\n- partner-delivered code must be reviewed \n\n- remediation planning needs code evidence \n\n \n\n### Required improvement \n\n \n\nEnsure the auditor returns outputs that the architect can directly consume: \n\n- technical risks \n\n- security/governor findings \n\n- object/field/automation usage \n\n- implementation constraints \n\n- design alignment gaps \n\n- remediation suggestions \n\n- confidence if heuristic \n\n \n\nDo not redesign the whole auditor. \n\nImprove the contract and project integration. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 9 — PHASE-AWARE RUNTIME BEHAVIOR \n\n \n\nAt runtime, `salesforce-architect` must use the state machine. \n\n \n\nThis means: \n\n- detect current phase \n\n- determine if the request is valid for that phase \n\n- determine whether artifacts should be created, updated, or blocked \n\n- avoid regenerating artifacts unnecessarily \n\n- increment versions conservatively when revisions occur \n\n \n\nDo not recreate all artifacts unless explicitly requested. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 10 — OUTPUT DISCIPLINE AND VERSIONING \n\n \n\nImprove artifact version discipline without breaking current file generation. \n\n \n\nRecommended naming examples: \n\n- `Functional_Design_v1.docx` \n\n- `Functional_Design_v2.docx` \n\n- `Fit_Gap_Matrix_v1.xlsx` \n\n- `Code_Audit_Report_v1.md` \n\n- `Architecture_Overview_v2.md` \n\n \n\nFor runtime behavior: \n\n- preserve current folder layout \n\n- add version awareness where needed \n\n- ensure the architect can register code-audit outputs in the project README \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 11 — INCIDENT AND GOVERNANCE HARDENING \n\n \n\nAdd or improve incident reporting for governance failures. \n\n \n\nExamples: \n\n- `salesforce|PROJECT_ROUTING|missing_project_key|blocked` \n\n- `salesforce|ROLE_ASSIGNMENT|wrong_specialist_selected|rework_needed` \n\n- `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|subagent_output_incomplete|rejected` \n\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|design_alignment_gap|review_required` \n\n \n\nThese must use the existing unified incident path. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 12 — FILES TO TOUCH \n\n \n\nUpdate conservatively. \n\n \n\nAt minimum: \n\n- `skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md` \n\n- `skills/salesforce-architect/scripts/run_pipeline.py` \n\n- supporting architect scripts as needed \n\n- `skills/salesforce-code-auditor/SKILL.md` \n\n- supporting auditor scripts as needed \n\n- architect references/examples for: \n\n- role model \n\n- state machine \n\n- DoD by role \n\n- architect review protocol \n\n- architect ↔ auditor handoff \n\n \n\nDo not create unnecessary duplicate structures if current files can be extended cleanly. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## PART 13 — VALIDATION \n\n \n\nRun a validation proving: \n\n \n\n1. A Salesforce request creates or reuses the correct project folder \n\n2. Artifacts are written only inside the project folder \n\n3. The architect can assign at least 2 specialist roles correctly \n\n4. The architect can invoke `salesforce-code-auditor` as a subordinate validator \n\n5. The architect can reject a weak specialist output and request correction \n\n6. The project README updates correctly \n\n7. The state machine is respected \n\n8. Definition of Done is actually enforced in at least one specialist handoff \n\n9. No scattered Salesforce artifacts are created outside the project directory \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n## FINAL OUTPUT REQUIRED \n\n \n\nReturn a Handoff Report clearly separated into: \n\n \n\n### A. One-time foundation work completed \n\nList the stable references created or improved once \n\n \n\n### B. Permanent runtime behavior improved \n\nList the runtime behavior changes added to the skills \n\n \n\n### C. Files changed \n\nList exact files \n\n \n\n### D. Validation results \n\nSummarize pass/fail with evidence \n\n \n\n### E. Outcome \n\nsuccess | partial | failure"}],"timestamp":1773075614293}}
{"type":"message","id":"2d0b396a","parentId":"20379c20","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:00:31.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a realizar el endurecimiento incremental de los skills de Salesforce. Primero, voy a leer el estado actual de ambos skills."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_n3kxisBAsev6vqBDUPdopxGS","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":3313,"output":92,"cacheRead":65088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68493,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773075614296}}
{"type":"message","id":"8482d760","parentId":"2d0b396a","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:00:31.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_n3kxisBAsev6vqBDUPdopxGS","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: salesforce-architect\ndescription: Production-ready skill for analyzing complex business processes, extracting requirements, producing Salesforce architecture decisions, generating FIT/GAP analysis, functional design documentation, data models, and validating architecture using official Salesforce documentation only.\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: salesforce-architect\n---\n\n# Salesforce Architect Skill\n\n## Overview\nA production‑ready skill for analyzing complex business processes, extracting requirements, producing Salesforce architecture decisions, generating FIT/GAP analysis, functional design documentation, data models, and validating architecture using official Salesforce documentation only.\n\n## CRITICAL RULE – USE WORKSPACE REFERENCES\nThe skill must read and consult the following reference PDFs (located in `<workspace>/references/`) before generating any output artifacts:\n\n1. `_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf` – defines the structure of the Functional Design document.\n2. `IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf` – defines the structure and fields of the FIT/GAP matrix.\n3. `IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf` – example of a completed functional design.\n4. `Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf` – example data model structure.\n\nIf any of these documents are missing, the skill must:\n1. Stop execution\n2. Emit an incident\n3. Ask the user to confirm the references location\n\n## Salesforce Documentation Evidence Policy\nAllowed domains:\n- `help.salesforce.com`\n- `developer.salesforce.com`\n- `architect.salesforce.com`\n- `trailhead.salesforce.com`\n\nEvery architecture decision must include a reference link to official Salesforce documentation. If evidence cannot be found:\n- Mark the decision `UNVERIFIED`\n- Request clarification from the user\n- Do not finalize the design\n\n## Supported Clouds\n- Sales Cloud\n- Service Cloud\n- Field Service\n- Financial Services Cloud\n- Data Cloud\n- Agentforce\n- OmniStudio\n- Digital Engagement\n- Experience Cloud\n\nThe skill must evaluate licensing constraints before recommending features. For example: if Field Service licenses are unavailable, propose a custom visit management solution instead of FSL.\n\n## Skill Directory Structure\n```\nskills/salesforce-architect/\n├── SKILL.md (this file)\n├── scripts/\n│   ├── run_pipeline.py          # Main orchestrator\n│   ├── stage1_discovery.py\n│   ├── stage2_requirements.py\n│   ├── stage3_fit_gap.py\n│   ├── stage4_functional_design.py\n│   ├── stage5_data_model.py\n│   ├── stage6_arch_validation.py\n│   ├── stage7_export.py\n│   ├── official_docs_retrieval.py\n│   ├── debate_mode.py\n│   ├── learning_emit.py\n│   └── utils_io.py\n├── references/\n│   ├── TEMPLATES_INDEX.md\n│   ├── EC0249_mapping.md\n│   ├── VF_functional_design_mapping.md\n│   ├── FitGap_mapping.md\n│   ├── DataModel_mapping.md\n│   ├── Salesforce_official_whitelist.md\n│   └── pattern_keys.md\n└── examples/\n    ├── example_minimum_inputs.md\n    ├── example_with_transcript.md\n    ├── example_with_scope_fitgap.md\n    └── example_end_to_end.md\n```\n\n## Runtime Project Structure\nWhen executing the skill, a new project folder is created under `workspace/projects/<project_key>/` with the following layout:\n\n```\nworkspace/projects/<project_key>/\n├── discovery/\n│   ├── Discovery_Report.md\n│   ├── Discovery_Process_Analysis.md\n│   └── Discovery_QA.xlsx\n├── fit_gap/\n│   └── Fit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx\n├── design/\n│   └── Functional_Design.docx\n├── data_model/\n│   └── Data_Model.xlsx\n├── architecture/\n│   ├── Architecture_Overview.md\n│   └── Evidence_Log.md\n├── evidence/\n│   └── Evidence_Log.md (symlink or copy)\n└── README.md\n```\n\n## Pipeline Stages\n\n### Stage 0 – Intake Gate\n**Mandatory inputs** (block pipeline if missing):\n- Project name\n- Industry\n- Country\n- Salesforce clouds licensed\n- User count\n- Process description\n- Implementation scope\n\nIf any mandatory input is missing, generate discovery questions and stop.\n\n### Stage 1 – Discovery (EC0249)\nExtract actors, processes, events, systems, unknowns from transcripts/notes/SOW.\n**Outputs:**\n- `Discovery_Report.md`\n- `Discovery_Process_Analysis.md`\n- `Discovery_QA.xlsx`\n\n### Stage 2 – Requirements Consolidation\nTransform discovery into structured requirements with:\n- ID\n- Process\n- Actor\n- Description\n- Trigger\n- Acceptance criteria\n\nIntegrations must not be assumed.\n\n### Stage 3 – FIT / GAP Analysis\nFIT = requested + in project scope, GAP = requested + not in project scope.\nMust request SOW/proposal/scope before classification.\n**Output:** `Fit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx` with columns:\n- ReqID\n- Process\n- Requirement\n- Fit/GAP\n- Justification\n- Time impact\n- Cost impact\n- Implementation type\n- License dependency\n- Risk\n- Evidence link\n- Status\n\n### Stage 4 – Functional Design\nStructure MUST follow `<workspace>/references/_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf`.\nGenerate `Functional_Design.docx` with sections:\n- Introduction\n- Scope\n- Business process algorithms\n- System interactions\n- Object model\n- Automations\n- Security\n- Reporting\n- Risks\n\nBefore finalizing architecture, enter **Debate Mode** presenting 2–3 architecture alternatives with pros/cons, licensing impact, documentation evidence.\n\n### Stage 5 – Data Model\nStructure must follow `<workspace>/references/Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf`.\nGenerate `Data_Model.xlsx` with tabs per object. Each object must include:\n- Fields, types, required flags\n- Relationships\n- Record types\n- Validations\n\n### Stage 6 – Architecture Validation\nValidate against licensing constraints, Salesforce limits, security best practices, scalability.\n**Outputs:**\n- `Architecture_Overview.md`\n- `Evidence_Log.md`\n\n### Stage 7 – Export\nUse `python-docx` for Word, `openpyxl` for Excel. Export all artifacts.\n\n## Learning System Integration\nIf blocking conditions occur, append incidents to `workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\nExample pattern keys:\n- `discovery|MISSING|nonnegotiable|scope|blocked`\n- `evidence|MISSING|salesforce_official|feature_unverified|blocked`\n- `fitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify|blocked`\n- `licensing|CONFLICT|feature_requires_license|not_available|alternate_needed`\n\nThen trigger learning‑loop fallback.\n\n## Multi‑Agent Mode\nThe skill supports optional architecture sub‑agents:\n- SalesCloudArchitect\n- ServiceCloudArchitect\n- FieldServiceArchitect\n- DataCloudArchitect\n- ExperienceArchitect\n- OmniStudioArchitect\n- AgentforceArchitect\n- SecurityArchitect\n\n`run_pipeline.py` must allow:\n- `--mode single`\n- `--mode multi`\n\nAll long‑running agents must register with `agent‑watchdog`.\n\n## Required Demo Execution\nTo validate the skill, run a demo project:\n```\nproject_key = demo_salesforce_architect\n```\n\nExpected behavior:\n1. Generate discovery outputs\n2. Block FIT/GAP if scope missing\n3. Emit learning incident\n4. Trigger learning loop fallback\n5. Generate Word and Excel artifacts\n\n## How to Use\n1. Ensure the reference PDFs are present in `<workspace>/references/`.\n2. Run the pipeline:\n   ```bash\n   cd /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/scripts\n   python3 run_pipeline.py --project-key <key> --inputs <input_file.json>\n   ```\n3. For demo:\n   ```bash\n   python3 run_pipeline.py --project-key demo_salesforce_architect --demo\n   ```\n\n## Handoff Report Requirement\nEvery sub‑agent spawned by this skill must end its final response with a structured Handoff Report using this exact format:\n\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**:\n  - [TYPE=ERROR|NEAR_MISS|MISUNDERSTANDING|TOOL_FAILURE|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF; SEV=S1|S2|S3|S4] <brief symptom> (evidence: <1‑line concrete detail, no secrets>)\n  - Pattern hint: <optional>\n  - Prevention rule: <optional>\n- **Files touched**: <list or \"none\">\n- **Next action**: <1‑line suggestion>\n- **Watchdog fields** (required for monitoring):\n  - session_id: <your session identifier>\n  - run_id: <your run identifier>\n  - last_activity_at: <timestamp of last progress>\n  - progress_marker: <current step or checkpoint>\n\nIf no incidents occurred, write \"Incidents: none\"."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773075631460}}
{"type":"message","id":"b547a1ce","parentId":"8482d760","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:00:43.691Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_xW8jIjK9ZnbLI4QSlEsOe6K2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-code-auditor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":2086,"output":67,"cacheRead":68480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70633,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773075631472}}
{"type":"message","id":"fe2dbe64","parentId":"b547a1ce","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:00:43.740Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_xW8jIjK9ZnbLI4QSlEsOe6K2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: salesforce-code-auditor\ndescription: A production‑ready skill for progressive technical analysis of Salesforce codebases (Apex, LWC, Visualforce, Triggers, Flows, Metadata) with token‑efficient auditing.\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: salesforce-code-auditor\n---\n\n# Salesforce Code Auditor Skill\n\n## Overview\nA production‑ready skill for **progressive technical analysis of Salesforce codebases** (Apex, LWC, Visualforce, Triggers, Flows, Metadata) with **token‑efficient auditing**. The agent requests only the minimal necessary code to reconstruct the real execution logic of a process.\n\nDesigned to **work together with the `salesforce‑architect` skill**.\n\n## Workspace Code Intake Model\nThe user must place code inside a case folder created by the skill.\n\nDirectory created automatically:\n`<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/inputs/`\n\nSupported formats:\n- Apex `.cls`\n- Apex Triggers `.trigger`\n- LWC `.js`, `.html`, `.xml`\n- Visualforce `.page`\n- Metadata `.xml`\n- Flow metadata\n- DTO / integration classes\n\nThe skill **indexes files first instead of reading them immediately**.\n\n## Required Runtime Structure\n```\n<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/\n  CASE.md\n  inputs/\n  work/\n  snippets/\n  temp_analysis/\n  outputs/\n  INDEX.md\n  MANIFEST.json\n  DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json\n  ENTRYPOINTS.json\n  EXECUTION_TRACE.md\n  FINDINGS.md\n  TEST_MATRIX.md\n  AUDIT_REPORT.md\n```\n\n## Skill Directory Structure\n```\nskills/salesforce-code-auditor/\n  SKILL.md (this file)\n  scripts/\n    init_case.py\n    index_inputs.py\n    detect_entrypoints.py\n    build_dependency_graph.py\n    extract_snippets.py\n    generate_reports.py\n    utils_fs.py\n  references/\n    FILE_TYPES.md\n    REVIEW_CHECKLISTS.md\n    TOKEN_STRATEGY.md\n    REPORT_TEMPLATE.md\n  examples/\n    example_intake.md\n    example_manifest.md\n    example_audit_report.md\n```\n\n## Analysis Methodology\nReconstruct system behavior in this order:\n\n1 — UI Layer\n  Identify entry points: Visualforce pages, Lightning Web Components, Aura Components, Flow Screens\n  Detect: buttons, actions, Apex calls, events\n\n2 — Controller Layer\n  Analyze controller classes called by the UI.\n  Detect: invoked methods, validations, business logic, SOQL queries, DML operations\n\n3 — Auxiliary Classes\n  Trace additional classes used by controllers: service classes, utility classes, validators, parsers\n\n4 — Integration and DTO Layer\n  Identify classes responsible for: callouts, response parsing, external API integrations, DTO transport objects\n\n5 — Triggers\n  Detect triggers related to objects used by the process.\n  Analyze: trigger context events, automation side effects, recursive logic risks\n\n6 — Metadata and Automation\n  Detect: flows, process builders, platform events, async logic\n\n## Token Optimization Strategy\n**Never load all code simultaneously.**\n\nProcedure:\n1. Index files using `index_inputs.py`\n2. Detect entrypoints\n3. Request specific files or snippets\n4. Extract only required methods using `extract_snippets.py`\n\nThe analysis proceeds **incrementally**.\n\n## SFDX Support\nSupports both:\n- Option A — SFDX structure: `force-app/main/default/`\n- Option B — loose files in `inputs/`\n\nThe indexing script must detect both.\n\n## Dependency Reconstruction\n`build_dependency_graph.py` must generate `DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json` containing:\n- class dependencies\n- method calls\n- trigger relationships\n- integration flows\n\n## Execution Trace\nGenerate `EXECUTION_TRACE.md` describing runtime order:\nUI → Controller → Services → Integrations → Triggers\n\n## Audit Findings\n`FINDINGS.md` must identify:\n- governor limit risks\n- SOQL in loops\n- missing FLS checks\n- mixed responsibilities\n- weak error handling\n- security vulnerabilities\n\n## Testing Matrix\nGenerate `TEST_MATRIX.md` containing:\n- scenario\n- trigger action\n- expected system behavior\n- related code location\n\n## Final Audit Report\n`AUDIT_REPORT.md` must include:\n- Summary\n- Architecture Observations\n- Technical Risks\n- Performance Risks\n- Security Risks\n- Refactor Opportunities\n- Design Alignment\n\nThe last section must compare the real code behaviour against outputs produced by the **salesforce‑architect skill** when available.\n\n## Integration with Learning System\nIf critical issues are detected append incidents to `workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n\nExample pattern keys:\n- `security|FLS_MISSING|apex`\n- `limits|SOQL_IN_LOOP|apex`\n- `architecture|MIXED_CONCERNS|controller`\n- `integration|UNHANDLED_CALLOUT_FAILURE`\n\nThen trigger error‑learning‑loop index rebuild fallback.\n\n## Demonstration Test\nRun a demo case: `demo_code_audit`\n\nThe test must:\n1. Create case folder\n2. Simulate input files\n3. Generate INDEX.md\n4. Build dependency graph\n5. Produce audit report\n\n## How to Use\n1. Ensure the skill directory is present.\n2. Run the pipeline:\n   ```bash\n   cd /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-code-auditor/scripts\n   python3 init_case.py --project-key <key> --case-id <case>\n   ```\n3. Place source files in the generated `inputs/` folder.\n4. Run the indexing:\n   ```bash\n   python3 index_inputs.py --project-key <key> --case-id <case>\n   ```\n5. Continue with detection, dependency graph, and reports.\n   ```bash\n   python3 detect_entrypoints.py --project-key <key> --case-id <case>\n   python3 build_dependency_graph.py --project-key <key> --case-id <case>\n   python3 generate_reports.py --project-key <key> --case-id <case>\n   ```\n6. For demo:\n   ```bash\n   python3 init_case.py --project-key demo --case-id demo_code_audit --demo\n   ```\n\n## Handoff Report Requirement\nEvery sub‑agent spawned by this skill must end its final response with a structured Handoff Report using this exact format:\n\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**:\n  - [TYPE=ERROR|NEAR_MISS|MISUNDERSTANDING|TOOL_FAILURE|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF; SEV=S1|S2|S3|S4] <brief symptom> (evidence: <1‑line concrete detail, no secrets>)\n  - Pattern hint: <optional>\n  - Prevention rule: <optional>\n- **Files touched**: <list or \"none\">\n- **Next action**: <1‑line suggestion>\n- **Watchdog fields** (required for monitoring):\n  - session_id: <your session identifier>\n  - run_id: <your run identifier>\n  - last_activity_at: <timestamp of last progress>\n  - progress_marker: <current step or checkpoint>\n\nIf no incidents occurred, write \"Incidents: none\"."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773075643726}}
