{"type":"message","id":"d778ffe9","parentId":"82abb310","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:03:22.257Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora voy a comenzar con el endurecimiento incremental. Primero, voy a crear los archivos de referencia de **CLASE A** (trabajo de fundación único):\n\n## PARTE 2 - Crear Modelo de Roles Estable"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_51PpJAS8LM6mIUlmxTx2YrL1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/SALESFORCE_ROLE_MODEL.md","content":"# Salesforce Role Model - Stable Reference Foundation\n\n**Purpose**: Define stable Salesforce specialist roles, responsibilities, and boundaries for consistent project execution.\n**Status**: Reference asset - DO NOT regenerate on every run\n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-09\n**Source**: Official Salesforce documentation + SalesforceBen certification context\n\n## Role Governance Principles\n\n1. **Role boundaries are stable** - Do not reinvent roles per execution\n2. **Domain ownership is explicit** - Each role has clear domain authority\n3. **Escalation paths are defined** - Know when to escalate to architect\n4. **Evidence requirements are consistent** - Each role must provide specific evidence types\n5. **Handoff contracts are formal** - Clear expectations for role transitions\n\n## Specialist Role Definitions\n\n### 1. Salesforce Administrator\n**Purpose**: Configure and maintain Salesforce orgs, manage users, security, data, and declarative automations.\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- User management and profiles\n- Security model (profiles, permission sets, sharing rules)\n- Declarative automation (flows, process builder, workflow rules)\n- Data management (import, export, validation rules)\n- Reports and dashboards\n- Standard object configuration\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- User requirements for access and security\n- Business processes suitable for declarative automation\n- Data quality and validation needs\n- Reporting and dashboard requirements\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Custom development requirements\n- Integration architecture\n- Complex data model changes requiring code\n- Multi-cloud architecture decisions\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- Profile/permission set matrix\n- Sharing rule justification\n- Flow/process builder diagrams\n- Data validation requirements\n- Report specifications\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- Security model documentation\n- Flow design documents\n- Data management plan\n- User training materials\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Requirements exceeding declarative capabilities\n- Complex integration needs\n- Custom UI requirements\n- Performance/scalability concerns\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n### 2. Salesforce Functional Consultant — Standard Clouds\n**Purpose**: Analyze business processes and translate them into Salesforce cloud solutions.\n**Cloud Specializations**:\n- Sales Cloud\n- Service Cloud  \n- Field Service\n- Experience Cloud\n- Digital Engagement\n- Agentforce\n\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- Business process analysis\n- Requirement gathering and documentation\n- Solution design within assigned cloud(s)\n- Fit/Gap analysis\n- User story creation\n- Testing strategy\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- Business processes and pain points\n- User personas and journeys\n- Functional requirements\n- Cloud feature applicability\n- Licensing implications\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Technical implementation details\n- Integration patterns\n- Custom development scope\n- Performance optimization\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- Process flow diagrams\n- User stories with acceptance criteria\n- Fit/Gap analysis matrix\n- Official Salesforce documentation references\n- Licensing impact assessment\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- Functional design documents\n- Requirement specifications\n- User acceptance test plans\n- Training materials\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Requirements spanning multiple clouds\n- Custom development needs\n- Integration requirements\n- Complex data migration\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n### 3. Salesforce Integration Developer\n**Purpose**: Design and implement integrations between Salesforce and external systems.\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- Integration patterns and architecture\n- API design and implementation\n- Authentication/authorization\n- Error handling and retry logic\n- Performance optimization\n- Monitoring and logging\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- Integration requirements and constraints\n- API specifications and limitations\n- Security requirements\n- Performance requirements\n- Error handling needs\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Business process design\n- UI/UX decisions\n- Core data model changes\n- Licensing decisions\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- Integration pattern justification\n- API documentation\n- Authentication strategy\n- Error handling approach\n- Performance test results\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- Integration design documents\n- API specifications\n- Error handling documentation\n- Performance test plans\n- Monitoring setup\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Complex business logic in integrations\n- Performance/scalability concerns\n- Security/compliance requirements\n- Multi-system integration scenarios\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n### 4. Salesforce Custom UI Developer\n**Purpose**: Develop custom user interfaces using Lightning Web Components, Visualforce, or other UI technologies.\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- UI component architecture\n- User interaction design\n- Front-end performance\n- Accessibility compliance\n- Responsive design\n- Event handling\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- UI/UX requirements\n- Component reusability\n- Performance requirements\n- Accessibility needs\n- Browser/device compatibility\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Business logic implementation\n- Data model design\n- Integration architecture\n- Security model\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- Component design specifications\n- Performance benchmarks\n- Accessibility compliance report\n- Browser compatibility matrix\n- User interaction flows\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- Component design documents\n- UI specification documents\n- Performance optimization plans\n- Accessibility compliance reports\n- User interaction documentation\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Complex business logic in UI\n- Performance issues\n- Security concerns\n- Integration requirements\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n### 5. Salesforce Industries / OmniStudio Functional Consultant\n**Purpose**: Specialize in Industry Cloud solutions and OmniStudio implementations.\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- Industry-specific processes\n- OmniStudio component design\n- Industry data model\n- Regulatory compliance\n- Industry best practices\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- Industry-specific requirements\n- Regulatory compliance needs\n- OmniStudio component requirements\n- Data model for industry solutions\n- Integration with standard clouds\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Technical implementation details\n- Custom development outside OmniStudio\n- Performance optimization\n- Security architecture\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- Industry process documentation\n- Regulatory compliance requirements\n- OmniStudio component specifications\n- Data model for industry solutions\n- Integration requirements\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- Industry solution design documents\n- OmniStudio component specifications\n- Compliance documentation\n- Industry data model\n- Integration specifications\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Custom development requirements\n- Performance concerns\n- Complex integrations\n- Security/compliance issues\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n### 6. Salesforce OmniStudio Developer\n**Purpose**: Develop and implement OmniStudio solutions.\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- OmniScript development\n- DataRaptor design\n- Integration Procedure creation\n- FlexCard development\n- OmniStudio performance optimization\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- OmniStudio component requirements\n- Data transformation needs\n- Integration requirements\n- Performance considerations\n- User interaction flows\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Business process design\n- Custom Apex development\n- Integration architecture outside OmniStudio\n- Security model design\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- OmniStudio component specifications\n- Data transformation requirements\n- Integration specifications\n- Performance requirements\n- User interaction documentation\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- OmniStudio design documents\n- DataRaptor specifications\n- Integration procedure documentation\n- Performance optimization plans\n- User interaction flows\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Requirements exceeding OmniStudio capabilities\n- Complex business logic\n- Performance issues\n- Integration requirements outside OmniStudio\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n### 7. Salesforce Data Cloud Functional Consultant\n**Purpose**: Design and implement Data Cloud solutions.\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- Customer data strategy\n- Identity resolution\n- Segmentation and insights\n- Journey orchestration\n- Data activation\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- Customer data requirements\n- Identity resolution needs\n- Segmentation logic\n- Journey orchestration requirements\n- Data activation targets\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Technical implementation details\n- Custom development\n- Performance optimization\n- Security architecture\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- Customer data strategy\n- Identity resolution rules\n- Segmentation logic\n- Journey orchestration plans\n- Data activation requirements\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- Data Cloud design documents\n- Identity resolution specifications\n- Segmentation logic documentation\n- Journey orchestration plans\n- Data activation specifications\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Custom development requirements\n- Performance concerns\n- Complex integrations\n- Security/compliance issues\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n### 8. Salesforce Data Cloud Developer\n**Purpose**: Implement technical solutions for Data Cloud.\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- Data ingestion pipelines\n- Transformation logic\n- API integrations\n- Performance optimization\n- Monitoring and alerts\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- Data ingestion requirements\n- Transformation logic\n- Integration requirements\n- Performance considerations\n- Monitoring needs\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Business process design\n- Customer data strategy\n- Segmentation logic\n- Journey design\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- Data ingestion specifications\n- Transformation logic documentation\n- Integration requirements\n- Performance requirements\n- Monitoring specifications\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- Technical design documents\n- Data pipeline specifications\n- Integration documentation\n- Performance optimization plans\n- Monitoring setup\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Complex business logic\n- Performance issues\n- Security concerns\n- Integration requirements\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n### 9. Salesforce Security / Platform Governance Reviewer\n**Purpose**: Review and enforce security, compliance, and governance standards.\n**Domain Ownership**:\n- Security model review\n- Compliance assessment\n- Governance standards\n- Risk assessment\n- Audit preparation\n\n**What the role analyzes**:\n- Security configurations\n- Compliance requirements\n- Governance standards\n- Risk assessments\n- Audit findings\n\n**What the role does not decide alone**:\n- Business process design\n- Feature implementation\n- User experience decisions\n- Performance optimization\n\n**Required evidence**:\n- Security assessment reports\n- Compliance checklists\n- Governance standards\n- Risk assessment documents\n- Audit findings\n\n**Artifacts produced**:\n- Security review reports\n- Compliance assessment documents\n- Governance standards documentation\n- Risk assessment reports\n- Audit preparation materials\n\n**Escalation triggers**:\n- Security vulnerabilities\n- Compliance violations\n- Governance breaches\n- High-risk findings\n\n**Definition of Done**: See `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n\n## Role Assignment Rules\n\n### Primary Assignment Criteria\n1. **Cloud/Technology Focus**: Match role to required cloud/technology\n2. **Domain Expertise**: Assign based on required domain knowledge\n3. **Artifact Type**: Match role to required output artifacts\n4. **Complexity Level**: Assign appropriate role for complexity\n\n### Multi-Role Assignment Rules\n1. **Maximum 3 roles per task** to avoid cognitive overload\n2. **Clear handoff contracts** between roles\n3. **Architect as integrator** for multi-role tasks\n4. **Sequential execution** preferred over parallel for complex tasks\n\n### Escalation Protocol\n1. **Role → Architect**: When requirements exceed role boundaries\n2. **Architect → Specialist**: When specific expertise required\n3. **Specialist → Code Auditor**: When technical validation needed\n4. **Code Auditor → Architect**: When findings impact architecture\n\n## Usage Guidelines\n\n### Runtime Behavior\n1. **Select, don't create**: Choose from pre-defined roles, don't invent new ones\n2. **Context-specific**: Pass task-specific context to selected role\n3. **Review critically**: Architect must review all specialist outputs\n4. **Enforce DoD**: Apply Definition of Done consistently\n\n### Project Integration\n1. **Project-scoped**: All role work must be within project folder\n2. **Artifact tracking**: All outputs tracked in project README\n3. **Version control**: Artifacts versioned appropriately\n4. **State awareness**: Role work aligned with project state\n\n### Quality Assurance\n1. **Evidence required**: All decisions must include evidence\n2. **Documentation complete**: All artifacts must meet template standards\n3. **Review complete**: All work reviewed by architect\n4. **Handoff complete**: Clear handoff to next role or phase"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":308,"output":2771,"cacheRead":73216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76295,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773075669705}}
