{"type":"message","id":"c326fdc7","parentId":"e35266ef","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:04:45.302Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_tGv5vJ2v8uBZTDvcO3ShIzus","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md","content":"# Role Assignment Rules - Stable Reference Foundation\n\n**Purpose**: Define clear rules for assigning Salesforce specialist roles to tasks.\n**Status**: Reference asset - DO NOT regenerate on every run\n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-09\n\n## Assignment Decision Matrix\n\n### Input Analysis Dimensions\n1. **Task Type**: What type of work is requested?\n2. **Cloud/Technology**: Which Salesforce cloud/technology is involved?\n3. **Complexity**: How complex is the task?\n4. **Artifact Requirements**: What artifacts need to be produced?\n5. **Evidence Requirements**: What evidence needs to be provided?\n\n### Assignment Rules by Task Type\n\n#### 1. Business Process Analysis Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Salesforce Functional Consultant\n**Secondary Role**: Salesforce Administrator (for declarative aspects)\n**Assignment Criteria**:\n- Process documentation required → Functional Consultant\n- Configuration changes needed → Administrator involvement\n- Multiple clouds involved → Architect coordinates multiple Functional Consultants\n\n#### 2. Configuration & Setup Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Salesforce Administrator\n**Secondary Role**: Functional Consultant (for business context)\n**Assignment Criteria**:\n- User management → Administrator\n- Security setup → Administrator\n- Declarative automation → Administrator\n- Complex business rules → Functional Consultant + Administrator\n\n#### 3. Custom Development Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Based on technology:\n- Apex/backend → Integration Developer\n- LWC/UI → Custom UI Developer\n- OmniStudio → OmniStudio Developer\n- Data Cloud → Data Cloud Developer\n\n**Assignment Criteria**:\n- Backend logic → Integration Developer\n- User interface → Custom UI Developer\n- Industry solutions → OmniStudio Developer\n- Customer data → Data Cloud Developer\n\n#### 4. Integration Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Salesforce Integration Developer\n**Secondary Role**: Functional Consultant (for business context)\n**Assignment Criteria**:\n- External system integration → Integration Developer\n- API development → Integration Developer\n- Data synchronization → Integration Developer\n- Business process context → Functional Consultant\n\n#### 5. Security & Governance Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Salesforce Security / Platform Governance Reviewer\n**Secondary Role**: Administrator (for implementation)\n**Assignment Criteria**:\n- Security review → Security Reviewer\n- Compliance assessment → Security Reviewer\n- Governance audit → Security Reviewer\n- Implementation → Administrator\n\n#### 6. Code Review & Audit Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Code Auditor (via salesforce-code-auditor skill)\n**Secondary Role**: Architect (for architectural impact)\n**Assignment Criteria**:\n- Technical code review → Code Auditor\n- Security audit → Code Auditor\n- Performance review → Code Auditor\n- Architectural impact → Architect review\n\n### Complexity-Based Assignment Rules\n\n#### Low Complexity Tasks\n**Definition**: Straightforward, single-domain, well-defined requirements\n**Assignment**: Single specialist role\n**Examples**:\n- Create reports/dashboards → Administrator\n- Simple flow automation → Administrator\n- Basic configuration → Administrator\n\n#### Medium Complexity Tasks\n**Definition**: Multiple components, some ambiguity, requires analysis\n**Assignment**: Primary specialist + architect oversight\n**Examples**:\n- Business process automation → Functional Consultant + Architect review\n- Custom component development → Custom UI Developer + Architect review\n- Simple integration → Integration Developer + Architect review\n\n#### High Complexity Tasks\n**Definition**: Cross-domain, ambiguous requirements, significant impact\n**Assignment**: Multiple specialists + architect coordination\n**Examples**:\n- Multi-cloud solution → Multiple Functional Consultants + Architect\n- Complex integration ecosystem → Integration Developer + Security Reviewer + Architect\n- Enterprise data strategy → Data Cloud team + Architect\n\n### Cloud-Specific Assignment Rules\n\n#### Sales Cloud Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Sales Cloud Functional Consultant\n**Supporting Roles**: Administrator, Custom UI Developer\n**Typical Tasks**:\n- Lead-to-cash process design\n- Opportunity management\n- Forecasting\n- Sales analytics\n\n#### Service Cloud Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Service Cloud Functional Consultant\n**Supporting Roles**: Administrator, OmniStudio Developer\n**Typical Tasks**:\n- Case management\n- Service analytics\n- Omni-channel routing\n- Knowledge management\n\n#### Field Service Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Field Service Functional Consultant\n**Supporting Roles**: Administrator, Integration Developer\n**Typical Tasks**:\n- Scheduling and dispatch\n- Mobile workforce management\n- Inventory management\n- Field service analytics\n\n#### Experience Cloud Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Experience Cloud Functional Consultant\n**Supporting Roles**: Administrator, Custom UI Developer\n**Typical Tasks**:\n- Community design\n- Member management\n- Content management\n- Self-service portals\n\n#### Data Cloud Tasks\n**Primary Role**: Data Cloud Functional Consultant\n**Supporting Roles**: Data Cloud Developer, Integration Developer\n**Typical Tasks**:\n- Customer data unification\n- Segmentation and insights\n- Journey orchestration\n- Data activation\n\n### Assignment Validation Rules\n\n#### Pre-Assignment Checks\n1. **Role Availability**: Is the required role defined in role model?\n2. **Domain Match**: Does task domain match role domain ownership?\n3. **Complexity Match**: Is role appropriate for task complexity?\n4. **Evidence Alignment**: Can role provide required evidence types?\n\n#### Post-Assignment Validation\n1. **Output Quality**: Does output meet Definition of Done?\n2. **Evidence Completeness**: Are all required evidence types provided?\n3. **Architect Review**: Has architect reviewed and approved output?\n4. **Project Alignment**: Is output aligned with project state and goals?\n\n### Escalation Triggers for Re-assignment\n\n#### Immediate Re-assignment Required\n1. **Role Boundary Violation**: Task requires decisions outside role boundaries\n2. **Evidence Gap**: Role cannot provide required evidence types\n3. **Complexity Mismatch**: Task complexity exceeds role capability\n4. **Domain Mismatch**: Task domain not in role domain ownership\n\n#### Architect Intervention Required\n1. **Multi-Role Coordination**: Task requires multiple specialists\n2. **Cross-Domain Impact**: Task impacts multiple domains\n3. **Architectural Decisions**: Task requires architectural decisions\n4. **Quality Issues**: Output does not meet quality standards\n\n### Runtime Assignment Logic\n\n#### Decision Flow\n```\n1. Analyze task requirements\n2. Determine task type\n3. Identify involved clouds/technologies\n4. Assess complexity level\n5. Check artifact requirements\n6. Match to role model\n7. Validate assignment\n8. Execute with architect oversight\n9. Review output against DoD\n10. Escalate if needed\n```\n\n#### Assignment Examples\n\n**Example 1: Simple Flow Automation**\n- Task: \"Create a flow to auto-assign cases based on product\"\n- Type: Configuration\n- Cloud: Service Cloud\n- Complexity: Low\n- Role: Administrator\n- Validation: Architect reviews flow design\n\n**Example 2: Custom Lead Scoring Component**\n- Task: \"Build LWC component for lead scoring dashboard\"\n- Type: Custom Development\n- Technology: LWC\n- Complexity: Medium\n- Role: Custom UI Developer\n- Validation: Architect reviews component design + Code Auditor reviews code\n\n**Example 3: ERP Integration**\n- Task: \"Integrate Salesforce with SAP for order sync\"\n- Type: Integration\n- Complexity: High\n- Role: Integration Developer + Functional Consultant\n- Validation: Architect reviews integration design + Security Reviewer assesses security\n\n### Assignment Logging Requirements\n\n#### Required Log Fields\n1. **Task ID**: Unique identifier for the task\n2. **Assigned Role**: Primary role assigned\n3. **Supporting Roles**: Additional roles involved\n4. **Assignment Rationale**: Why this role was chosen\n5. **Complexity Assessment**: Low/Medium/High\n6. **Expected Outputs**: List of expected artifacts\n7. **Actual Outputs**: List of delivered artifacts\n8. **Quality Assessment**: Pass/Fail against DoD\n9. **Escalation Events**: Any reassignments or architect interventions\n\n#### Log Location\n- Project folder: `<project_key>/role_assignments.log`\n- Skill references: For pattern analysis and improvement\n\n### Continuous Improvement\n\n#### Assignment Pattern Analysis\n1. **Success Patterns**: What assignments work well?\n2. **Failure Patterns**: What assignments frequently fail?\n3. **Role Gaps**: Are there missing roles in the model?\n4. **Rule Gaps**: Are there missing assignment rules?\n\n#### Model Updates\n1. **Quarterly Review**: Review and update role model\n2. **Incident-Driven Updates**: Update based on assignment failures\n3. **Technology Updates**: Update for new Salesforce features\n4. **Complexity Refinement**: Refine complexity assessment rules"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":64,"output":1844,"cacheRead":76288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78196,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773075802287}}
