{"type":"message","id":"c5f119c3","parentId":"f9d60de5","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:06:50.614Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## PARTE 3 - Definir Máquina de Estados del Proyecto Salesforce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_r3ZbmbjdxAE2OV0FCTwdNJIQ","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/SALESFORCE_PROJECT_STATE_MACHINE.md","content":"# Salesforce Project State Machine - Stable Reference Foundation\n\n**Purpose**: Define formal lifecycle states for Salesforce projects with clear entry/exit conditions.\n**Status**: Reference asset - DO NOT regenerate on every run\n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-09\n\n## State Machine Overview\n\n### Lifecycle States\n```\nDISCOVERY → REQUIREMENTS → FIT_GAP → DESIGN → DATA_MODEL → ARCH_REVIEW → CODE_AUDIT → REMEDIATION → FINALIZED\n```\n\n### State Transition Rules\n1. **Sequential by default**: States generally progress in order\n2. **Conditional transitions**: Some states can be skipped based on conditions\n3. **Regression allowed**: Can return to previous states if needed\n4. **Blocking conditions**: Some transitions have mandatory prerequisites\n\n## State Definitions\n\n### DISCOVERY\n**Purpose**: Gather initial information about business processes, actors, and systems.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- Project key identified\n- Initial business context provided\n- No existing discovery artifacts for this project\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- `Discovery_Report.md`\n- `Discovery_Process_Analysis.md`\n- `Discovery_QA.xlsx`\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- Missing mandatory inputs (project name, industry, country, clouds, user count, process description, scope)\n- Incomplete actor/process identification\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- REQUIREMENTS (default)\n- FIT_GAP (if scope/SOW provided)\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Direct to DESIGN (must go through REQUIREMENTS or FIT_GAP first)\n- Direct to FINALIZED\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Validate completeness of discovery\n- Identify missing information\n- Ensure EC0249 compliance\n- Emit incidents for blocking conditions\n\n### REQUIREMENTS\n**Purpose**: Transform discovery into structured, actionable requirements.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- DISCOVERY artifacts complete and validated\n- All mandatory inputs available\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- Consolidated requirements list\n- Requirement prioritization\n- Acceptance criteria per requirement\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- Incomplete discovery\n- Unclear acceptance criteria\n- Missing stakeholder validation\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- FIT_GAP (if scope/SOW available)\n- DESIGN (if requirements complete and validated)\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Back to DISCOVERY unless major gaps found\n- Direct to CODE_AUDIT\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Validate requirement completeness\n- Ensure traceability to discovery\n- Prioritize requirements\n- Validate acceptance criteria\n\n### FIT_GAP\n**Purpose**: Analyze requirements against available Salesforce features and identify gaps.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- REQUIREMENTS complete OR DISCOVERY complete with scope/SOW\n- Scope/SOW document available\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- `Fit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx` with columns:\n  - ReqID, Process, Requirement, Fit/GAP, Justification\n  - Time impact, Cost impact, Implementation type\n  - License dependency, Risk, Evidence link, Status\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- Missing scope/SOW document\n- Incomplete requirements\n- Unclear licensing constraints\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- DESIGN (default)\n- REQUIREMENTS (if gaps reveal missing requirements)\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Direct to DATA_MODEL (must go through DESIGN first)\n- Direct to FINALIZED\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Validate scope/SOW availability\n- Ensure proper Fit/GAP classification\n- Document licensing impacts\n- Identify architectural implications of gaps\n\n### DESIGN\n**Purpose**: Create functional design based on requirements and Fit/GAP analysis.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- FIT_GAP complete OR REQUIREMENTS complete (if no Fit/GAP needed)\n- Clear understanding of what will be built vs. gaps\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- `Functional_Design.docx` following reference template\n- Architecture alternatives (2-3 options)\n- Pros/cons analysis\n- Licensing impact assessment\n- Official documentation evidence\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- Unresolved Fit/GAP items\n- Missing evidence for key decisions\n- Unclear licensing constraints\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- DATA_MODEL (default)\n- ARCH_REVIEW (for complex designs)\n- FIT_GAP (if design reveals new gaps)\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Direct to CODE_AUDIT (must have data model first)\n- Direct to FINALIZED\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Ensure design follows template\n- Validate evidence for decisions\n- Conduct debate mode for alternatives\n- Document architectural decisions\n\n### DATA_MODEL\n**Purpose**: Design detailed data model supporting the functional design.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- DESIGN complete and validated\n- Clear understanding of data requirements\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- `Data_Model.xlsx` following reference template\n- Object definitions with fields, types, relationships\n- Validation rules\n- Record types\n- Indexing considerations\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- Incomplete functional design\n- Unclear data relationships\n- Missing validation requirements\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- ARCH_REVIEW (default)\n- DESIGN (if data model reveals design issues)\n- CODE_AUDIT (if existing code needs review)\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Direct to REMEDIATION\n- Direct to FINALIZED\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Validate data model completeness\n- Ensure relationship integrity\n- Consider performance implications\n- Document data governance requirements\n\n### ARCH_REVIEW\n**Purpose**: Architectural review and validation of design and data model.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- DESIGN and DATA_MODEL complete\n- OR specific architectural review requested\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- Architecture review report\n- Risk assessment\n- Scalability analysis\n- Security assessment\n- Integration impact analysis\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- Missing design or data model artifacts\n- Unresolved architectural risks\n- Unvalidated assumptions\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- CODE_AUDIT (if code review needed)\n- REMEDIATION (if issues found)\n- FINALIZED (if no issues and no code audit needed)\n- DESIGN/DATA_MODEL (if major issues found)\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Direct to DISCOVERY\n- Direct to REQUIREMENTS\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Conduct comprehensive architectural review\n- Identify risks and mitigation strategies\n- Validate against Salesforce limits and best practices\n- Make go/no-go decision for implementation\n\n### CODE_AUDIT\n**Purpose**: Technical review of existing or proposed code.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- ARCH_REVIEW complete OR specific code audit requested\n- Code available for review\n- Clear audit objectives\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- Code audit report\n- Findings with severity levels\n- Code snippets as evidence\n- Remediation suggestions\n- Impact assessment\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- No code available for audit\n- Unclear audit objectives\n- Missing context about code purpose\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- REMEDIATION (if findings require fixes)\n- ARCH_REVIEW (for architectural impact assessment)\n- FINALIZED (if no significant findings)\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Direct to DESIGN\n- Direct to DATA_MODEL\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Define audit scope and objectives\n- Review audit findings\n- Assess architectural impact\n- Decide remediation requirements\n\n### REMEDIATION\n**Purpose**: Address issues found during code audit or architectural review.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- CODE_AUDIT or ARCH_REVIEW identified issues requiring fixes\n- Clear remediation plan\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- Remediation plan\n- Updated artifacts (design, data model, code)\n- Validation of fixes\n- Updated risk assessment\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- Unclear remediation requirements\n- Missing approval for changes\n- Unresolved dependencies\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- CODE_AUDIT (for re-audit of fixes)\n- ARCH_REVIEW (for re-review of changes)\n- FINALIZED (when all issues resolved)\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Direct to DISCOVERY\n- Direct to REQUIREMENTS\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Approve remediation plan\n- Validate fixes\n- Update architectural documentation\n- Ensure no regression of existing functionality\n\n### FINALIZED\n**Purpose**: Project completion with all artifacts finalized and approved.\n\n**Entry Conditions**:\n- All previous states complete and validated\n- All artifacts approved\n- No open critical issues\n- Stakeholder sign-off (if required)\n\n**Required Artifacts**:\n- Final project package\n- Executive summary\n- Lessons learned\n- Handoff documentation\n\n**Blocking Conditions**:\n- Open critical issues\n- Missing stakeholder approval (if required)\n- Incomplete artifacts\n\n**Allowed Next States**:\n- None (terminal state)\n- Can re-enter DISCOVERY for new phase/version\n\n**Prohibited Transitions**:\n- Any transition from FINALIZED except new project phase\n\n**Architect Responsibilities**:\n- Final validation of all artifacts\n- Ensure completeness of documentation\n- Document lessons learned\n- Formal project closure\n\n## Hard Rules and Constraints\n\n### Absolute Prohibitions\n1. **No FIT_GAP without scope/SOW**: Must have scope document for classification\n2. **No DESIGN without consolidated discovery**: Must understand what's being built\n3. **No FINALIZED with critical audit findings**: All critical issues must be resolved\n4. **No CODE_AUDIT without clear objectives**: Must know what to look for\n\n### Mandatory Validations\n1. **Evidence validation**: All decisions must have official documentation evidence\n2. **Licensing validation**: All features must be validated against available licenses\n3. **Limit validation**: All designs must respect Salesforce limits\n4. **Security validation**: All designs must follow security best practices\n\n### State Persistence Rules\n1. **Project README must track current state**\n2. **State transitions must be logged**\n3. **Artifacts must be versioned per state**\n4. **Rollback must be possible to previous states**\n\n## Runtime Behavior Requirements\n\n### State Detection\nAt runtime, the architect must:\n1. Check project folder for existing artifacts\n2. Determine current state based on artifact completeness\n3. Validate state consistency\n4. Log state detection results\n\n### State Transition Validation\nBefore any state transition, the architect must:\n1. Validate entry conditions for target state\n2. Check for blocking conditions\n3. Ensure required artifacts exist and are complete\n4. Log transition with rationale\n\n### Artifact Management\nFor each state, the architect must:\n1. Ensure artifacts are created in project folder\n2. Version artifacts appropriately\n3. Validate artifact completeness against templates\n4. Update project README with artifact versions\n\n### Incident Reporting\nFor state machine violations, emit incidents:\n- `salesforce|STATE_MACHINE|missing_prerequisite|blocked`\n- `salesforce|STATE_MACHINE|invalid_transition|rejected`\n- `salesforce|STATE_MACHINE|artifact_incomplete|blocked`\n- `salesforce|STATE_MACHINE|blocking_condition|requires_action`\n\n## Project README Integration\n\n### Required README Sections\n```\n# Project: <project_key>\n\n## Current State: <state>\n- Entered: <timestamp>\n- Validated: <timestamp>\n\n## State History\n- DISCOVERY: <start> - <end>\n- REQUIREMENTS: <start> - <end>\n- ...\n\n## Artifact Versions\n- Discovery: v1\n- Requirements: v1\n- Fit/Gap: v1\n- Design: v2\n- Data Model: v1\n- Architecture Review: v1\n- Code Audit: v1\n- Remediation: v1\n\n## Next Actions\n- [ ] Action 1\n- [ ] Action 2\n```\n\n### README Update Triggers\n1. **State transition**: Update current state and history\n2. **Artifact creation**: Update artifact versions\n3. **Issue identification**: Update next actions\n4. **Validation complete**: Update validation timestamps\n\n## Quality Gates\n\n### State Completion Criteria\nEach state must meet specific completion criteria before transition:\n1. **Artifacts complete**: All required artifacts created and validated\n2. **Quality validated**: Artifacts meet quality standards\n3. **Evidence complete**: All decisions have supporting evidence\n4. **Risks identified**: All risks identified and documented\n\n### Architectural Review Gates\nMandatory architectural review at:\n1. **DESIGN completion**: Validate design decisions\n2. **DATA_MODEL completion**: Validate data architecture\n3. **CODE_AUDIT findings**: Validate impact of findings\n4. **FINALIZATION**: Final architectural sign-off\n\n### Continuous Validation\nThroughout all states:\n1. **Licensing compliance**: Continuous validation against available licenses\n2. **Security compliance**: Continuous security validation\n3. **Performance considerations**: Continuous performance assessment\n4. **Scalability considerations**: Continuous scalability assessment"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":109,"output":2813,"cacheRead":78144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81066,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773075885313}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb966254","parentId":"c5f119c3","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:06:50.668Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_r3ZbmbjdxAE2OV0FCTwdNJIQ","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 12404 bytes to /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/SALESFORCE_PROJECT_STATE_MACHINE.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773076010640}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebad4311","parentId":"cb966254","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:09:15.704Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## PARTE 4 - Definir Definition of Done por Rol"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WOtrdfhLLThIEzIPIDelaKJn","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md","content":"# Definition of Done by Role - Stable Reference Foundation\n\n**Purpose**: Define explicit completion criteria for each Salesforce specialist role.\n**Status**: Reference asset - DO NOT regenerate on every run\n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-09\n\n## DoD Governance Principles\n\n1. **Role-specific**: Each role has unique completion criteria\n2. **Evidence-based**: Completion requires specific evidence types\n3. **Architect-validated**: Architect must validate against DoD\n4. **Project-aligned**: DoD criteria align with project state and goals\n\n## Role Definitions of Done\n\n### 1. Salesforce Administrator\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- Configuration specifications\n- Security model documentation\n- Automation design documents\n- Data management plans\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **User Management**:\n   - Profile/permission set matrix complete\n   - Role hierarchy documented\n   - Sharing rules justified and documented\n   - Login/IP restrictions specified\n\n2. **Security Model**:\n   - Object/field-level security documented\n   - Record sharing model defined\n   - Audit trail requirements specified\n   - Compliance requirements addressed\n\n3. **Declarative Automation**:\n   - Flow/process builder diagrams complete\n   - Decision logic documented\n   - Error handling specified\n   - Performance considerations noted\n\n4. **Data Management**:\n   - Validation rules documented\n   - Data import/export procedures defined\n   - Data quality rules specified\n   - Archival/purge policies defined\n\n5. **Reports & Dashboards**:\n   - Report specifications complete\n   - Dashboard requirements documented\n   - Scheduling requirements specified\n   - Access controls defined\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ All configurations documented in standard templates\n- ✅ Security model reviewed for compliance\n- ✅ Automation flows validated for business logic\n- ✅ Data management procedures tested\n- ✅ Reports/dashboards meet user requirements\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Security model aligns with business requirements\n- [ ] Automation designs are maintainable\n- [ ] Data management procedures are practical\n- [ ] Performance implications considered\n- [ ] Documentation complete and clear\n\n### 2. Salesforce Functional Consultant\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- Process analysis documents\n- Requirement specifications\n- Fit/Gap analysis\n- Solution design documents\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **Process Analysis**:\n   - Current/future state process maps\n   - Pain points and opportunities identified\n   - Actor/role mappings complete\n   - System interactions documented\n\n2. **Requirements**:\n   - User stories with acceptance criteria\n   - Requirement prioritization\n   - Dependencies identified\n   - Assumptions documented\n\n3. **Fit/Gap Analysis**:\n   - Clear Fit vs. GAP classification\n   - Justification for each classification\n   - Licensing impact assessment\n   - Customization requirements identified\n\n4. **Solution Design**:\n   - Cloud feature mapping complete\n   - Configuration vs. customization decisions\n   - Integration points identified\n   - Data requirements documented\n\n5. **Business Context**:\n   - Industry-specific considerations\n   - Regulatory compliance requirements\n   - Organizational change impact\n   - Training requirements identified\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ Processes mapped to Salesforce capabilities\n- ✅ Requirements traceable to business needs\n- ✅ Fit/Gap analysis supported by evidence\n- ✅ Solution design aligns with licensing\n- ✅ Business context fully considered\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Processes optimized for Salesforce\n- [ ] Requirements complete and unambiguous\n- [ ] Fit/Gap analysis accurate and justified\n- [ ] Solution design technically feasible\n- [ ] Business risks identified and addressed\n\n### 3. Salesforce Integration Developer\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- Integration design documents\n- API specifications\n- Error handling documentation\n- Performance test plans\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **Integration Design**:\n   - Integration pattern selected and justified\n   - Data flow diagrams complete\n   - Transformation logic documented\n   - Synchronization strategy defined\n\n2. **API Specifications**:\n   - Endpoint definitions complete\n   - Request/response formats documented\n   - Authentication/authorization specified\n   - Rate limiting considerations noted\n\n3. **Error Handling**:\n   - Error classification (transient/permanent)\n   - Retry logic defined\n   - Alerting/monitoring requirements\n   - Recovery procedures documented\n\n4. **Performance**:\n   - Performance requirements documented\n   - Load testing strategy defined\n   - Bottleneck identification\n   - Scaling considerations noted\n\n5. **Security**:\n   - Data encryption requirements\n   - Access control mechanisms\n   - Audit logging requirements\n   - Compliance considerations\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ Integration design follows best practices\n- ✅ API specifications complete and testable\n- ✅ Error handling robust and documented\n- ✅ Performance requirements achievable\n- ✅ Security requirements addressed\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Integration pattern appropriate for use case\n- [ ] API design follows REST/GraphQL best practices\n- [ ] Error handling strategy comprehensive\n- [ ] Performance implications understood\n- [ ] Security model robust and compliant\n\n### 4. Salesforce Custom UI Developer\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- Component design documents\n- UI specification documents\n- Performance optimization plans\n- Accessibility compliance reports\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **Component Design**:\n   - Component architecture documented\n   - Reusability analysis complete\n   - State management strategy defined\n   - Event handling documented\n\n2. **UI Specifications**:\n   - Wireframes/mockups complete\n   - User interaction flows documented\n   - Responsive design requirements\n   - Browser/device compatibility matrix\n\n3. **Performance**:\n   - Performance benchmarks established\n   - Optimization opportunities identified\n   - Lazy loading strategy defined\n   - Caching strategy documented\n\n4. **Accessibility**:\n   - WCAG compliance level specified\n   - Screen reader compatibility tested\n   - Keyboard navigation documented\n   - Color contrast requirements met\n\n5. **Testing**:\n   - Unit test coverage requirements\n   - Integration test scenarios\n   - User acceptance test criteria\n   - Performance test plans\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ Component design follows LWC/Aura best practices\n- ✅ UI specifications complete and implementable\n- ✅ Performance optimization adequate\n- ✅ Accessibility requirements met\n- ✅ Testing strategy comprehensive\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Component architecture maintainable\n- [ ] UI design aligns with Salesforce design system\n- [ ] Performance optimization appropriate\n- [ ] Accessibility compliance verified\n- [ ] Testing strategy adequate\n\n### 5. Salesforce Industries / OmniStudio Functional Consultant\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- Industry solution design documents\n- OmniStudio component specifications\n- Compliance documentation\n- Industry data model\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **Industry Analysis**:\n   - Industry-specific processes documented\n   - Regulatory requirements identified\n   - Compliance gaps analyzed\n   - Industry best practices applied\n\n2. **OmniStudio Design**:\n   - OmniScript requirements documented\n   - DataRaptor transformation logic\n   - Integration Procedure specifications\n   - FlexCard design requirements\n\n3. **Compliance**:\n   - Regulatory compliance matrix\n   - Audit trail requirements\n   - Reporting requirements\n   - Data retention policies\n\n4. **Data Model**:\n   - Industry-specific objects/fields\n   - Relationship mappings\n   - Validation rules\n   - Data governance requirements\n\n5. **Integration**:\n   - Integration with standard clouds\n   - Data synchronization requirements\n   - API consumption needs\n   - External system interfaces\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ Industry requirements fully captured\n- ✅ OmniStudio design follows best practices\n- ✅ Compliance requirements addressed\n- ✅ Data model supports industry processes\n- ✅ Integration requirements defined\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Industry analysis comprehensive\n- [ ] OmniStudio design optimal for requirements\n- [ ] Compliance requirements fully addressed\n- [ ] Data model supports business processes\n- [ ] Integration approach feasible\n\n### 6. Salesforce OmniStudio Developer\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- OmniStudio design documents\n- DataRaptor specifications\n- Integration procedure documentation\n- Performance optimization plans\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **OmniStudio Implementation**:\n   - OmniScript design complete\n   - DataRaptor transformations documented\n   - Integration Procedure logic defined\n   - FlexCard implementation specifications\n\n2. **Performance**:\n   - Performance benchmarks established\n   - Optimization opportunities identified\n   - Caching strategy documented\n   - Load testing requirements\n\n3. **Testing**:\n   - Unit test coverage\n   - Integration test scenarios\n   - User acceptance test criteria\n   - Performance test results\n\n4. **Documentation**:\n   - Technical design documents\n   - User guides\n   - Administration guides\n   - Troubleshooting guides\n\n5. **Maintenance**:\n   - Monitoring requirements\n   - Alerting configuration\n   - Backup/recovery procedures\n   - Version upgrade plans\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ OmniStudio implementation follows best practices\n- ✅ Performance requirements met\n- ✅ Testing comprehensive\n- ✅ Documentation complete\n- ✅ Maintenance procedures defined\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Implementation optimal for requirements\n- [ ] Performance adequate for expected load\n- [ ] Testing strategy comprehensive\n- [ ] Documentation usable by target audience\n- [ ] Maintenance procedures practical\n\n### 7. Salesforce Data Cloud Functional Consultant\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- Data Cloud design documents\n- Identity resolution specifications\n- Segmentation logic documentation\n- Journey orchestration plans\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **Data Strategy**:\n   - Customer data unification approach\n   - Identity resolution rules defined\n   - Data quality requirements\n   - Governance policies documented\n\n2. **Segmentation**:\n   - Segmentation logic documented\n   - Audience definitions complete\n   - Personalization requirements\n   - Activation criteria defined\n\n3. **Journey Design**:\n   - Customer journey maps\n   - Orchestration logic documented\n   - Trigger conditions defined\n   - Measurement criteria established\n\n4. **Activation**:\n   - Activation targets identified\n   - Channel requirements documented\n   - Content personalization needs\n   - Measurement and optimization\n\n5. **Governance**:\n   - Data privacy requirements\n   - Compliance considerations\n   - Access control requirements\n   - Audit trail specifications\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ Data strategy supports business objectives\n- ✅ Segmentation logic accurate and actionable\n- ✅ Journey design optimized for customer experience\n- ✅ Activation approach feasible\n- ✅ Governance requirements addressed\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Data strategy aligns with business goals\n- [ ] Segmentation logic technically feasible\n- [ ] Journey design implementable\n- [ ] Activation approach practical\n- [ ] Governance model compliant\n\n### 8. Salesforce Data Cloud Developer\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- Technical design documents\n- Data pipeline specifications\n- Integration documentation\n- Performance optimization plans\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **Data Pipeline**:\n   - Ingestion pipeline design\n   - Transformation logic documented\n   - Quality validation rules\n   - Error handling procedures\n\n2. **Integration**:\n   - Source system interfaces\n   - API consumption specifications\n   - Data synchronization logic\n   - Real-time/batch processing requirements\n\n3. **Performance**:\n   - Performance requirements documented\n   - Scaling strategy defined\n   - Monitoring requirements\n   - Optimization opportunities identified\n\n4. **Security**:\n   - Data encryption requirements\n   - Access control mechanisms\n   - Audit logging specifications\n   - Compliance considerations\n\n5. **Operations**:\n   - Deployment procedures\n   - Monitoring and alerting\n   - Backup/recovery plans\n   - Maintenance procedures\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ Data pipeline design robust and scalable\n- ✅ Integration approach feasible\n- ✅ Performance requirements achievable\n- ✅ Security requirements addressed\n- ✅ Operations procedures defined\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Pipeline design follows best practices\n- [ ] Integration approach optimal\n- [ ] Performance strategy adequate\n- [ ] Security model compliant\n- [ ] Operations procedures practical\n\n### 9. Salesforce Security / Platform Governance Reviewer\n\n**Core Deliverables**:\n- Security review reports\n- Compliance assessment documents\n- Governance standards documentation\n- Risk assessment reports\n\n**Required Evidence**:\n1. **Security Assessment**:\n   - Vulnerability analysis complete\n   - Threat modeling documented\n   - Risk assessment matrix\n   - Mitigation recommendations\n\n2. **Compliance Review**:\n   - Regulatory requirements mapped\n   - Compliance gaps identified\n   - Remediation requirements documented\n   - Audit preparation checklist\n\n3. **Governance Standards**:\n   - Development standards documented\n   - Deployment procedures defined\n   - Change management processes\n   - Quality assurance requirements\n\n4. **Risk Assessment**:\n   - Risk identification complete\n   - Impact analysis documented\n   - Probability assessment\n   - Mitigation strategies defined\n\n5. **Audit Preparation**:\n   - Evidence collection procedures\n   - Documentation requirements\n   - Stakeholder communication plans\n   - Remediation tracking procedures\n\n**Quality Gates**:\n- ✅ Security assessment comprehensive\n- ✅ Compliance review complete\n- ✅ Governance standards practical\n- ✅ Risk assessment accurate\n- ✅ Audit preparation adequate\n\n**Architect Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Security findings actionable\n- [ ] Compliance gaps addressable\n- [ ] Governance standards enforceable\n- [ ] Risk assessment realistic\n- [ ] Audit preparation sufficient\n\n## DoD Enforcement Protocol\n\n### Validation Workflow\n```\n1. Specialist completes work\n2. Specialist self-validates against role DoD\n3. Specialist submits to architect for review\n4. Architect validates against DoD checklist\n5. Architect either:\n   - Approves (DoD met)\n   - Requests corrections (DoD not met)\n   - Escalates (major issues found)\n```\n\n### Rejection Criteria\nWork must be rejected if:\n1. **Missing required evidence types**\n2. **Quality gates not passed**\n3. **Architect validation checklist items failed**\n4. **Project alignment issues**\n5. **State machine violations**\n\n### Correction Protocol\nWhen work is rejected:\n1. **Specific feedback** on DoD failures\n2. **Clear correction requirements**\n3. **Priority classification** (blocking vs. non-blocking)\n4. **Timeline for corrections**\n5. **Re-validation process**\n\n### DoD Compliance Tracking\n**Required tracking**:\n- DoD validation per role per task\n- Rejection rates and reasons\n- Correction turnaround times\n- Quality trends over time\n\n**Tracking location**: Project folder + skill references for pattern analysis\n\n## Continuous Improvement\n\n### DoD Refinement Process\n1. **Quarterly review** of DoD effectiveness\n2. **Incident analysis** for DoD-related issues\n3. **Role feedback** incorporation\n4. **Technology updates** reflection\n\n### Success Metrics\n1. **First-time approval rate** (target: >80%)\n2. **Correction turnaround time** (target: <24 hours)\n3. **Architect review efficiency** (target: <30 minutes per review)\n4. **Quality improvement trends** (measured over time)\n\n### DoD Evolution Rules\n1. **Backward compatibility**: New DoD versions must not invalidate previous work\n2. **Stakeholder alignment**: DoD changes require architect approval\n3. **Documentation updates**: DoD changes must be documented\n4. **Training requirements**: DoD changes may require role training updates"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":102,"output":3319,"cacheRead":81024,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773076010659}}
