{"type":"message","id":"22ec9221","parentId":"79bb8034","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:10:14.382Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## PARTE 5 - Definir Contrato de Gobernanza Arquitecto ↔ Auditor de Código"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_D3QAkS2aGB4ThGwM24E1Swaz","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md","content":"# Code Audit Handoff Modes - Stable Reference Foundation\n\n**Purpose**: Define formal governance contract between architect and code auditor with clear modes, contracts, and escalation paths.\n**Status**: Reference asset - DO NOT regenerate on every run\n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-09\n\n## Handoff Governance Principles\n\n1. **Clear mode selection**: Each audit request must specify handoff mode\n2. **Formal contracts**: Required inputs and outputs defined per mode\n3. **Severity handling**: Clear protocol for handling findings by severity\n4. **Architectural impact**: Findings must be assessed for architectural impact\n5. **Project integration**: All audits must be project-scoped and tracked\n\n## Handoff Modes\n\n### Mode A — Architecture → Code Audit\n**Use when**: Architect needs current-state technical truth before design decisions.\n\n**Typical Scenarios**:\n- Understanding existing codebase before redesign\n- Assessing technical debt impact on new design\n- Validating assumptions about current implementation\n- Identifying constraints for new architecture\n\n**Required Request Contract from Architect**:\n```\n## Code Audit Request - Mode A\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Architecture → Code Audit\n**Request Timestamp**: <timestamp>\n\n### Audit Objectives\n1. Primary objective: <clear statement>\n2. Secondary objectives: <list>\n3. Specific questions to answer: <list>\n\n### Scope Definition\n- **In Scope**: <specific components, files, areas>\n- **Out of Scope**: <components to exclude>\n- **Depth**: Deep/Medium/Shallow review\n\n### Context Provided\n- Business context: <summary>\n- Architectural context: <current understanding>\n- Known issues: <any known problems>\n- Constraints: <technical/business constraints>\n\n### Success Criteria\n- Must identify: <specific items>\n- Must assess: <specific aspects>\n- Must provide: <specific outputs>\n```\n\n**Required Output Contract from Auditor**:\n```\n## Code Audit Report - Mode A\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Architecture → Code Audit\n**Completion Timestamp**: <timestamp>\n\n### Executive Summary\n- Overall assessment: <summary>\n- Key findings: <bullet points>\n- Architectural implications: <summary>\n\n### Technical Truth Assessment\n- Current implementation reality: <description>\n- Gap vs. assumed reality: <analysis>\n- Constraints identified: <list>\n\n### Findings by Category\n#### 1. Architecture & Design\n- Findings: <list with evidence>\n- Impact: <architectural impact>\n- Recommendations: <suggestions>\n\n#### 2. Technical Debt\n- Findings: <list with evidence>\n- Impact: <on new design>\n- Recommendations: <suggestions>\n\n#### 3. Constraints & Limitations\n- Findings: <list with evidence>\n- Impact: <on design decisions>\n- Workarounds: <if available>\n\n### Answers to Architect Questions\n1. Question: <original question>\n   Answer: <detailed answer with evidence>\n   Confidence: High/Medium/Low\n\n### Architectural Recommendations\n- Design considerations: <based on findings>\n- Risk mitigation: <suggestions>\n- Implementation approach: <recommendations>\n```\n\n### Mode B — Code Audit → Architecture\n**Use when**: Audit findings must change architecture decisions.\n\n**Typical Scenarios**:\n- Critical security findings requiring design changes\n- Performance issues impacting architecture\n- Scalability constraints requiring redesign\n- Compliance violations needing architectural fixes\n\n**Required Request Contract from Architect**:\n```\n## Code Audit Request - Mode B\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Code Audit → Architecture\n**Request Timestamp**: <timestamp>\n\n### Trigger for Audit\n- Initial finding: <what triggered need for audit>\n- Concern: <specific concern about implementation>\n- Risk: <perceived risk needing validation>\n\n### Focus Areas\n- **Primary focus**: <area of greatest concern>\n- **Secondary focus**: <additional areas>\n- **Validation needed**: <what needs to be validated>\n\n### Decision Context\n- Current architecture: <brief description>\n- Pending decisions: <decisions awaiting audit results>\n- Timeline constraints: <any time pressures>\n- Stakeholder concerns: <specific stakeholder worries>\n\n### Success Criteria\n- Must validate/invalidate: <specific concerns>\n- Must provide evidence: <for architectural decisions>\n- Must assess impact: <on current architecture>\n```\n\n**Required Output Contract from Auditor**:\n```\n## Code Audit Report - Mode B\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Code Audit → Architecture\n**Completion Timestamp**: <timestamp>\n\n### Executive Summary\n- Validation result: <concerns validated/invalidated>\n- Criticality assessment: <overall criticality>\n- Urgency: <immediate/short-term/long-term>\n\n### Findings Requiring Architectural Change\n#### 1. Critical Findings\n- Finding: <description with evidence>\n- Architectural impact: <specific impact>\n- Required change: <what must change>\n- Priority: Critical/High/Medium\n\n#### 2. Design Flaws\n- Finding: <description with evidence>\n- Root cause: <architectural root cause>\n- Required redesign: <what needs redesign>\n- Alternatives: <possible alternatives>\n\n#### 3. Compliance Gaps\n- Finding: <description with evidence>\n- Regulation/standard: <specific requirement>\n- Architectural fix: <required architectural change>\n- Verification: <how to verify fix>\n\n### Impact Assessment\n#### On Current Design\n- Components affected: <list>\n- Design changes required: <specific changes>\n- Ripple effects: <other areas impacted>\n\n#### On Implementation\n- Effort estimate: <implementation effort>\n- Risk during change"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1773076155749,"errorMessage":"Request was aborted"}}
