{"type":"message","id":"059b0d69","parentId":"b1d65627","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:25:25.182Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora voy a crear el **ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md** que también es parte del trabajo de fundación:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WV6yyZHyLDjJaRMEESniMgju","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md","content":"# Architect Review Protocol - Stable Reference Foundation\n\n**Purpose**: Define standardized review process for architect validation of specialist outputs.\n**Status**: Reference asset - DO NOT regenerate on every run\n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-09\n\n## Review Governance Principles\n\n1. **Consistent process**: Same review steps for all specialist outputs\n2. **Evidence-based**: All validations require evidence\n3. **Role-appropriate**: Review criteria tailored to specialist role\n4. **Project-aligned**: Review considers project state and goals\n5. **Actionable feedback**: Clear guidance for corrections when needed\n\n## Review Workflow\n\n### Step 1: Submission Validation\n**Purpose**: Ensure work is ready for architect review.\n\n**Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Work submitted by authorized specialist role\n- [ ] All required artifacts present\n- [ ] Artifacts follow naming conventions\n- [ ] Artifacts placed in correct project location\n- [ ] Self-validation against DoD completed by specialist\n\n**Rejection Criteria**:\n- Missing required artifacts\n- Artifacts outside project folder\n- Naming convention violations\n- No self-validation completed\n\n**Incident if rejected**:\n- `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|submission_invalid|missing_artifacts`\n\n### Step 2: Role-Specific DoD Validation\n**Purpose**: Validate against Definition of Done for specific role.\n\n**Process**:\n1. Load appropriate DoD from `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md`\n2. Validate each DoD criterion\n3. Document validation results\n4. Identify gaps\n\n**Validation Output**:\n```\n## DoD Validation Results - <Role> - <Timestamp>\n\n### Criteria Met (✅)\n1. <criterion 1>\n2. <criterion 2>\n\n### Criteria Partially Met (⚠️)\n1. <criterion 3> - <gap description>\n2. <criterion 4> - <gap description>\n\n### Criteria Not Met (❌)\n1. <criterion 5> - <gap description>\n2. <criterion 6> - <gap description>\n\n### Overall Assessment\n- DoD Compliance: <percentage>%\n- Blocking Issues: <count>\n- Non-blocking Issues: <count>\n```\n\n**Rejection Criteria**:\n- Critical DoD criteria not met (❌)\n- Multiple major gaps (⚠️) affecting quality\n- Evidence missing for key decisions\n\n**Incident if rejected**:\n- `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|dod_not_met|<role>_<criterion>`\n\n### Step 3: Project State Alignment\n**Purpose**: Ensure work aligns with current project state.\n\n**Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] Work appropriate for current state (per state machine)\n- [ ] Artifacts versioned correctly\n- [ ] Dependencies on previous artifacts maintained\n- [ ] No regression of previous decisions\n- [ ] State transition readiness assessed\n\n**State-Specific Validations**:\n\n**DISCOVERY phase work**:\n- [ ] EC0249 compliance verified\n- [ ] All mandatory inputs addressed\n- [ ] Process analysis complete\n- [ ] Actor identification complete\n\n**DESIGN phase work**:\n- [ ] Follows functional design template\n- [ ] Evidence for all decisions provided\n- [ ] Licensing constraints considered\n- [ ] Architecture alternatives presented\n\n**CODE_AUDIT phase work**:\n- [ ] Audit objectives met\n- [ ] Findings severity appropriate\n- [ ] Evidence provided for all findings\n- [ ] Remediation suggestions actionable\n\n**Rejection Criteria**:\n- Work inappropriate for current state\n- Causes state machine violation\n- Regresses previous decisions\n- Missing state-specific requirements\n\n**Incident if rejected**:\n- `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|state_misalignment|<state>_violation`\n\n### Step 4: Quality and Completeness\n**Purpose**: Validate overall quality and completeness.\n\n**Quality Dimensions**:\n1. **Accuracy**: Information correct and verified\n2. **Completeness**: All required elements present\n3. **Clarity**: Information understandable\n4. **Consistency**: Internal and external consistency\n5. **Actionability**: Output usable for next steps\n\n**Validation Checklist**:\n- [ ] All information verified against evidence\n- [ ] No contradictions within artifacts\n- [ ] Consistent with project constraints\n- [ ] Clear next steps defined\n- [ ] Risks and assumptions documented\n\n**Rejection Criteria**:\n- Unverified assumptions\n- Internal contradictions\n- Unclear or ambiguous information\n- Missing risk assessment\n\n**Incident if rejected**:\n- `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|quality_insufficient|<dimension>_failed`\n\n### Step 5: Architectural Impact Assessment\n**Purpose**: Assess impact on overall architecture.\n\n**Assessment Areas**:\n1. **Scalability impact**: How does this affect system scalability?\n2. **Performance impact**: What are the performance implications?\n3. **Security impact**: What security considerations arise?\n4. **Maintainability impact**: How does this affect long-term maintenance?\n5. **Integration impact**: What are the integration implications?\n\n**Validation Output**:\n```\n## Architectural Impact Assessment\n\n### Positive Impacts\n1. <impact 1>\n2. <impact 2>\n\n### Concerns / Risks\n1. <concern 1> - <severity> - <mitigation>\n2. <concern 2> - <severity> - <mitigation>\n\n### Required Architectural Changes\n1. <change 1>\n2. <change 2>\n\n### Approval Conditions\n- [ ] Condition 1\n- [ ] Condition 2\n```\n\n**Rejection Criteria**:\n- Unacceptable architectural risks\n- Violates architectural principles\n- Creates technical debt beyond threshold\n- Incompatible with overall architecture\n\n**Incident if rejected**:\n- `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|arch_impact_unacceptable|<area>_risk`\n\n## Review Decision Types\n\n### Approval\n**Conditions**:\n- All DoD criteria met or exceeded\n- Aligns with project state\n- Quality standards met\n- Acceptable architectural impact\n- No blocking issues\n\n**Actions**:\n1. Update project README with approval\n2. Version artifacts appropriately\n3. Log approval in review log\n4. Trigger next steps in workflow\n\n### Conditional Approval\n**Conditions**:\n- Minor issues that don't block progress\n- Issues have clear resolution path\n- Specialist commits to addressing issues\n- Issues don't affect core functionality\n\n**Actions**:\n1. Document conditions for full approval\n2. Create follow-up tasks\n3. Approve with conditions noted\n4. Schedule follow-up review\n\n### Request Corrections\n**Conditions**:\n- Significant but fixable issues\n- Specialist can address within reasonable time\n- Issues affect quality but not fundamentals\n- Clear correction requirements\n\n**Actions**:\n1. Provide specific correction requirements\n2. Set deadline for corrections\n3. Return work to specialist\n4. Schedule re-review\n\n### Rejection\n**Conditions**:\n- Fundamental flaws\n- Missing critical elements\n- Unacceptable quality\n- Architectural violations\n- State machine violations\n\n**Actions**:\n1. Document rejection reasons\n2. Provide guidance for complete rework\n3. Escalate if pattern emerges\n4. Log incident for learning system\n\n## Review Documentation Requirements\n\n### Review Log Entry\n**Required fields**:\n```\n## Review Log - <Project> - <Artifact> - <Timestamp>\n\n### Basic Information\n- Reviewer: <architect>\n- Specialist: <role>\n- Artifact: <name>\n- Version: <version>\n\n### Review Results\n- Submission: <valid/invalid>\n- DoD Compliance: <percentage>%\n- State Alignment: <aligned/misaligned>\n- Quality Assessment: <score>\n- Architectural Impact: <acceptable/unacceptable>\n\n### Decision\n- Decision: <approval/conditional/rejection>\n- Decision Reason: <summary>\n- Conditions: <if conditional>\n- Corrections Required: <if rejected>\n\n### Issues Found\n1. <issue 1> - <severity> - <status>\n2. <issue 2> - <severity> - <status>\n\n### Next Steps\n1. <step 1>\n2. <step 2>\n```\n\n### Project README Updates\n**Required updates after review**:\n```\n## Review History\n- <date>: <artifact> - <version> - <decision> - <reviewer>\n\n## Current Status\n- Last Review: <date>\n- Review Outcome: <decision>\n- Open Issues: <count>\n- Next Review: <date if scheduled>\n```\n\n## Quality Metrics and Continuous Improvement\n\n### Review Performance Metrics\n1. **Review cycle time**: Time from submission to decision\n2. **First-time approval rate**: Percentage approved without corrections\n3. **Correction turnaround**: Time from rejection to resubmission\n4. **Issue severity distribution**: Breakdown of issues by severity\n5. **Role-specific patterns**: Approval rates by specialist role\n\n### Continuous Improvement Process\n1. **Monthly review analysis**: Analyze review patterns and metrics\n2. **Role feedback sessions**: Gather feedback from specialists\n3. **Protocol refinement**: Update protocol based on learnings\n4. **Training updates**: Update specialist training based on review findings\n\n### Success Criteria\n1. **Target first-time approval rate**: >80%\n2. **Target review cycle time**: <4 hours for standard reviews\n3. **Target correction turnaround**: <24 hours for minor corrections\n4. **Target issue resolution**: >95% of issues resolved per review cycle\n\n## Integration with Learning System\n\n### Pattern Detection\n**Review success patterns**:\n- Role-specific approval patterns\n- State-specific quality patterns\n- Project-type success factors\n\n**Review failure patterns**:\n- Common DoD violations\n- Frequent state misalignments\n- Recurring quality issues\n- Architectural risk patterns\n\n### Incident Learning\n**Incident analysis**:\n- Root cause analysis for rejections\n- Pattern identification across projects\n- Protocol gap identification\n- Training need identification\n\n**Protocol updates**:\n- Update based on incident patterns\n- Refine validation criteria\n- Add new checkpoints as needed\n- Clarify ambiguous requirements\n\n## Escalation Protocol\n\n### When to Escalate\n1. **Pattern of rejections**: Same specialist repeatedly rejected\n2. **Major architectural issues**: Findings requiring executive attention\n3. **Project timeline impact**: Reviews causing significant delays\n4. **Quality crisis**: Consistent quality failures across multiple specialists\n\n### Escalation Path\n1. **Architect → Project Lead**: For pattern issues or timeline impacts\n2. **Project Lead → Practice Lead**: For major architectural or quality issues\n3. **Practice Lead → Executive**: For strategic or systemic issues\n\n### Escalation Documentation\n**Required documentation for escalation**:\n- Review history and patterns\n- Impact assessment\n- Recommended actions\n- Requested support level"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":66642,"output":2381,"cacheRead":18624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87647,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773077013512}}
