{"type":"message","id":"b9f363c8","parentId":"71c1b096","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:25:44.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora voy a proceder con las mejoras de **CLASE B** (Comportamiento en tiempo de ejecución). Primero, voy a actualizar el archivo principal `SKILL.md` del salesforce-architect:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_BaVcYHUaLOuEdHBmQspDNhfa","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md","offset":1,"limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":62329,"output":146,"cacheRead":20672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83147,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773077125201}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a75cabb","parentId":"b9f363c8","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:25:44.885Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_BaVcYHUaLOuEdHBmQspDNhfa","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: salesforce-architect\ndescription: Production-ready skill for analyzing complex business processes, extracting requirements, producing Salesforce architecture decisions, generating FIT/GAP analysis, functional design documentation, data models, and validating architecture using official Salesforce documentation only.\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: salesforce-architect\n---\n\n# Salesforce Architect Skill\n\n## Overview\nA production‑ready skill for analyzing complex business processes, extracting requirements, producing Salesforce architecture decisions, generating FIT/GAP analysis, functional design documentation, data models, and validating architecture using official Salesforce documentation only.\n\n## CRITICAL RULE – USE WORKSPACE REFERENCES\nThe skill must read and consult the following reference PDFs (located in `<workspace>/references/`) before generating any output artifacts:\n\n1. `_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf` – defines the structure of the Functional Design document.\n2. `IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf` – defines the structure and fields of the FIT/GAP matrix.\n3. `IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf` – example of a completed functional design.\n4. `Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf` – example data model structure.\n\nIf any of these documents are missing, the skill must:\n1. Stop execution\n2. Emit an incident\n3. Ask the user to confirm the references location\n\n## Salesforce Documentation Evidence Policy\nAllowed domains:\n- `help.salesforce.com`\n- `developer.salesforce.com`\n- `architect.salesforce.com`\n- `trailhead.salesforce.com`\n\nEvery architecture decision must include a reference link to official Salesforce documentation. If evidence cannot be found:\n- Mark the decision `UNVERIFIED`\n- Request clarification from the user\n- Do not finalize the design\n\n## Supported Clouds\n- Sales Cloud\n- Service Cloud\n- Field Service\n- Financial Services Cloud\n- Data Cloud\n- Agentforce\n- OmniStudio\n- Digital Engagement\n- Experience Cloud\n\nThe skill must evaluate licensing constraints before recommending features. For example: if Field Service licenses are unavailable, propose a custom visit management solution instead of FSL.\n\n\n[206 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773077144860}}
{"type":"message","id":"f83711e9","parentId":"4a75cabb","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:26:14.564Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a actualizar el SKILL.md para incluir las nuevas referencias y comportamientos:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_CeKkRjKVliWPzaXEZAuMei22","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md","oldText":"## CRITICAL RULE – USE WORKSPACE REFERENCES\nThe skill must read and consult the following reference PDFs (located in `<workspace>/references/`) before generating any output artifacts:\n\n1. `_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf` – defines the structure of the Functional Design document.\n2. `IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf` – defines the structure and fields of the FIT/GAP matrix.\n3. `IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf` – example of a completed functional design.\n4. `Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf` – example data model structure.\n\nIf any of these documents are missing, the skill must:\n1. Stop execution\n2. Emit an incident\n3. Ask the user to confirm the references location","newText":"## CRITICAL RULE – USE WORKSPACE REFERENCES\nThe skill must read and consult the following reference PDFs (located in `<workspace>/references/`) before generating any output artifacts:\n\n1. `_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf` – defines the structure of the Functional Design document.\n2. `IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf` – defines the structure and fields of the FIT/GAP matrix.\n3. `IDEINCA - Documento Funcional V1NoGAPs.pdf` – example of a completed functional design.\n4. `Diseño Funcional(Modelo de datos) - IDEINCA.xlsx.pdf` – example data model structure.\n\nIf any of these documents are missing, the skill must:\n1. Stop execution\n2. Emit an incident\n3. Ask the user to confirm the references location\n\n## HARDENED GOVERNANCE REFERENCES (NEW)\nThe skill must also consult the following governance references (located in `skills/salesforce-architect/references/`):\n\n1. `SALESFORCE_ROLE_MODEL.md` – stable role definitions and boundaries\n2. `ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md` – rules for assigning specialist roles\n3. `DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md` – completion criteria per role\n4. `SALESFORCE_PROJECT_STATE_MACHINE.md` – project lifecycle states\n5. `ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md` – standardized review process\n6. `CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md` – architect ↔ auditor governance\n\nThese are **reference assets, not runtime-generated**. The architect must:\n- Select from pre-defined roles, not invent new ones\n- Apply DoD consistently across all specialist work\n- Enforce state machine transitions\n- Follow review protocol for all validations\n- Use appropriate handoff modes with code auditor"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":504,"output":702,"cacheRead":83136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84342,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773077144880}}
