rsions\n+161 - Discovery: v<version>\n+162 - Requirements: v<version>\n+163 - Fit/Gap: v<version>\n+164 - Design: v<version>\n+165 - Data Model: v<version>\n+166 - Architecture Review: v<version>\n+167 - Code Audit: v<version> (if exists)\n+168 - Remediation: v<version> (if exists)\n+169 \n+170 ## Code Audits\n+171 - Case ID: <case_id>\n+172 - Mode: <A/B/C>\n+173 - Date: <timestamp>\n+174 - Findings: <summary>\n+175 - Status: <open/in remediation/closed>\n+176 \n+177 ## Next Actions\n+178 - [ ] Action 1\n+179 - [ ] Action 2\n+180 ```\n+181 \n+182 ### Artifact Containment Rule\n+183 **NO Salesforce artifact may be created outside:**\n+184 `<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/...`\n+185 \n+186 **Exceptions**: Only global references in `<workspace>/references/`\n+187 \n+188 **Violation response**: Emit incident `salesforce|PROJECT_ROUTING|artifact_outside_project|blocked`\n+189 ```\n+190 \n 123 ## Pipeline Stages\n 124 \n 125 ### Stage 0 – Intake Gate\n 126 **Mandatory inputs** (block pipeline if missing):\n     ...","firstChangedLine":121},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773077213924}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b67cdad","parentId":"25faefd7","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:27:00.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora voy a agregar una sección sobre el uso de sub-agentes especializados:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_8xDW6T8LdLnHjPk5bjTXBZx2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md","offset":200,"limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":85,"output":116,"cacheRead":85504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85705,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773077213942}}
{"type":"message","id":"42bac708","parentId":"3b67cdad","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:27:00.768Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_8xDW6T8LdLnHjPk5bjTXBZx2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Process description\n- Implementation scope\n\nIf any mandatory input is missing, generate discovery questions and stop.\n\n### Stage 1 – Discovery (EC0249)\nExtract actors, processes, events, systems, unknowns from transcripts/notes/SOW.\n**Outputs:**\n- `Discovery_Report.md`\n- `Discovery_Process_Analysis.md`\n- `Discovery_QA.xlsx`\n\n### Stage 2 – Requirements Consolidation\nTransform discovery into structured requirements with:\n- ID\n- Process\n- Actor\n- Description\n- Trigger\n- Acceptance criteria\n\nIntegrations must not be assumed.\n\n### Stage 3 – FIT / GAP Analysis\nFIT = requested + in project scope, GAP = requested + not in project scope.\nMust request SOW/proposal/scope before classification.\n**Output:** `Fit_Gap_Matrix.xlsx` with columns:\n- ReqID\n- Process\n- Requirement\n- Fit/GAP\n- Justification\n- Time impact\n- Cost impact\n- Implementation type\n- License dependency\n- Risk\n- Evidence link\n- Status\n\n### Stage 4 – Functional Design\nStructure MUST follow `<workspace>/references/_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf`.\nGenerate `Functional_Design.docx` with sections:\n- Introduction\n- Scope\n- Business process algorithms\n- System interactions\n- Object model\n- Automations\n- Security\n\n[92 more lines in file. Use offset=250 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773077220758}}
{"type":"message","id":"267f7121","parentId":"42bac708","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:27:32.275Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a agregar una sección sobre el uso de sub-agentes después de las etapas de la pipeline:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_LGt44UvIrKP7xiQHA4MbdP3h","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md","oldText":"## Multi‑Agent Mode\nThe skill supports optional architecture sub‑agents:\n- SalesCloudArchitect\n- ServiceCloudArchitect\n- FieldServiceArchitect\n- DataCloudArchitect\n- ExperienceArchitect\n- OmniStudioArchitect\n- AgentforceArchitect\n- SecurityArchitect\n\n`run_pipeline.py` must allow:\n- `--mode single`\n- `--mode multi`\n\nAll long‑running agents must register with `agent‑watchdog`.","newText":"## HARDENED SUB‑AGENT SPECIALIST USAGE\n\n### Default Execution Model\n**Sub‑agents as default** for specialist work. The architect must:\n\n1. **Select from role model**: Choose pre‑defined role from `SALESFORCE_ROLE_MODEL.md`\n2. **Never reinvent roles**: Use stable role definitions, don't create new ones\n3. **Pass task‑specific context**: Provide only necessary context to specialist\n4. **Review critically**: Apply `ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md` to all outputs\n\n### Runtime Decision Logic\nFor each task, the architect must decide:\n\n1. **Single‑domain vs multi‑domain**: One specialist or multiple?\n2. **Specialist needed?**: Can architect handle or needs specialist?\n3. **Code auditor needed?**: When technical validation required\n4. **Output strength**: Is output strong enough or needs challenge?\n\n### Architect Roles Enforced\nThe architect must act explicitly as:\n- **Router**: Directs work to appropriate specialists\n- **Reviewer**: Validates against DoD and quality standards\n- **Challenger**: Questions assumptions, requests evidence\n- **Integrator**: Combines specialist outputs into coherent whole\n- **Project Owner**: Maintains project integrity and progress\n\n### Specialist Role Assignment\nAvailable specialist roles (from role model):\n1. Salesforce Administrator\n2. Salesforce Functional Consultant — Standard Clouds\n3. Salesforce Integration Developer\n4. Salesforce Custom UI Developer\n5. Salesforce Industries / OmniStudio Functional Consultant\n6. Salesforce OmniStudio Developer\n7. Salesforce Data Cloud Functional Consultant\n8. Salesforce Data Cloud Developer\n9. Salesforce Security / Platform Governance Reviewer\n\n**Assignment rules**: Follow `ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md`\n\n### Output Rejection Protocol\nWhen specialist output is weak:\n1. **Specific feedback**: What exactly fails DoD or quality standards\n2. **Clear correction requirements**: What needs to be fixed\n3. **Priority classification**: Blocking vs. non‑blocking issues\n4. **Timeline for corrections**: Reasonable deadline\n5. **Re‑validation process**: How corrections will be reviewed\n\n**Incident for repeated rejections**: `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|subagent_output_incomplete|rejected`\n\n### Watchdog Registration\nAll long‑running sub‑agents must register with `agent‑watchdog`:\n- Expected runtime >5 minutes → mandatory registration\n- Monitor for stalls and timeouts\n- Automatic recovery escalation"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":394,"output":729,"cacheRead":85632,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86755,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773077220766}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed3764a2","parentId":"267f7121","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:27:32.328Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_LGt44UvIrKP7xiQHA4MbdP3h","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 278 - `licensing|CONFLICT|feature_requires_license|not_available|alternate_needed`\n 279 \n 280 Then trigger learning‑loop fallback.\n 281 \n-282 ## Multi‑Agent Mode\n-283 The skill supports optional architecture sub‑agents:\n-284 - SalesCloudArchitect\n-285 - ServiceCloudArchitect\n-286 - FieldServiceArchitect\n-287 - DataCloudArchitect\n-288 - ExperienceArchitect\n-289 - OmniStudioArchitect\n-290 - AgentforceArchitect\n-291 - SecurityArchitect\n+282 ## HARDENED SUB‑AGENT SPECIALIST USAGE\n 292 \n-293 `run_pipeline.py` must allow:\n-294 - `--mode single`\n-295 - `--mode multi`\n+284 ### Default Execution Model\n+285 **Sub‑agents as default** for specialist work. The architect must:\n 296 \n-297 All long‑running agents must register with `agent‑watchdog`.\n+287 1. **Select from role model**: Choose pre‑defined role from `SALESFORCE_ROLE_MODEL.md`\n+288 2. **Never reinvent roles**: Use stable role definitions, don't create new ones\n+289 3. **Pass task‑specific context**: Provide only necessary context to specialist\n+290 4. **Review critically**: Apply `ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md` to all outputs\n 298 \n+292 ### Runtime Decision Logic\n+293 For each task, the architect must decide:\n+294 \n+295 1. **Single‑domain vs multi‑domain**: One specialist or multiple?\n+296 2. **Specialist needed?**: Can architect handle or needs specialist?\n+297 3. **Code auditor needed?**: When technical validation required\n+298 4. **Output strength**: Is output strong enough or needs challenge?\n+299 \n+300 ### Architect Roles Enforced\n+301 The architect must act explicitly as:\n+302 - **Router**: Directs work to appropriate specialists\n+303 - **Reviewer**: Validates against DoD and quality standards\n+304 - **Challenger**: Questions assumptions, requests evidence\n+305 - **Integrator**: Combines specialist outputs into coherent whole\n+306 - **Project Owner**: Maintains project integrity and progress\n+307 \n+308 ### Specialist Role Assignment\n+309 Available specialist roles (from role model):\n+310 1. Salesforce Administrator\n+311 2. Salesforce Functional Consultant — Standard Clouds\n+312 3. Salesforce Integration Developer\n+313 4. Salesforce Custom UI Developer\n+314 5. Salesforce Industries / OmniStudio Functional Consultant\n+315 6. Salesforce OmniStudio Developer\n+316 7. Salesforce Data Cloud Functional Consultant\n+317 8. Salesforce Data Cloud Developer\n+318 9. Salesforce Security / Platform Governance Reviewer\n+319 \n+320 **Assignment rules**: Follow `ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md`\n+321 \n+322 ### Output Rejection Protocol\n+323 When specialist output is weak:\n+324 1. **Specific feedback**: What exactly fails DoD or quality standards\n+325 2. **Clear correction requirements**: What needs to be fixed\n+326 3. **Priority classification**: Blocking vs. non‑blocking issues\n+327 4. **Timeline for corrections**: Reasonable deadline\n+328 5. **Re‑validation process**: How corrections will be reviewed\n+329 \n+330 **Incident for repeated rejections**: `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|subagent_output_incomplete|rejected`\n+331 \n+332 ### Watchdog Registration\n+333 All long‑running sub‑agents must register with `agent‑watchdog`:\n+334 - Expected runtime >5 minutes → mandatory registration\n+335 - Monitor for stalls and timeouts\n+336 - Automatic recovery escalation\n+337 \n 299 ## Required Demo Execution\n 300 To validate the skill, run a demo project:\n 301 ```\n 302 project_key = demo_salesforce_architect\n     ...","firstChangedLine":282},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773077252308}}
{"type":"message","id":"4590798b","parentId":"ed3764a2","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:27:41.115Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora voy a agregar una sección sobre la integración con el auditor de código:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ZsbubWJHbkMWDNLCfF6tY2gs","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md","offset":300,"limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":82,"output":116,"cacheRead":86720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86918,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773077252325}}
{"type":"message","id":"042d80c6","parentId":"4590798b","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:27:41.185Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ZsbubWJHbkMWDNLCfF6tY2gs","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### Architect Roles Enforced\nThe architect must act explicitly as:\n- **Router**: Directs work to appropriate specialists\n- **Reviewer**: Validates against DoD and quality standards\n- **Challenger**: Questions assumptions, requests evidence\n- **Integrator**: Combines specialist outputs into coherent whole\n- **Project Owner**: Maintains project integrity and progress\n\n### Specialist Role Assignment\nAvailable specialist roles (from role model):\n1. Salesforce Administrator\n2. Salesforce Functional Consultant — Standard Clouds\n3. Salesforce Integration Developer\n4. Salesforce Custom UI Developer\n5. Salesforce Industries / OmniStudio Functional Consultant\n6. Salesforce OmniStudio Developer\n7. Salesforce Data Cloud Functional Consultant\n8. Salesforce Data Cloud Developer\n9. Salesforce Security / Platform Governance Reviewer\n\n**Assignment rules**: Follow `ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md`\n\n### Output Rejection Protocol\nWhen specialist output is weak:\n1. **Specific feedback**: What exactly fails DoD or quality standards\n2. **Clear correction requirements**: What needs to be fixed\n3. **Priority classification**: Blocking vs. non‑blocking issues\n4. **Timeline for corrections**: Reasonable deadline\n5. **Re‑validation process**: How corrections will be reviewed\n\n**Incident for repeated rejections**: `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|subagent_output_incomplete|rejected`\n\n### Watchdog Registration\nAll long‑running sub‑agents must register with `agent‑watchdog`:\n- Expected runtime >5 minutes → mandatory registration\n- Monitor for stalls and timeouts\n- Automatic recovery escalation\n\n## Required Demo Execution\nTo validate the skill, run a demo project:\n```\nproject_key = demo_salesforce_architect\n```\n\nExpected behavior:\n1. Generate discovery outputs\n2. Block FIT/GAP if scope missing\n3. Emit learning incident\n4. Trigger learning loop fallback\n5. Generate Word and Excel artifacts\n\n[31 more lines in file. Use offset=350 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773077261147}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b0dea69","parentId":"042d80c6","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:28:32.060Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a agregar una sección sobre la integración con el auditor de código antes de la ejecución de demo:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_UpMOajkpQI6gBQ4juvBW3YC3","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/SKILL.md","oldText":"### Watchdog Registration\nAll long‑running sub‑agents must register with `agent‑watchdog`:\n- Expected runtime >5 minutes → mandatory registration\n- Monitor for stalls and timeouts\n- Automatic recovery escalation\n\n## Required Demo Execution","newText":"### Watchdog Registration\nAll long‑running sub‑agents must register with `agent‑watchdog`:\n- Expected runtime >5 minutes → mandatory registration\n- Monitor for stalls and timeouts\n- Automatic recovery escalation\n\n## HARDENED CODE AUDITOR INTEGRATION\n\n### Subordinate Validator Role\n`salesforce‑code‑auditor` operates as a **subordinate validator** under architect governance.\n\n### Project‑Scoped Audit Structure\nAll audits must be within:\n`<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/...`\n\n### Architect‑Controlled Invocation\nThe architect invokes auditor when:\n\n1. **Current‑state understanding needed**: Before design decisions\n2. **Design validation**: Check if implementation supports design\n3. **Technical constraints**: When code affects architecture\n4. **Partner‑delivered code**: Review external code\n5. **Remediation planning**: Need code evidence for fixes\n\n### Handoff Modes (from `CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md`)\n1. **Mode A — Architecture → Code Audit**: Need technical truth before design\n2. **Mode B — Code Audit → Architecture**: Findings require architectural changes\n3. **Mode C — Design Validation**: Validate design feasibility\n\n### Required Auditor Outputs\nThe auditor must return architect‑consumable outputs:\n- Technical risks with severity levels\n- Security/governor findings\n- Object/field/automation usage analysis\n- Implementation constraints\n- Design alignment gaps\n- Remediation suggestions\n- Confidence levels for heuristic findings\n\n### Audit Integration with State Machine\n- **DISCOVERY phase**: Mode A audits to understand current state\n- **DESIGN phase**: Mode C audits to validate design feasibility\n- **ARCH_REVIEW phase**: Mode B audits for architectural validation\n- **CODE_AUDIT phase**: Formal audit as state progression\n- **REMEDIATION phase**: Follow‑up audits for fix validation\n\n### Blocking Conditions\nFindings block architectural finalization when:\n- CRITICAL security vulnerabilities without mitigation\n- Architectural flaws requiring design changes\n- Performance issues making solution unusable\n- Integration failures preventing core functionality\n\n**Incident for blocking findings**: `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|design_alignment_gap|review_required`\n\n## PHASE‑AWARE RUNTIME BEHAVIOR\n\n### State Machine Enforcement\nAt runtime, the architect must:\n\n1. **Detect current phase**: Check project README and artifacts\n2. **Validate request for phase**: Is request valid for current state?\n3. **Determine artifact action**: Create new, update existing, or block?\n4. **Avoid regeneration**: Don't recreate artifacts unnecessarily\n5. **Version conservatively**: Increment versions only when substantive changes\n\n### State‑Specific Rules\n- **No FIT_GAP without scope/SOW**: Must have scope document\n- **No DESIGN without consolidated discovery**: Must understand what's being built\n- **No FINALIZED with critical audit findings**: All critical issues resolved\n- **No CODE_AUDIT without clear objectives**: Must know what to look for\n\n### Artifact Version Discipline\n**Naming examples**:\n- `Functional_Design_v1.docx`\n- `Functional_Design_v2.docx`\n- `Fit_Gap_Matrix_v1.xlsx`\n- `Code_Audit_Report_v1.md`\n- `Architecture_Overview_v2.md`\n\n**Version increment rules**:\n- Major changes → increment version\n- Minor corrections → same version with correction log\n- Format changes only → no version increment\n- Re‑creation with same content → no version increment\n\n## INCIDENT AND GOVERNANCE HARDENING\n\n### Governance Failure Incidents\n- `salesforce|PROJECT_ROUTING|missing_project_key|blocked`\n- `salesforce|ROLE_ASSIGNMENT|wrong_specialist_selected|rework_needed`\n- `salesforce|ARCH_REVIEW|subagent_output_incomplete|rejected`\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|design_alignment_gap|review_required`\n- `salesforce|STATE_MACHINE|missing_prerequisite|blocked`\n- `salesforce|STATE_MACHINE|invalid_transition|rejected`\n\n### Incident Reporting Path\nAll incidents use existing unified path to `workspace/.learnings/ERRORS.md`\n\n### Learning Integration\nIncidents trigger error‑learning‑loop for:\n- Pattern detection across projects\n- Guardrail promotion to AGENTS.md/TOOLS.md\n- Protocol refinement based on failures\n- Training need identification\n\n## Required Demo Execution"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":432,"output":1125,"cacheRead":86912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88469,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773077261174}}
