{"type":"message","id":"5071dbbe","parentId":"841e28ec","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:28:10.231Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_yZdLyqK3lApsuNOBI82sVjXt","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: salesforce-code-auditor\ndescription: A production‑ready skill for progressive technical analysis of Salesforce codebases (Apex, LWC, Visualforce, Triggers, Flows, Metadata) with token‑efficient auditing.\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: salesforce-code-auditor\n---\n\n# Salesforce Code Auditor Skill\n\n## Overview\nA production‑ready skill for **progressive technical analysis of Salesforce codebases** (Apex, LWC, Visualforce, Triggers, Flows, Metadata) with **token‑efficient auditing**. The agent requests only the minimal necessary code to reconstruct the real execution logic of a process.\n\nDesigned to **work together with the `salesforce‑architect` skill**.\n\n## Workspace Code Intake Model\nThe user must place code inside a case folder created by the skill.\n\nDirectory created automatically:\n`<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/inputs/`\n\nSupported formats:\n- Apex `.cls`\n- Apex Triggers `.trigger`\n- LWC `.js`, `.html`, `.xml`\n- Visualforce `.page`\n- Metadata `.xml`\n- Flow metadata\n- DTO / integration classes\n\nThe skill **indexes files first instead of reading them immediately**.\n\n## Required Runtime Structure\n```\n<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/\n  CASE.md\n  inputs/\n  work/\n  snippets/\n  temp_analysis/\n  outputs/\n  INDEX.md\n  MANIFEST.json\n  DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json\n  ENTRYPOINTS.json\n  EXECUTION_TRACE.md\n  FINDINGS.md\n  TEST_MATRIX.md\n  AUDIT_REPORT.md\n```\n\n\n[166 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773080890219}}
{"type":"message","id":"ced155ae","parentId":"5071dbbe","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:28:50.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a agregar una sección sobre la integración endurecida con el arquitecto:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_BT6VktQgHdbpPU2mgiZBjkT8","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-code-auditor/SKILL.md","oldText":"Designed to **work together with the `salesforce‑architect` skill**.","newText":"Designed to **work together with the `salesforce‑architect` skill** as a **subordinate validator** under architect governance.\n\n## HARDENED ARCHITECT INTEGRATION\n\n### Governance Relationship\nThe code‑auditor operates as a **subordinate validator** to the salesforce‑architect. All audits must be:\n- Project‑scoped under architect control\n- Invoked through defined handoff modes\n- Returning architect‑consumable outputs\n- Subject to architect review and validation\n\n### Handoff Modes (Governance Contract)\nThe architect invokes the auditor using defined handoff modes from `CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md`:\n\n1. **Mode A — Architecture → Code Audit**\n   - **When**: Architect needs current‑state technical truth before design decisions\n   - **Request**: Clear audit objectives, scope, context\n   - **Response**: Technical assessment, constraints, recommendations\n\n2. **Mode B — Code Audit → Architecture**\n   - **When**: Audit findings must change architecture decisions\n   - **Request**: Focus on specific concerns, architectural context\n   - **Response**: Critical findings, architectural impact, remediation options\n\n3. **Mode C — Design Validation Mode**\n   - **When**: Architect needs to validate if implementation supports proposed design\n   - **Request**: Design context, validation objectives, specific points\n   - **Response**: Feasibility assessment, gap analysis, implementation complexity\n\n### Required Output Format for Architect Consumption\nAll audit reports must be structured for direct architect consumption:\n\n```\n## Code Audit Report - Mode <A/B/C>\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case ID**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: <A/B/C>\n\n### Executive Summary\n- Overall code health assessment\n- Key findings summary\n- Architectural implications\n\n### Technical Assessment\n- Code structure and organization\n- Design patterns used\n- Technical debt identified\n- Performance characteristics\n\n### Constraints & Limitations\n- Technical constraints for new development\n- Integration limitations\n- Scalability constraints\n- Security limitations\n\n### Risk Assessment\n- **CRITICAL (Sev1)**: Security vulnerabilities, data loss risks, performance failures\n- **HIGH (Sev2)**: Significant security/performance issues, major code quality problems\n- **MEDIUM (Sev3)**: Code quality issues, performance optimizations, minor security concerns\n- **LOW (Sev4)**: Code style issues, documentation improvements, test coverage\n\n### Recommendations for Architecture\n1. <recommendation 1>\n2. <recommendation 2>\n3. <recommendation 3>\n\n### Evidence\n- Code snippets supporting findings\n- Performance metrics\n- Security vulnerability details\n- Design pattern analysis\n```\n\n### Blocking Conditions for Architectural Finalization\nFindings that **block architectural finalization**:\n- CRITICAL security vulnerabilities without approved mitigation\n- Architectural flaws requiring design changes\n- Performance issues making solution unusable\n- Integration failures preventing core functionality\n\n**Incident emission for blocking findings**: `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|design_alignment_gap|review_required`"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":55870,"output":775,"cacheRead":33856,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90501,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773080890228}}
{"type":"message","id":"2f77c870","parentId":"ced155ae","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:28:50.929Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_BT6VktQgHdbpPU2mgiZBjkT8","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-code-auditor/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n   9 \n  10 ## Overview\n  11 A production‑ready skill for **progressive technical analysis of Salesforce codebases** (Apex, LWC, Visualforce, Triggers, Flows, Metadata) with **token‑efficient auditing**. The agent requests only the minimal necessary code to reconstruct the real execution logic of a process.\n  12 \n- 13 Designed to **work together with the `salesforce‑architect` skill**.\n+ 13 Designed to **work together with the `salesforce‑architect` skill** as a **subordinate validator** under architect governance.\n  14 \n+ 15 ## HARDENED ARCHITECT INTEGRATION\n+ 16 \n+ 17 ### Governance Relationship\n+ 18 The code‑auditor operates as a **subordinate validator** to the salesforce‑architect. All audits must be:\n+ 19 - Project‑scoped under architect control\n+ 20 - Invoked through defined handoff modes\n+ 21 - Returning architect‑consumable outputs\n+ 22 - Subject to architect review and validation\n+ 23 \n+ 24 ### Handoff Modes (Governance Contract)\n+ 25 The architect invokes the auditor using defined handoff modes from `CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md`:\n+ 26 \n+ 27 1. **Mode A — Architecture → Code Audit**\n+ 28    - **When**: Architect needs current‑state technical truth before design decisions\n+ 29    - **Request**: Clear audit objectives, scope, context\n+ 30    - **Response**: Technical assessment, constraints, recommendations\n+ 31 \n+ 32 2. **Mode B — Code Audit → Architecture**\n+ 33    - **When**: Audit findings must change architecture decisions\n+ 34    - **Request**: Focus on specific concerns, architectural context\n+ 35    - **Response**: Critical findings, architectural impact, remediation options\n+ 36 \n+ 37 3. **Mode C — Design Validation Mode**\n+ 38    - **When**: Architect needs to validate if implementation supports proposed design\n+ 39    - **Request**: Design context, validation objectives, specific points\n+ 40    - **Response**: Feasibility assessment, gap analysis, implementation complexity\n+ 41 \n+ 42 ### Required Output Format for Architect Consumption\n+ 43 All audit reports must be structured for direct architect consumption:\n+ 44 \n+ 45 ```\n+ 46 ## Code Audit Report - Mode <A/B/C>\n+ 47 \n+ 48 **Project**: <project_key>\n+ 49 **Audit Case ID**: <case_id>\n+ 50 **Mode**: <A/B/C>\n+ 51 \n+ 52 ### Executive Summary\n+ 53 - Overall code health assessment\n+ 54 - Key findings summary\n+ 55 - Architectural implications\n+ 56 \n+ 57 ### Technical Assessment\n+ 58 - Code structure and organization\n+ 59 - Design patterns used\n+ 60 - Technical debt identified\n+ 61 - Performance characteristics\n+ 62 \n+ 63 ### Constraints & Limitations\n+ 64 - Technical constraints for new development\n+ 65 - Integration limitations\n+ 66 - Scalability constraints\n+ 67 - Security limitations\n+ 68 \n+ 69 ### Risk Assessment\n+ 70 - **CRITICAL (Sev1)**: Security vulnerabilities, data loss risks, performance failures\n+ 71 - **HIGH (Sev2)**: Significant security/performance issues, major code quality problems\n+ 72 - **MEDIUM (Sev3)**: Code quality issues, performance optimizations, minor security concerns\n+ 73 - **LOW (Sev4)**: Code style issues, documentation improvements, test coverage\n+ 74 \n+ 75 ### Recommendations for Architecture\n+ 76 1. <recommendation 1>\n+ 77 2. <recommendation 2>\n+ 78 3. <recommendation 3>\n+ 79 \n+ 80 ### Evidence\n+ 81 - Code snippets supporting findings\n+ 82 - Performance metrics\n+ 83 - Security vulnerability details\n+ 84 - Design pattern analysis\n+ 85 ```\n+ 86 \n+ 87 ### Blocking Conditions for Architectural Finalization\n+ 88 Findings that **block architectural finalization**:\n+ 89 - CRITICAL security vulnerabilities without approved mitigation\n+ 90 - Architectural flaws requiring design changes\n+ 91 - Performance issues making solution unusable\n+ 92 - Integration failures preventing core functionality\n+ 93 \n+ 94 **Incident emission for blocking findings**: `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|design_alignment_gap|review_required`\n+ 95 \n  15 ## Workspace Code Intake Model\n  16 The user must place code inside a case folder created by the skill.\n  17 \n  18 Directory created automatically:\n     ...","firstChangedLine":13},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773080930917}}
