{"type":"message","id":"c5dfae4b","parentId":"47e0f3ac","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:50:44.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfecto, el usuario está totalmente de acuerdo con mi análisis y me da instrucciones claras sobre el orden de prioridad. Ya he comenzado a implementar las mejoras en el orden correcto:\n\n1. ✅ **Parser estructurado para referencias** - Ya creé `role_model.yaml` y `state_machine.yaml`\n2. 🚧 **Motor real de state machine** - Ya creé `state_machine_engine.py` con validación robusta\n3. 🚧 **Validación determinística de DoD** - Ya creé `dod_validator.py` con reglas determinísticas\n4. 📝 **README/project control file robusto** - Necesito mejorar el engine para manejar mejor el README\n\nEl usuario quiere que primero me enfoque en el motor de state machine antes que en el DoD, lo cual tiene sentido. Voy a completar el motor de state machine y luego probarlo.\n\nTambién necesito crear el archivo YAML para las definiciones de DoD que el validador espera. Voy a crear `dod_definitions.yaml` primero, luego completar las pruebas del motor de state machine, y finalmente mejorar la gestión del README.\n\nVoy a proceder en este orden:\n1. Crear `dod_definitions.yaml`\n2. Completar y probar el motor de state machine\n3. Mejorar la gestión del README en el engine\n4. Ejecutar validaciones actualizadas","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Voy a proceder en el orden correcto. Primero, voy a crear las definiciones de DoD en YAML:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_oaksPu5iUI9TIOZwSSs8aZeR","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/dod_definitions.yaml","content":"# Definition of Done Definitions - Structured YAML Reference\n# Purpose: Deterministic validation rules for specialist outputs\n# Status: Reference asset - DO NOT regenerate on every run\n# Last Updated: 2026-03-09\n\nversion: \"1.0\"\nformat: \"yaml\"\ndescription: \"Deterministic Definition of Done validation rules\"\n\nvalidation_rules:\n  required_fields:\n    all_roles:\n      - purpose_stated\n      - assumptions_documented\n      - evidence_provided\n      - decisions_documented\n      - next_actions_defined\n    \n    salesforce_administrator:\n      - security_model_documented\n      - user_management_plan\n      - automation_design\n      - data_governance_plan\n      - reporting_requirements\n    \n    functional_consultant_standard:\n      - process_interpretation\n      - scope_dependencies\n      - official_evidence\n      - open_decisions\n      - user_stories_defined\n    \n    integration_developer:\n      - integration_pattern\n      - authentication_assumptions\n      - retry_error_strategy\n      - limits_failure_modes\n      - impacted_objects_events\n    \n    custom_ui_developer:\n      - ui_interaction_model\n      - component_structure\n      - event_flow\n      - navigation_implications\n      - accessibility_considerations\n    \n    code_auditor:\n      - findings_listed\n      - code_evidence_snippets\n      - severity_levels\n      - architectural_impact\n      - remediation_suggestions\n      - confidence_level\n    \n    architect:\n      - final_decision\n      - rationale\n      - alternatives_considered\n      - unresolved_risks\n      - next_steps\n  \n  required_sections:\n    all_roles:\n      - executive_summary\n      - detailed_analysis\n      - assumptions\n      - evidence\n      - recommendations\n    \n    design_documents:\n      - introduction\n      - scope\n      - business_process_algorithms\n      - system_interactions\n      - object_model\n      - automations\n      - security\n    \n    audit_reports:\n      - executive_summary\n      - technical_assessment\n      - findings\n      - risk_assessment\n      - recommendations\n      - evidence\n    \n    requirements_documents:\n      - introduction\n      - business_context\n      - functional_requirements\n      - non_functional_requirements\n      - acceptance_criteria\n      - assumptions_constraints\n  \n  evidence_requirements:\n    minimum_evidence_count: 3\n    evidence_types:\n      - official_documentation\n      - code_snippets\n      - diagrams\n      - test_results\n      - performance_metrics\n      - security_assessments\n    \n    evidence_quality:\n      - source_cited\n      - relevance_explained\n      - timestamp_provided\n      - authority_established\n  \n  handoff_completeness:\n    required_elements:\n      - clear_next_owner\n      - outstanding_issues_listed\n      - dependencies_identified\n      - acceptance_criteria_met\n      - quality_gates_passed\n    \n    quality_checks:\n      - no_ambiguous_terms\n      - all_acronyms_defined\n      - consistent_terminology\n      - actionable_recommendations\n\nvalidation_thresholds:\n  blocking_threshold: 0.8    # Must have 80% of required fields/sections\n  warning_threshold: 0.9     # Should have 90% of required fields/sections\n  minimum_evidence_score: 0.7\n  minimum_handoff_score: 0.8\n\nrole_mappings:\n  # Map common role names to normalized keys\n  Salesforce Administrator: salesforce_administrator\n  Administrator: salesforce_administrator\n  Admin: salesforce_administrator\n  \n  Salesforce Functional Consultant: functional_consultant_standard\n  Functional Consultant: functional_consultant_standard\n  Business Analyst: functional_consultant_standard\n  \n  Salesforce Integration Developer: integration_developer\n  Integration Developer: integration_developer\n  Integration Specialist: integration_developer\n  \n  Salesforce Custom UI Developer: custom_ui_developer\n  UI Developer: custom_ui_developer\n  LWC Developer: custom_ui_developer\n  \n  Salesforce Code Auditor: code_auditor\n  Code Auditor: code_auditor\n  Technical Reviewer: code_auditor\n  \n  Salesforce Architect: architect\n  Architect: architect\n  Solution Architect: architect\n\n# Field pattern mappings for validation\nfield_patterns:\n  purpose_stated:\n    - \"purpose\"\n    - \"objective\"\n    - \"goal\"\n    - \"aim\"\n  \n  assumptions_documented:\n    - \"assumption\"\n    - \"presumption\"\n    - \"given that\"\n    - \"assuming\"\n  \n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1773082180888,"errorMessage":"Request was aborted"}}
