{"type":"message","id":"897a1b19","parentId":"9542a279","timestamp":"2026-03-09T18:51:10.306Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_axuoBZQH0RTn9o8xT3aCj0wR","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects Registry\n\n## OpenClaw Memory System\n- **Status**: In progress\n- **Tech Stack**: PostgreSQL, pgvector, Python, Gemini API\n- **Description**: Full memory stack upgrade with vector database, smart loading, and auto-curation\n- **Location**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/`\n- **URL**: N/A (local system)\n\n## Error Learning Loop\n- **Status**: Live\n- **Tech Stack**: Python, cron, semantic deduplication\n- **Description**: Autonomous incident capture, deduplication, and guardrail promotion system\n- **Location**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/error-learning-loop/`\n- **URL**: N/A (internal tool)\n\n## Workspace Janitor\n- **Status**: Live\n- **Tech Stack**: Python, file classification, cleanup automation\n- **Description**: Safe workspace maintenance with user-authorized cleanup\n- **Location**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/workspace-janitor/`\n- **URL**: N/A (internal tool)\n\n## Agent Watchdog\n- **Status**: Live\n- **Tech Stack**: Python, session monitoring, stall detection\n- **Description**: Monitors running agents and detects stalls for automatic recovery\n- **Location**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/`\n- **URL**: N/A (internal tool)\n\n## Salesforce Development Skills\n- **Status**: In progress\n- **Tech Stack**: Salesforce, Apex, LWC, Python analysis\n- **Description**: Production-ready skills for Salesforce architecture and code auditing\n- **Location**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/`, `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-code-auditor/`\n- **URL**: N/A (skills development)\n\n---\n\n## Update Policy (Hardening CHANGE 8)\n**Conservative updates only:**\n- ✅ **Sufficient context exists** → Update normally\n- ⚠️ **Partial/uncertain context** → Preserve existing entries, mark uncertain rows with `[?]`\n- ❌ **Information too weak** → Ask user instead of overwriting\n\n**Before any overwrite:**\n1. Create backup in `memory/backups/`\n2. Log update in `memory_curation_log.md`\n\n**If projects.md becomes too large/noisy:**\n- Emit incident: `memory|QUALITY|projects_registry|too_large|needs_pruning`\n\n*Note: Please provide details about your active external projects for a more complete registry.*"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773082270286}}
