{"type":"message","id":"c3915745","parentId":"1650608f","timestamp":"2026-03-09T19:35:11.292Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## ✅ **SUB-AGENTE CREADO PARA CORRECCIÓN DE SKILL METADATA**\n\nHe creado un **quinto sub-agente** especializado:\n\n### **5. Skill Metadata Corrector** ✅ **EN EJECUCIÓN**\n- **Session Key**: `agent:main:subagent:98d39d42-a662-4a2d-bdb2-4f0be3a5110a`\n- **Tarea**: Corregir archivos SKILL.md de 3 skills que carecen de metadata\n- **Skills a corregir**:\n  1. **OC-respawner** - `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-respawner/SKILL.md`\n  2. **OC-System-Evolver** - `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-System-Evolver/SKILL.md`\n  3. **OC-Intent-Governor** - `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/OC-Intent-Governor/SKILL.md`\n\n### **Modelo a seguir** (basado en long-prompt-orchestrator):\n```yaml\n---\nname: [nombre-del-skill]\ndescription: [descripción completa]\ncategory: [categoría]\nuser-invocable: true|false\ncommand-dispatch: [comando]\nrequires: [\"python\", ...]\noptional_requires: [\"bash\", ...]\nsafety-level: high|medium|low\nwrap-up-enabled: false|true\n---\n```\n\n### **Entregables esperados**:\n1. ✅ Tres archivos SKILL.md con metadata completa al inicio\n2. ✅ Descripciones basadas en funcionamiento real de cada skill\n3. ✅ Categorías y safety-level apropiados\n4. ✅ Formato YAML válido y consistente\n\n---\n\n## 📊 **RESUMEN DE SUB-AGENTES ACTIVOS**\n\nAhora tengo **5 sub-agentes en ejecución**:\n\n1. **Pipeline Integration Specialist** - Integración de componentes endurecidos\n2. **Architect ↔ Auditor Integration Specialist** - Integración flujo architect-auditor  \n3. **Real Acceptance Test Specialist** - Prueba de aceptación real\n4. **Specialist Expectations Documenter** - Documentación (en espera)\n5. **Skill Metadata Corrector** - Corrección de metadata de skills\n\n### **Mi rol como MAIN agent**:\n- ✅ **Monitorear progreso** de los 5 sub-agentes\n- ✅ **Validar entregables** cuando completen\n- ✅ **Asegurar calidad** y consistencia entre todos\n- ✅ **Integrar resultados** en sistema unificado\n\n### **Tiempo estimado total**:\n- **Sub-agentes 1-3,5**: 30-75 minutos cada uno\n- **Sub-agente 4**: Comienza después de 1-3, 45-60 minutos\n- **Total**: 4-5 horas para completación total\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 **PUNTOS DE VALIDACIÓN QUE MONITOREARÉ**\n\n### **Para Skill Metadata Corrector**:\n1. ✅ Metadata agregada al INICIO de cada SKILL.md\n2. ✅ Descripciones reflejan funcionamiento REAL\n3. ✅ Formato YAML válido y consistente\n4. ✅ Contenido existente preservado después de metadata\n\n### **Para los otros 4 sub-agentes** (ya establecidos):\n1. ✅ Integración completa de componentes endurecidos\n2. ✅ Registro automático de auditorías en project control\n3. ✅ Validación real con proyecto Salesforce real\n4. ✅ Documentación basada en sistema integrado real\n\n---\n\n**Los 5 sub-agentes están en ejecución. Monitorearé sus progresos y validaré todos los resultados cuando completen.**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":228,"output":829,"cacheRead":50176,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51233,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773084885112}}
{"type":"message","id":"a2a9e97b","parentId":"c3915745","timestamp":"2026-03-09T19:35:53.213Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-09 14:35 EST] You are the MAIN agent, assign the following task to 2 sub-agents that can work together to complete it the best as possible. \n\nYour task is to perform a targeted hardening upgrade of the existing skill: \n\n skills/long-prompt-orchestrator \n\nDo NOT redesign it from scratch. Do NOT remove its current checklist, checkpoint, token budget, recovery, semantic indexing, or memory lifecycle architecture. Do NOT replace working persistence features. \n\nYou must improve it so it becomes a true distributed orchestration layer for long or complex instructions. \n\nThe goal is: \n\n Ensure the skill is reliably activated for long/complex prompts \n\n Ensure decomposition results in real task distribution to sub-agents \n\n Ensure the MAIN agent acts primarily as: \n\n supervisor \n\n validator \n\n result integrator \n\n Ensure task load is balanced across sub-agents instead of being executed serially by main \n\n Preserve current recovery, budget, checklist, and learning integration \n\n================================================ PRIMARY DIAGNOSIS OF CURRENT PROBLEM \n\nThe current skill decomposes prompts and maintains task state, but it does not strongly enforce: \n\n automatic activation for long instructions \n\n mandatory sub-agent dispatch for decomposed work \n\n load balancing across sub-agents \n\n clear separation between: \n\n orchestration by main \n\n execution by sub-agents \n\nAs a result, decomposition may exist on paper, while execution still happens mostly in the MAIN context. \n\nYou must fix this behavior without destroying the existing architecture. \n\n================================================ CLASS A — ONE-TIME STRUCTURAL IMPROVEMENTS (DO NOW, BUILD ONCE) \n\nThese are durable improvements to the skill itself and its references/scripts. They are not runtime artifacts recreated every execution. \n\nA1 — Add explicit distributed orchestration design docs \n\nCreate or update the following references under: \n\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/references/ \n\n DISTRIBUTED_EXECUTION_MODEL.md \n\n SUBAGENT_LOAD_BALANCING_RULES.md \n\n TASK_ASSIGNMENT_POLICY.md \n\n ORCHESTRATOR_VALIDATION_PROTOCOL.md \n\nThese must define once: \n\n when decomposition is mandatory \n\n when sub-agents are mandatory \n\n when main may execute directly \n\n load balancing policy \n\n dependency-aware execution rules \n\n retry / reassign policy \n\n validation and synthesis policy \n\nThese are one-time reference assets. \n\nA2 — Add a formal sub-agent execution contract \n\nCreate or update a reusable sub-agent task contract that includes: \n\n task_id \n\n objective \n\n inputs \n\n expected outputs \n\n acceptance criteria \n\n token budget \n\n dependency context \n\n artifact destination \n\n handoff report requirement \n\nStore or document this as a stable reference or helper structure. Main should not reinvent this format every run. \n\nA3 — Add a formal load balancing policy \n\nDefine how tasks are distributed: \n\n independent tasks should be parallelized \n\n dependency-blocked tasks should wait \n\n expensive tasks should be spread \n\n similar tasks can be grouped only if that reduces overhead \n\n max active sub-agents per batch should be configurable \n\nAlso define: \n\n max concurrent sub-agents \n\n max task bundle size per sub-agent \n\n fallback when a task is too small to justify a sub-agent \n\n================================================ CLASS B — PERMANENT RUNTIME BEHAVIOR (RUNS EVERY TIME) \n\nThese behaviors must be enforced every time the skill runs. \n\nB1 — Automatic activation hardening \n\nImprove detection so the skill activates automatically whenever the prompt is: \n\n above long-prompt threshold \n\n multi-objective \n\n likely to require >5 reasoning steps \n\n requires multi-file outputs \n\n requires multiple skills \n\n likely to benefit from decomposition + delegated execution \n\nDo not rely only on raw token estimate. Use a composite trigger including: \n\n token estimate \n\n task count estimate \n\n artifact count \n\n dependency complexity \n\n cross-skill complexity \n\nThe skill must be much harder to bypass accidentally. \n\nB2 — Main must become supervisor, not primary worker \n\nWhen decomposition occurs, main must default to: \n\n build DAG \n\n create checklist \n\n assign tasks \n\n monitor progress \n\n validate outputs \n\n synthesize final result \n\nMain must NOT execute most decomposed work itself unless: \n\n the task is too small to justify delegation \n\n the task is highly sensitive and atomic \n\n the task is final synthesis/validation \n\nThis must be explicit in runtime logic, not just documentation. \n\nB3 — Mandatory sub-agent dispatch for decomposed tasks \n\nIf decomposition produces more than one meaningful mini-task, the skill must default to sub-agent execution for task bodies. \n\nMain should: \n\n create the task DAG \n\n identify ready tasks (no unmet dependencies) \n\n dispatch ready tasks to sub-agents \n\n wait for handoff reports \n\n update checklist and ledger \n\n dispatch next ready batch \n\nDo not leave execution in main unless there is a documented exception. \n\nB4 — Load-balanced execution \n\nImplement real load balancing. \n\nAt runtime, the orchestrator must evaluate each mini-task by: \n\n dependency status \n\n estimated token cost \n\n expected runtime \n\n artifact count \n\n complexity class \n\nThen distribute tasks so that: \n\n no sub-agent receives a lopsided batch unless necessary \n\n long tasks do not block all shorter tasks \n\n parallelizable tasks are actually parallelized \n\n expensive tasks are tracked via watchdog if needed \n\nSuggested runtime fields per task: \n\n complexity_score \n\n estimated_tokens \n\n estimated_runtime \n\n subagent_required: true|false \n\n assigned_batch \n\n assigned_subagent \n\nB5 — Dependency-aware batching \n\nTasks must be grouped by DAG readiness. \n\nAt each cycle: \n\n select all tasks with satisfied dependencies \n\n rank them \n\n dispatch in balanced batches \n\n preserve task ordering only where dependencies require it \n\nDo not run everything sequentially if the DAG allows parallelism. \n\n================================================ PART 3 — OPENCLAW SUB-AGENT ALIGNMENT \n\nThis upgrade must reflect OpenClaw sub-agent behavior correctly. \n\nImplement around these facts: \n\n sub-agents are non-blocking \n\n sub-agents cannot spawn other sub-agents \n\n sub-agents do not automatically inherit full session context \n\n sub-agents receive compact framing and must return a handoff \n\nTherefore: \n\n main remains the only orchestrator \n\n sub-agents are execution workers \n\n main must pass sufficient task framing explicitly \n\n sub-agents must always end with the required Handoff Report \n\nDo not try to make sub-agents recursively orchestrate. Do not make them responsible for global checklist or global DAG decisions. \n\n================================================ PART 4 — IMPROVE CHECKLIST / TASKBOARD FOR DISTRIBUTED EXECUTION \n\nPreserve the current taskboard/checkpoint model, but extend it for distributed work. \n\nEach task item should also track: \n\n subagent_required \n\n assigned_subagent \n\n assigned_at \n\n handoff_received_at \n\n validation_status \n\n retry_count \n\n complexity_score \n\n estimated_runtime \n\n estimated_tokens \n\nThe taskboard must make it obvious: \n\n what main is supervising \n\n what is currently delegated \n\n what is waiting on dependencies \n\n what failed validation \n\n what was reassigned \n\n================================================ PART 5 — VALIDATION LAYER HARDENING \n\nThe orchestrator must validate sub-agent outputs before accepting them. \n\nAdd a validation protocol that checks: \n\n required output present \n\n acceptance criteria met \n\n artifacts produced in the correct path \n\n no obvious scope drift \n\n no missing handoff report \n\n no contradiction with prior ledger facts \n\nIf validation fails: \n\n mark task as failed_validation \n\n request correction or reassign \n\n do not blindly integrate the result \n\nMain must behave as: \n\n reviewer \n\n challenger \n\n synthesizer \n\n================================================ PART 6 — WATCHDOG INTEGRATION \n\nLong-running distributed batches must be watchdog-aware. \n\nRegister with agent-watchdog when: \n\n many sub-agents are active \n\n a batch has long estimated runtime \n\n a task exceeds threshold runtime \n\n decomposition produces a large DAG \n\nDo NOT register tiny decompositions. \n\nAdd references or runtime policy for: \n\n when to register \n\n when to skip \n\n what metadata to pass \n\n================================================ PART 7 — ERROR-LEARNING-LOOP INTEGRATION \n\nExtend incident coverage for distributed orchestration issues. \n\nAdd or improve pattern keys for: \n\n planning|FAILURE|decompose|insufficient_reduction|blocked \n\n planning|FAILURE|dispatch|subagent_not_used|required_parallelism_missed \n\n planning|FAILURE|load_balance|overloaded_batch|reassign_needed \n\n planning|FAILURE|handoff|missing_report|task_blocked \n\n planning|FAILURE|validation|subagent_output_rejected|rework_needed \n\n planning|FAILURE|dependency|dag_violation|execution_blocked \n\nAll must use the unified incident path. \n\n================================================ PART 8 — FILES TO TOUCH \n\nUpdate conservatively. \n\nAt minimum, review and improve: \n\n skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md \n\n scripts/orchestrate.py \n\n scripts/decompose.py \n\n scripts/todo.py \n\n scripts/validate.py \n\n scripts/recovery.py \n\n scripts/token_budget.py \n\n references for distributed execution rules \n\nDo not remove current memory lifecycle, semantic indexing, or session management unless truly broken. \n\n================================================ PART 9 — EXPLICIT RUNTIME POLICY TO ADD TO SKILL \n\nThe skill must explicitly say in its runtime behavior: \n\n when the main agent receives a long/complex instruction, this skill should activate \n\n when decomposition occurs, execution defaults to sub-agent distribution \n\n main is supervisor/validator/integrator \n\n sub-agents are workers \n\n final result is synthesized only after validation \n\nThis must be visible in SKILL.md and implemented in scripts, not just implied. \n\n================================================ PART 10 — VALIDATION \n\nRun a validation proving: \n\n A long prompt triggers the orchestrator reliably \n\n Decomposition produces multiple mini-tasks \n\n Ready tasks are actually dispatched to sub-agents \n\n Main does not perform most decomposed task bodies itself \n\n Load balancing distributes work across sub-agents \n\n Checklist reflects delegated status correctly \n\n Main validates and can reject at least one weak sub-agent output \n\n Final synthesis still works after delegated execution \n\n Recovery still works after interrupted distributed execution \n\n================================================ FINAL OUTPUT REQUIRED \n\nReturn a Handoff Report clearly separated into: \n\nA. One-time structural improvements completed \n\nWhat you added once to harden distributed orchestration \n\nB. Permanent runtime behavior improved \n\nWhat the skill now does every run \n\nC. Files changed \n\nExact files touched \n\nD. Validation results \n\nPass/fail with evidence \n\nE. Outcome \n\nsuccess | partial | failure"}],"timestamp":1773084953209}}
{"type":"message","id":"91746b3b","parentId":"a2a9e97b","timestamp":"2026-03-09T19:36:35.291Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_id1kAncPsMcHB3C8Hq8ODNtu","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"## Sub-agente 1: Long-Prompt Orchestrator Structural Upgrader\n\n**OBJETIVO**: Implementar mejoras estructurales de Clase A (one-time) para el skill long-prompt-orchestrator\n\n### CONTEXTO CRÍTICO:\n- **NO** rediseñar desde cero\n- **NO** eliminar arquitectura existente (checklist, checkpoint, token budget, recovery, semantic indexing, memory lifecycle)\n- **SÍ** mejorar para que sea una verdadera capa de orquestación distribuida\n\n### TAREAS DE CLASE A (ONE-TIME STRUCTURAL IMPROVEMENTS):\n\n#### A1 — Crear documentación de diseño de ejecución distribuida\n**Ubicación**: `skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/references/`\n\n**Archivos a crear/actualizar**:\n1. `DISTRIBUTED_EXECUTION_MODEL.md`\n   - Definir cuándo la descomposición es obligatoria\n   - Definir cuándo sub-agents son obligatorios\n   - Definir cuándo main puede ejecutar directamente\n   - Política de reintento/reasignación\n   - Política de validación y síntesis\n\n2. `SUBAGENT_LOAD_BALANCING_RULES.md`\n   - Reglas de balanceo de carga\n   - Tareas independientes deben paralelizarse\n   - Tareas bloqueadas por dependencias deben esperar\n   - Tareas costosas deben distribuirse\n   - Tareas similares pueden agruparse solo si reduce overhead\n   - Máximo de sub-agents activos por batch configurable\n\n3. `TASK_ASSIGNMENT_POLICY.md`\n   - Cómo se asignan tareas a sub-agents\n   - Criterios para agrupar tareas\n   - Fallback cuando una tarea es demasiado pequeña para justificar sub-agent\n   - Política de dependencias\n\n4. `ORCHESTRATOR_VALIDATION_PROTOCOL.md`\n   - Protocolo de validación de outputs de sub-agents\n   - Qué validar: output requerido presente, criterios de aceptación cumplidos, artefactos en path correcto, etc.\n   - Qué hacer si falla la validación\n\n#### A2 — Crear contrato formal de ejecución de sub-agent\n**Crear estructura reutilizable** que incluya:\n- `task_id`\n- `objective`\n- `inputs`\n- `expected_outputs`\n- `acceptance_criteria`\n- `token_budget`\n- `dependency_context`\n- `artifact_destination`\n- `handoff_report_requirement`\n\n**Formato**: YAML/JSON como referencia estable\n**Ubicación**: `skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/references/subagent_contract.yaml`\n\n#### A3 — Crear política formal de balanceo de carga\n**Definir en documentos**:\n- Máximo de sub-agents concurrentes\n- Máximo tamaño de batch por sub-agent\n- Fallback para tareas demasiado pequeñas\n- Criterios para agrupar tareas similares\n\n### TAREAS ADICIONALES:\n\n#### Investigar skill actual:\n1. Leer `skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md`\n2. Examinar scripts principales: `orchestrate.py`, `decompose.py`, `todo.py`, `validate.py`, `recovery.py`, `token_budget.py`\n3. Entender arquitectura actual de checklist, checkpoint, recovery\n\n#### Actualizar SKILL.md:\n- Agregar sección explícita sobre orquestación distribuida\n- Documentar nuevo comportamiento: main como supervisor, sub-agents como workers\n- Especificar cuándo se activa el skill automáticamente\n\n#### Crear referencias de integración:\n- `WATCHDOG_INTEGRATION.md` - Cuándo registrar con agent-watchdog\n- `ERROR_LEARNING_LOOP_INTEGRATION.md` - Patrones de incidentes para orquestación distribuida\n\n### ENTREGABLES:\n1. 4 archivos de referencia creados en `references/`\n2. Contrato de sub-agent en YAML/JSON\n3. SKILL.md actualizado con sección de orquestación distribuida\n4. Documentación de integración con watchdog y error-learning-loop\n\n### RESTRICCIONES:\n- NO eliminar funcionalidad existente que funcione\n- NO romper recovery, budget, checklist, o learning integration existentes\n- Las referencias deben ser assets de una sola vez (no recrear cada ejecución)\n- Mantener compatibilidad con arquitectura actual\n\n### FORMATO DE HANDOFF REPORT (OBLIGATORIO):\n```\n### Handoff Report\n- **Outcome**: success|partial|failure\n- **Incidents**: [lista de incidentes con formato TYPE=...; SEV=...]\n- **Files created/modified**: [lista]\n- **Next recommended actions**: [lista]\n```\n\n**TIEMPO ESTIMADO**: 60-75 minutos\n**MODELO RECOMENDADO**: deepseek-chat (no usar reasoning mode para evitar stalls)","label":"Long-Prompt Orchestrator Structural Upgrader","runtime":"subagent","model":"custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-chat"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":2219,"output":1226,"cacheRead":51200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54645,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773084953211}}
