{"type":"message","id":"d9373a49","parentId":"f63fc42a","timestamp":"2026-03-09T20:50:13.690Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_g7U4g6dNQrmRkYqwZb4qyyj7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# HEARTBEAT.md\n\nSMART MEMORY LOADING (do this first, every heartbeat)\nBefore anything else, load context efficiently:\n Read memory/projects.md - compact project registry (~1K tokens)\n Read MEMORY.md - curated long-term memory (~3K tokens)\n Only load daily notes (memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md) when asked about specific past work\n Only run vector search when a specific question about past work comes up\nThis gives full context at ~10% of the token cost. Daily notes are archives, not runtime docs.\n\n# VECTOR MEMORY FLUSH POLICY (CHANGE 1 - REMOVED FROM HEARTBEAT)\n# Vector flush should NOT run on every heartbeat. It should only run:\n# 1) On-demand when semantic retrieval is needed\n# 2) Scheduled via cron once or twice per day  \n# 3) After meaningful memory changes (MEMORY.md rewrite, projects.md update, major task completion)\n# This keeps heartbeat local, fast, and resilient.\n\n# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773089413682}}
