{"type":"message","id":"ccef3c13","parentId":"36ba1009","timestamp":"2026-03-09T20:56:03.404Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## ✅ **Long-Prompt Orchestrator Production Certification Validator - CREADO**\n\nHe creado un sub-agente especializado para la **validación final de certificación** del skill `long-prompt-orchestrator`.\n\n### 🎯 **OBJETIVO PRINCIPAL:**\n**CONFIRMAR que la integración de sub-agents es realmente operativa en OpenClaw y no una simulación maquillada.**\n\n### 🚫 **RESTRICCIONES ESTRICTAS:**\n- ✅ **NO** cambios de código\n- ✅ **SOLO** validación real del comportamiento\n- ✅ **EVIDENCIA OBJETIVA** requerida, no narrativa solamente\n\n### 🔍 **4 PUNTOS CRÍTICOS DE VALIDACIÓN:**\n\n#### **1. ✅ Sub-agents REALES (no abstracción local)**\n- Verificar que sean sesiones/sub-agents **reales** de OpenClaw\n- **NO** aceptar abstracción local con UUID solamente\n- **Evidencia**: IDs reales, `session_id`, `run_id`\n\n#### **2. ✅ Handoff Reports REALES (no fabricados)**\n- Confirmar Handoff Reports **emitidos por sub-agents**\n- **NO** aceptar handoffs fabricados por orchestrator\n- **Evidencia**: Extractos reales de Handoff Reports\n\n#### **3. ✅ Watchdog monitoring REAL**\n- Verificar que `agent-watchdog` vea los runs reales\n- **Evidencia**: `session_id` y `run_id` en logs de watchdog\n\n#### **4. ✅ Prueba compleja REAL**\n- **Mínimo 3 mini-tasks** generadas\n- **Mínimo 2 sub-agents distintos** utilizados\n- **Mínimo 1 validación explícita** por main\n- **1 síntesis final** hecha por main\n\n### 🧪 **PROMPT COMPLEJO DE PRUEBA:**\n```\nDiseña e implementa un sistema de monitoreo de salud para agentes AI en OpenClaw...\n```\n*(5 componentes detallados que obligan a descomposición real)*\n\n### 📋 **EVIDENCIA MÍNIMA REQUERIDA:**\n\n#### **A. IDs reales de ejecución** - `session_id`, `run_id`, timestamps\n#### **B. Handoff Reports reales** - Extractos completos, formato correcto\n#### **C. Taskboard evidence** - Assignment, handoff, estado, progreso\n#### **D. Main como supervisor** - NO ejecuta task bodies complejos\n#### **E. Watchdog integration** - Registration, monitoring, logs\n#### **F. Síntesis final** - Output consolidado por main\n\n### 📊 **CRITERIO DE APROBACIÓN:**\n**SOLO** marcar como **\"validated for production\"** si:\n- ✅ **4/4 puntos** comprobados con evidencia real\n- ✅ **0 puntos ambiguos** o no verificados\n- ✅ **EVIDENCIA CONCRETA** para cada punto\n\n**Si falla:** Marcar como **parcial/fallido** y explicar **exactamente qué faltó**.\n\n### 📁 **ENTREGABLES REQUERIDOS:**\n1. **`LONG_PROMPT_ORCHESTRATOR_CERTIFICATION_REPORT.md`** - Resumen de validación\n2. **`LONG_PROMPT_ORCHESTRATOR_EVIDENCE.md`** - Evidencia completa\n3. **Handoff Report final** del validador\n\n### ⏱️ **TIEMPO ESTIMADO:** 30-35 minutos\n\n### 📈 **ESTADO ACTUAL DE SUB-AGENTES:**\n\n#### **Activos (2):**\n1. **Compliance Validator & Final Integration Specialist** - 🔄 EN EJECUCIÓN (~6m)\n2. **Long-Prompt Orchestrator Production Certification Validator** - 🔄 EN EJECUCIÓN (0m)\n\n#### **Completados (8):** Todos los sub-agentes de implementación\n\n**El validador está ejecutando una prueba rigurosa para certificar que el long-prompt-orchestrator usa spawning REAL de sub-agents, no simulación maquillada.**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":207,"output":930,"cacheRead":108992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110129,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773089733940}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"9d0c0dd9","parentId":"ccef3c13","timestamp":"2026-03-09T20:58:05.708Z","summary":"## Goal\nPerform targeted hardening upgrade of Salesforce skill ecosystem (salesforce-architect and salesforce-code-auditor) to make salesforce-architect the single governing skill, tighten project routing, formalize specialist roles and project state machine, improve architect ↔ code-auditor integration, and preserve current working pipelines. Additionally, distribute and monitor sub-agent work for: 1) Integrating hardened components into the architect pipeline, 2) Integrating architect ↔ auditor flow, 3) Executing a real Salesforce acceptance test, 4) Documenting specialist expectations. Also, correct SKILL.md metadata for OC-respawner, OC-System-Evolver, and OC-Intent-Governor. Also, perform a targeted hardening upgrade of the `long-prompt-orchestrator` skill to become a true distributed orchestration layer without redesigning from scratch.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- **Incremental upgrade**: Not a greenfield redesign or replacement of current architecture.\n- **Preserve current behavior**: Keep working pipelines, artifacts, EC0249 enforcement, reference PDF enforcement, Salesforce evidence policy, project runtime structure, code-auditor case model, learning integration, watchdog compatibility, handoff report requirement.\n- **Separate work classes**:\n  - **Class A (One-time foundation)**: Create stable reference assets (role model, state machine, DoD, handoff contract) once, store in references/, do not regenerate every run.\n  - **Class B (Permanent runtime behavior)**: Improve runtime enforcement (project routing, sub-agent usage, phase-awareness, incident hardening).\n- **Do not redefine roles every run**: Use stable role model from references.\n- **Use sub-agents as default specialist execution model**.\n- **Avoid persistent agent sprawl**.\n- **Update files conservatively**: Minimum changes to SKILL.md, run_pipeline.py, supporting scripts.\n- **Validation required**: Test project folder creation, artifact containment, role assignment, code-auditor invocation, output rejection, README updates, state machine respect, DoD enforcement.\n- **Follow HEARTBEAT.md smart memory loading**: Load memory/projects.md and MEMORY.md first each heartbeat; vector flush removed from heartbeat; only load daily notes when asked about past work.\n- **For long-prompt-orchestrator upgrade**: Do NOT redesign from scratch. Do NOT remove its current checklist, checkpoint, token budget, recovery, semantic indexing, or memory lifecycle architecture. Do NOT replace working persistence features. Improve it to become a true distributed orchestration layer where the MAIN agent acts as supervisor/validator/integrator and task load is balanced across sub-agents.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Deleted five agents (discovery, ingesta, semantico, validador, organizador) and their workspaces.\n- [x] Updated `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/openclaw.json` to remove deleted agent references.\n- [x] Performed post-update quick check and fixed four issues (Tavily API Key, Workspace Janitor, Vector Memory, cron job Telegram delivery).\n- [x] Updated cron job `f0b88442-8dbd-416d-8444-75c611abac46` payload to `\"workspace-janitor scan\"` and cleared its zombie state.\n- [x] Verified manual cron job run (`manual:f0b88442-8dbd-416d-8444-75c611abac46:1773075362275:2`) completed successfully.\n- [x] **Class A foundation work**: Created 6 stable reference files in references/ (SALESFORCE_ROLE_MODEL.md, ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md, SALESFORCE_PROJECT_STATE_MACHINE.md, DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md, CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md, ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md).\n- [x] **Updated salesforce-architect/SKILL.md**: Added hardened governance, routing, sub-agent usage, code-auditor integration, phase-aware behavior, and incident hardening sections.\n- [x] **Created hardened pipeline script**: Created `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/scripts/run_pipeline_hardened.py` with `HardenedPipeline` class.\n- [x] **Partial update to utils_io.py**: Began adding hardening functions section with `load_governance_reference` stub.\n- [x] **Salesforce Skill Hardening Upgrade - COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY** (2026-03-09 13:25 - 14:22 EST). All 4 priority improvements implemented:\n    1. **Parser estructurado para referencias**: Converted all references to structured YAML format (`role_model.yaml`, `state_machine.yaml`, `dod_definitions.yaml`).\n    2. **Motor real de state machine**: Created `state_machine_engine.py` with robust validation.\n    3. **Validación determinística de DoD**: Implemented `dod_validator.py` with deterministic rules.\n    4. **README / Project control file robusto**: Developed `project_control.py` with complete system and `integrated_hardening.py` unified API.\n- [x] **Skill Metadata Corrector completed**: Corrected SKILL.md metadata for 3 skills (now lowercase names: `oc-respawner`, `oc-system-evolver`, `oc-intent-governor`) with proper YAML frontmatter.\n- [x] **Pipeline Integration Specialist completed**: Successfully integrated hardened components into `run_pipeline.py` at 5 critical moments (opening project, before phase change, before accepting sub-agent outputs, before closing deliverable, before marking phase complete). Fixed syntax error in `state_machine_engine.py` (line 449).\n- [x] **Architect ↔ Auditor Integration Specialist completed**: Successfully implemented integration with automatic project control registration, DoD validation of auditor outputs, blocking logic based on results, and incident generation. Created `auditor_integration.py`, `state_machine_engine_enhanced.py`, `dod_auditor_validator.py`, etc.\n- [x] **Long-Prompt Orchestrator Structural Upgrader completed**: Implemented Class A (one-time) structural improvements. Created 7 reference files (`DISTRIBUTED_EXECUTION_MODEL.md`, `SUBAGENT_LOAD_BALANCING_RULES.md`, `TASK_ASSIGNMENT_POLICY.md`, `ORCHESTRATOR_VALIDATION_PROTOCOL.md`, `subagent_contract.yaml`, `WATCHDOG_INTEGRATION.md`, `ERROR_LEARNING_LOOP_INTEGRATION.md`) and updated SKILL.md.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Real Acceptance Test Specialist**: Completed with partial result (4/6 critical points validated). Created real Salesforce project \"Lead Management Enhancement\". Point 2 (State transitions) failed due to state machine engine syntax error (now fixed by Pipeline Integration Specialist). Needs re-execution.\n- [ ] **Specialist Expectations Documenter**: Reactivated and currently running. Task: Document expectations for specialists based on the REAL integrated system (after other sub-agents completed).\n- [ ] **Long-Prompt Orchestrator Runtime Behavior Upgrader**: Currently running. Task: Implement Class B (permanent runtime behavior) improvements: automatic activation hardening, making main a supervisor (not primary worker), mandatory sub-agent dispatch, load-balanced execution, dependency-aware batching, validation layer hardening, watchdog integration, error-learning-loop integration.\n\n### Blocked\nNone.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Created wrapper scripts for skill invocation**: For Workspace Janitor and Vector Memory, creating centralized wrapper/status scripts was chosen as the optimal best practice for maintainability.\n- **Modified config loading to expand env vars**: Updated `load_config` in `tavily_integrations.py` to recursively expand environment variable placeholders (e.g., `${TAVILY_API_KEY}`) for security.\n- **Removed Telegram delivery from cron jobs**: Delivery mode set to `\"none\"` as specified.\n- **Stable role model**: Created once in references/, not reinvented per run. Architect selects from pre-defined roles.\n- **Project state machine**: Formalized 9-state lifecycle with hard rules (e.g., no FIT_GAP without scope/SOW).\n- **Sub-agent default**: Specialists executed as sub-agents, not persistent agents, to avoid sprawl.\n- **Architect as single governor**: All Salesforce work routed through salesforce-architect, all artifacts contained in project folders.\n- **Code auditor as subordinate validator**: Integrated via formal handoff modes (A, B, C) with severity-based blocking.\n- **Separate hardened pipeline script**: Created `run_pipeline_hardened.py` as new entry point with governance, preserving original `run_pipeline.py`.\n- **Incremental file updates**: Editing `utils_io.py` in sections to add hardening functions.\n- **Removed vector flush from heartbeat**: Vector memory flush should not run on every heartbeat. It should only run on-demand for semantic retrieval, via scheduled cron, or after meaningful memory changes (MEMORY.md rewrite, projects.md update, major task completion). This keeps heartbeat local, fast, and resilient.\n- **Distributed work via sub-agents**: For the 4-point Salesforce integration task, created 4 specialized sub-agents (Pipeline Integration Specialist, Architect ↔ Auditor Integration Specialist, Real Acceptance Test Specialist, Specialist Expectations Documenter) and monitored their progress.\n- **Corrected skill metadata to lowercase**: Standardized skill names to lowercase with hyphens (`oc-respawner`, `oc-system-evolver`, `oc-intent-governor`) for consistency.\n- **Long-prompt-orchestrator upgrade split**: Divided work into 2 sub-agents: Structural Upgrader (Class A one-time improvements) and Runtime Behavior Upgrader (Class B permanent runtime behavior).\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Wait for completion of Specialist Expectations Documenter and Long-Prompt Orchestrator Runtime Behavior Upgrader sub-agents.\n2. Re-execute the real acceptance test (point 3) now that the state machine engine syntax error is fixed.\n3. Create a Compliance Validator sub-agent to validate full compliance against the original 4-point instruction after all sub-agents complete.\n4. Integrate final results and provide complete report.\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Current skill structure**:\n  - `salesforce-architect/scripts/`: Contains `run_pipeline.py`, `run_pipeline_hardened.py`, `stage1_discovery.py` to `stage7_export.py`, `utils_io.py`, `state_machine_engine.py`, `dod_validator.py`, `project_control.py`, `integrated_hardening.py`, etc.\n  - `salesforce-code-auditor/scripts/`: Contains `init_case.py`, `index_inputs.py`, `build_dependency_graph.py`, `generate_reports.py`, etc.\n- **Reference PDFs required**: Located in `<workspace>/references/` (`_F3.1 Definición de diseño funcional VF.pdf`, `IDEINCA - Matriz FIT and GAP.pdf`, etc.).\n- **Project folder layout**: `<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/` with subfolders for discovery, fit_gap, design, data_model, architecture, evidence.\n- **Code audit case structure**: `<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/code_audit/<case_id>/` with inputs, work, snippets, outputs.\n- **Validation demo project**: `demo_salesforce_architect`.\n- **Incident examples**: `salesforce|PROJECT_ROUTING|missing_project_key|blocked`, `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|design_alignment_gap|review_required`.\n- **HEARTBEAT.md location**: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md` instructs smart memory loading: read `memory/projects.md` and `MEMORY.md` first each heartbeat; vector flush removed; daily notes only loaded when asked about past work.\n- **Active projects per memory**: OpenClaw Memory System, Error Learning Loop, Workspace Janitor, Agent Watchdog, Salesforce Development Skills.\n- **Improvements sub-agent ID**: `613cc35a-a953-4491-8931-bc75e625a2a7`.\n- **System version**: OpenClaw 2026.3.8.\n- **Vector memory status**: PostgreSQL connected, but Gemini Embeddings API not installed (`google-generativeai not installed`).\n- **Main agent's workspace**: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace` is intact and must not be modified unless related to specific agents being deleted.\n- **Sub-agent session keys currently active**:\n  - `agent:main:subagent:12c0b6a3-d572-4f7f-ba08-9193fb8321ff` (Specialist Expectations Documenter)\n  - `agent:main:subagent:751f055e-06b4-47ac-af68-4d0f5e0fc984` (Long-Prompt Orchestrator Runtime Behavior Upgrader)\n- **Real acceptance test project**: `lead_management_enhancement` created at `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/projects/lead_management_enhancement/`.\n- **Long-prompt-orchestrator references created**: `DISTRIBUTED_EXECUTION_MODEL.md`, `SUBAGENT_LOAD_BALANCING_RULES.md`, `TASK_ASSIGNMENT_POLICY.md`, `ORCHESTRATOR_VALIDATION_PROTOCOL.md`, `subagent_contract.yaml`, `WATCHDOG_INTEGRATION.md`, `ERROR_LEARNING_LOOP_INTEGRATION.md`.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- **Removed vector flush from heartbeat**: Vector memory flush should not run on every heartbeat. It should only run on-demand for semantic retrieval, via scheduled cron, or after meaningful memory changes (MEMORY.md rewrite, projects.md update, major task completion). This keeps heartbeat local, fast, and resilient.\n- **Distributed Salesforce integration work to 4 sub-agents**: Pipeline Integration Specialist, Architect ↔ Auditor Integration Specialist, Real Acceptance Test Specialist, Specialist Expectations Documenter (to run after integration).\n- **Corrected skill metadata for 3 skills**: Updated SKILL.md files for OC-respawner, OC-System-Evolver, OC-Intent-Governor to have proper YAML frontmatter with lowercase names.\n- **Split long-prompt-orchestrator upgrade into 2 sub-agents**: Structural Upgrader (Class A one-time) and Runtime Behavior Upgrader (Class B permanent runtime).\n\n## Open TODOs\n1. Complete the targeted hardening upgrade for the Salesforce skill ecosystem (wait for Specialist Expectations Documenter to finish).\n2. Complete the long-prompt-orchestrator upgrade (wait for Runtime Behavior Upgrader to finish).\n3. Re-execute the real acceptance test for Salesforce (point 3) after state machine fix.\n4. Create Compliance Validator sub-agent to validate full compliance against the original 4-point instruction.\n5. Ensure the next scheduled cron executions (workspace-janitor-daily at 13:00 Mon-Fri America/Panama, memory auto-curation at 14:00 on Mon, Fri) proceed without error.\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Do not modify files in `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace` unless related to the specific agents being deleted.\n- Follow HEARTBEAT.md for memory loading: read `memory/projects.md` and `MEMORY.md` first.\n- No automatic deletion by workspace janitor; requires user confirmation.\n- Conservative updates for memory files: create backups, log changes, ask user if information is weak.\n- For Salesforce hardening: Do not regress existing architect stage pipeline, reference PDF enforcement, EC0249 enforcement, Salesforce evidence policy, current project runtime structure, code-auditor case model, learning integration, watchdog compatibility, or handoff report requirement.\n- For long-prompt-orchestrator upgrade: Do NOT redesign from scratch. Do NOT remove its current checklist, checkpoint, token budget, recovery, semantic indexing, or memory lifecycle architecture. Do NOT replace working persistence features.\n- Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists in workspace context. Follow it strictly. Use exact file path `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md` (case-sensitive). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply `HEARTBEAT_OK`.\n\n## Pending user asks\n- The user asked to create a Compliance Validator sub-agent after the 4 original sub-agents finish, to validate compliance against the original 4-point instruction and its subpoints.\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- **Agent IDs deleted**: discovery, ingesta, semantico, validador, organizador.\n- **Cron Job ID**: `f0b88442-8dbd-416d-8444-75c611abac46`, `ccf8abf3-8317-4333-b980-c2bfe1dfd90f`.\n- **Run ID**: `manual:f0b88442-8dbd-416d-8444-75c611abac46:1773075362275:2`.\n- **Session ID (past)**: `d13a23e6-d7e4-4d0f-8d9e-660ebca4a175`, `8574d43c-5079-4c61-81b8-a8d3cde91a79`.\n- **Sub-agent ID**: `613cc35a-a953-4491-8931-bc75e625a2a7`.\n- **Current active sub-agent session keys**:\n    - `agent:ma