{"type":"message","id":"0364a2ed","parentId":"5628c6ad","timestamp":"2026-03-09T21:09:25.641Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_VfyGn6umb5L3lRaKaAVzXni6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/references/DISTRIBUTED_EXECUTION_MODEL.md","limit":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":196,"output":93,"cacheRead":57728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58017,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773090560685}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3c34b9a","parentId":"0364a2ed","timestamp":"2026-03-09T21:09:25.659Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_VfyGn6umb5L3lRaKaAVzXni6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Distributed Execution Model\n\n## Overview\nThis document defines when and how the Long Prompt Orchestrator transitions from sequential mini-task execution to distributed sub-agent execution. The orchestrator acts as a supervisor that delegates work to specialized sub-agents while maintaining coordination, validation, and recovery.\n\n## Decision Framework: When to Decompose\n\n### Mandatory Decomposition Triggers\nDecomposition is **required** when ANY of the following conditions are met:\n\n1. **Token Threshold**: Estimated prompt tokens > `MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS` (default: 4000)\n2. **Complexity Indicators**:\n   - Expected execution steps > 5 (based on keyword analysis)\n   - Multi-file outputs referenced (≥2 distinct file extensions)\n   - Multi-agent operations mentioned (\"sub‑agent\", \"validator\", \"spawn\", \"parallel\")\n   - Long tool execution sequences (≥4 tool-like keywords)\n3. **Explicit User Request**: User includes decomposition directives (\"break this down\", \"split into steps\", \"create a plan\")\n\n### Optional Decomposition Triggers\nDecomposition is **recommended** when ANY of the following conditions are met:\n\n1. **High-Risk Operations**: Tasks involving:\n   - File system modifications outside workspace\n   - External API calls with rate limits\n   - Database operations\n   - Network-intensive operations\n2. **Specialized Domains**: Tasks requiring:\n   - Salesforce architecture/development\n   - Web search/research operations\n   - Code auditing/security analysis\n\n[206 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773090565651}}
{"type":"message","id":"15022222","parentId":"f3c34b9a","timestamp":"2026-03-09T21:10:00.147Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora, déjame hacer una prueba directa para verificar si un sub-agent puede spawnear otros sub-agents. Voy a crear un pequeño script de prueba:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SDO6tDEOd36K65wRd6yMe3Tw","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/test_subagent_spawn.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTest script to verify if a sub-agent can spawn other sub-agents in OpenClaw.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport subprocess\nimport json\nimport sys\nimport os\n\ndef test_subagent_spawn_capability():\n    \"\"\"Test if sub-agents have permission to spawn other sub-agents.\"\"\"\n    \n    print(\"=== Testing Sub-Agent Spawn Capability ===\\n\")\n    \n    # First, let's check if we're running as a sub-agent\n    print(\"1. Checking current session context...\")\n    \n    # Try to get session information\n    try:\n        # Check if we can access sessions_list tool\n        test_cmd = [\"openclaw\", \"sessions\", \"list\", \"--json\"]\n        result = subprocess.run(test_cmd, capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            print(\"   ✅ Can access sessions list\")\n            sessions_data = json.loads(result.stdout)\n            print(f\"   Total sessions: {sessions_data.get('total', 'unknown')}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"   ❌ Cannot access sessions list: {result.stderr}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"   ⚠️ Error checking sessions: {e}\")\n    \n    print(\"\\n2. Testing sub-agent spawning...\")\n    \n    # Create a simple sub-agent spawn test\n    test_task = \"Test if sub-agent can spawn - respond with 'TEST_SUCCESS'\"\n    \n    spawn_cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\", \"sessions\", \"spawn\",\n        \"--task\", test_task,\n        \"--label\", \"Test Sub-Agent Spawn\",\n        \"--runtime\", \"subagent\",\n        \"--model\", \"deepseek-chat\",\n        \"--mode\", \"run\"\n    ]\n    \n    try:\n        print(f\"   Command: {' '.join(spawn_cmd[:4])}...\")\n        result = subprocess.run(spawn_cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=30)\n        \n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            print(\"   ✅ Sub-agent spawn command accepted\")\n            spawn_data = json.loads(result.stdout)\n            print(f\"   Status: {spawn_data.get('status', 'unknown')}\")\n            print(f\"   Child Session Key: {spawn_data.get('childSessionKey', 'unknown')}\")\n            print(f\"   Run ID: {spawn_data.get('runId', 'unknown')}\")\n            \n            # Check if it's actually a sub-agent or something else\n            if \"subagent\" in spawn_data.get('childSessionKey', ''):\n                print(\"   ✅ Confirmed: Spawning creates a sub-agent session\")\n            else:\n                print(\"   ⚠️ Warning: Session key doesn't contain 'subagent'\")\n                \n        else:\n            print(f\"   ❌ Sub-agent spawn failed: {result.stderr}\")\n            \n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n        print(\"   ⚠️ Command timed out - may be running in background\")\n    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n        print(f\"   ❌ Failed to parse response: {e}\")\n        print(f\"   Raw output: {result.stdout[:200]}...\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"   ❌ Unexpected error: {e}\")\n    \n    print(\"\\n3. Checking tool permissions...\")\n    \n    # Check what tools are available\n    tools_to_check = [\"sessions_spawn\", \"subagents\", \"exec\", \"read\"]\n    \n    for tool in tools_to_check:\n        # Try to see if we can use the tool by checking help\n        help_cmd = [\"openclaw\", \"help\", tool] if tool != \"sessions_spawn\" else [\"openclaw\", \"sessions\", \"spawn\", \"--help\"]\n        \n        try:\n            result = subprocess.run(help_cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10)\n            if result.returncode == 0:\n                print(f\"   ✅ Tool '{tool}' is available\")\n            else:\n                print(f\"   ⚠️ Tool '{tool}' help not accessible: {result.returncode}\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"   ❌ Error checking tool '{tool}': {e}\")\n    \n    print(\"\\n=== Test Complete ===\")\n    print(\"\\nConclusion: This test shows what a sub-agent CAN do from within OpenClaw.\")\n    print(\"The real question is whether the long-prompt-orchestrator skill is\")\n    print(\"actually using these capabilities or just simulating them.\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    test_subagent_spawn_capability()"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":371,"output":1090,"cacheRead":57984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773090565657}}
