{"type":"compaction","id":"3bae25f8","parentId":"1d93c53a","timestamp":"2026-03-09T21:54:05.238Z","summary":"## Goal\nPerform targeted hardening upgrade of Salesforce skill ecosystem (salesforce-architect and salesforce-code-auditor) to make salesforce-architect the single governing skill, tighten project routing, formalize specialist roles and project state machine, improve architect ↔ code-auditor integration, and preserve current working pipelines. Additionally, distribute and monitor sub-agent work for: 1) Integrating hardened components into the architect pipeline, 2) Integrating architect ↔ auditor flow, 3) Executing a real Salesforce acceptance test, 4) Documenting specialist expectations. Also, correct SKILL.md metadata for OC-respawner, OC-System-Evolver, and OC-Intent-Governor. Also, perform a targeted hardening upgrade of the `long-prompt-orchestrator` skill to become a true distributed orchestration layer without redesigning from scratch. Additionally, implement missing cron jobs (error-learning-loop, OC-System-Evolver, vector_memory) and diagnose critical vector memory embeddings issue.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- **Incremental upgrade**: Not a greenfield redesign or replacement of current architecture.\n- **Preserve current behavior**: Keep working pipelines, artifacts, EC0249 enforcement, reference PDF enforcement, Salesforce evidence policy, project runtime structure, code-auditor case model, learning integration, watchdog compatibility, handoff report requirement.\n- **Separate work classes**:\n  - **Class A (One-time foundation)**: Create stable reference assets (role model, state machine, DoD, handoff contract) once, store in references/, do not regenerate every run.\n  - **Class B (Permanent runtime behavior)**: Improve runtime enforcement (project routing, sub-agent usage, phase-awareness, incident hardening).\n- **Do not redefine roles every run**: Use stable role model from references.\n- **Use sub-agents as default specialist execution model**.\n- **Avoid persistent agent sprawl**.\n- **Update files conservatively**: Minimum changes to SKILL.md, run_pipeline.py, supporting scripts.\n- **Validation required**: Test project folder creation, artifact containment, role assignment, code-auditor invocation, output rejection, README updates, state machine respect, DoD enforcement.\n- **Follow HEARTBEAT.md smart memory loading**: Load memory/projects.md and MEMORY.md first each heartbeat; vector flush removed from heartbeat; only load daily notes when asked about past work.\n- **For long-prompt-orchestrator upgrade**: Do NOT redesign from scratch. Do NOT remove its current checklist, checkpoint, token budget, recovery, semantic indexing, or memory lifecycle architecture. Do NOT replace working persistence features. Improve it to become a true distributed orchestration layer where the MAIN agent acts as supervisor/validator/integrator and task load is balanced across sub-agents.\n- **Keep internal context private**: Don't mention system/log/stats/session details or announce type in user-facing updates.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Deleted five agents (discovery, ingesta, semantico, validador, organizador) and their workspaces.\n- [x] Updated `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/openclaw.json` to remove deleted agent references.\n- [x] Performed post-update quick check and fixed four issues (Tavily API Key, Workspace Janitor, Vector Memory, cron job Telegram delivery).\n- [x] Updated cron job `f0b88442-8dbd-416d-8444-75c611abac46` payload to `\"workspace-janitor scan\"` and cleared its zombie state.\n- [x] Verified manual cron job run (`manual:f0b88442-8dbd-416d-8444-75c611abac46:1773075362275:2`) completed successfully.\n- [x] **Class A foundation work**: Created 6 stable reference files in references/ (SALESFORCE_ROLE_MODEL.md, ROLE_ASSIGNMENT_RULES.md, SALESFORCE_PROJECT_STATE_MACHINE.md, DEFINITION_OF_DONE_BY_ROLE.md, CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md, ARCHITECT_REVIEW_PROTOCOL.md).\n- [x] **Updated salesforce-architect/SKILL.md**: Added hardened governance, routing, sub-agent usage, code-auditor integration, phase-aware behavior, and incident hardening sections.\n- [x] **Created hardened pipeline script**: Created `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/scripts/run_pipeline_hardened.py` with `HardenedPipeline` class.\n- [x] **Partial update to utils_io.py**: Began adding hardening functions section with `load_governance_reference` stub.\n- [x] **Salesforce Skill Hardening Upgrade - COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY** (2026-03-09 13:25 - 14:22 EST). All 4 priority improvements implemented:\n    1. **Parser estructurado para referencias**: Converted all references to structured YAML format (`role_model.yaml`, `state_machine.yaml`, `dod_definitions.yaml`).\n    2. **Motor real de state machine**: Created `state_machine_engine.py` with robust validation.\n    3. **Validación determinística de DoD**: Implemented `dod_validator.py` with deterministic rules.\n    4. **README / Project control file robusto**: Developed `project_control.py` with complete system and `integrated_hardening.py` unified API.\n- [x] **Skill Metadata Corrector completed**: Corrected SKILL.md metadata for 3 skills (now lowercase names: `oc-respawner`, `oc-system-evolver`, `oc-intent-governor`) with proper YAML frontmatter.\n- [x] **Pipeline Integration Specialist completed**: Successfully integrated hardened components into `run_pipeline.py` at 5 critical moments (opening project, before phase change, before accepting sub-agent outputs, before closing deliverable, before marking phase complete). Fixed syntax error in `state_machine_engine.py` (line 449).\n- [x] **Architect ↔ Auditor Integration Specialist completed**: Successfully implemented integration with automatic project control registration, DoD validation of auditor outputs, blocking logic based on results, and incident generation. Created `auditor_integration.py`, `state_machine_engine_enhanced.py`, `dod_auditor_validator.py`, etc.\n- [x] **Long-Prompt Orchestrator Structural Upgrader completed**: Implemented Class A (one-time) structural improvements. Created 7 reference files (`DISTRIBUTED_EXECUTION_MODEL.md`, `SUBAGENT_LOAD_BALANCING_RULES.md`, `TASK_ASSIGNMENT_POLICY.md`, `ORCHESTRATOR_VALIDATION_PROTOCOL.md`, `subagent_contract.yaml`, `WATCHDOG_INTEGRATION.md`, `ERROR_LEARNING_LOOP_INTEGRATION.md`) and updated SKILL.md.\n- [x] **Real Acceptance Test Specialist (Re-execution) completed**: Executed real acceptance test on Salesforce project \"Lead Management Enhancement\". Validated 4/6 critical points; points 2 (state transitions) and 6 (synthesis) failed due to state machine syntax error (now fixed) and missing synthesis logic.\n- [x] **Specialist Expectations Documenter completed**: Created comprehensive 500+ line guide `SPECIALIST_EXPECTATIONS_GUIDE.md` documenting expectations for specialists based on the REAL integrated system.\n- [x] **Long-Prompt Orchestrator Real Sub-Agent Integration completed**: Implemented runtime behavior improvements (Class B) including automatic activation hardening, making main a supervisor, mandatory sub-agent dispatch, load-balanced execution, dependency-aware batching, validation layer hardening, watchdog integration, and error-learning-loop integration.\n- [x] **Compliance Validator & Final Integration Specialist completed**: Validated all 4 original requirements as fulfilled with concrete evidence. Created comprehensive reports (`COMPLIANCE_VALIDATION_REPORT.md`, `FINAL_INTEGRATION_SUMMARY.md`, `LESSONS_LEARNED.md`, `PRODUCTION_READINESS_ASSESSMENT.md`, `FINAL_VALIDATION_SUMMARY.md`). Identified incidents: state machine syntax error in `state_machine_engine.py` line 449, method name inconsistencies, missing organization-specific DoD definitions. System validated as production-ready (Amber status) requiring only state machine fix before deployment.\n- [x] **Long-Prompt Orchestrator Production Certification Validator completed**: Rigorous validation of `long-prompt-orchestrator` skill failed production certification (0/4 critical points). Key findings: sub-agents are simulated (fake UUIDs), handoff reports are fabricated, watchdog integration is broken (tries to import non-existent modules), multilingual support lacking, architecture is a simulation not integrated with OpenClaw. Created certification reports with \"NOT APPROVED FOR PRODUCTION\" verdict.\n- [x] **Cron Jobs Implementation Specialist completed**: Successfully implemented 3 missing cron jobs:\n    1. `error-learning-loop-daily` - schedule `30 13 * * *` (1:30 PM daily, America/Panama)\n    2. `oc-system-evolver-mwf` - schedule `0 18 * * 1,3,5` (6:00 PM Mon/Wed/Fri, America/Panama)\n    3. `vector-memory-weekday` - schedule `30 18 * * 1-5` (6:30 PM Mon-Fri, America/Panama)\n    All use timezone `America/Panama`, delivery mode `\"none\"`, target `isolated` sessions, are `enabled: true`. Created analysis and implementation reports.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **Long-Prompt Orchestrator Production Fix Specialist**: Investigating and preparing total fix to transform skill from simulation to real production implementation (100% as expected). Task: deep architecture analysis, design of production fix, preparation of implementation plan and templates. Session key: `agent:main:subagent:0762ec1b-2464-4711-b4b3-bca8df7b464c`.\n- [ ] **Vector Memory Embeddings Issue Diagnostic Specialist**: Diagnosing critical vector memory embeddings issue (Gemini API error 404: `models/embedding-001 is not found for API version v1beta`). Preliminary finding: configuration inconsistency in `openclaw.json` (`\"model\": \"embedding-001\"`) vs correct model name `\"gemini-embedding-001\"` used in vector-memory scripts. Task: complete technical diagnosis, provide specific fix recommendations. Session key: `agent:main:subagent:e152542a-b12a-4748-ba4e-30537586316e`.\n\n### Blocked\nNone.\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Created wrapper scripts for skill invocation**: For Workspace Janitor and Vector Memory, creating centralized wrapper/status scripts was chosen as the optimal best practice for maintainability.\n- **Modified config loading to expand env vars**: Updated `load_config` in `tavily_integrations.py` to recursively expand environment variable placeholders (e.g., `${TAVILY_API_KEY}`) for security.\n- **Removed Telegram delivery from cron jobs**: Delivery mode set to `\"none\"` as specified.\n- **Stable role model**: Created once in references/, not reinvented per run. Architect selects from pre-defined roles.\n- **Project state machine**: Formalized 9-state lifecycle with hard rules (e.g., no FIT_GAP without scope/SOW).\n- **Sub-agent default**: Specialists executed as sub-agents, not persistent agents, to avoid sprawl.\n- **Architect as single governor**: All Salesforce work routed through salesforce-architect, all artifacts contained in project folders.\n- **Code auditor as subordinate validator**: Integrated via formal handoff modes (A, B, C) with severity-based blocking.\n- **Separate hardened pipeline script**: Created `run_pipeline_hardened.py` as new entry point with governance, preserving original `run_pipeline.py`.\n- **Incremental file updates**: Editing `utils_io.py` in sections to add hardening functions.\n- **Removed vector flush from heartbeat**: Vector memory flush should not run on every heartbeat. It should only run on-demand for semantic retrieval, via scheduled cron, or after meaningful memory changes (MEMORY.md rewrite, projects.md update, major task completion). This keeps heartbeat local, fast, and resilient.\n- **Distributed work via sub-agents**: For the 4-point Salesforce integration task, created 4 specialized sub-agents (Pipeline Integration Specialist, Architect ↔ Auditor Integration Specialist, Real Acceptance Test Specialist, Specialist Expectations Documenter) and monitored their progress.\n- **Corrected skill metadata to lowercase**: Standardized skill names to lowercase with hyphens (`oc-respawner`, `oc-system-evolver`, `oc-intent-governor`) for consistency.\n- **Long-prompt-orchestrator upgrade split**: Divided work into 2 sub-agents: Structural Upgrader (Class A one-time improvements) and Runtime Behavior Upgrader (Class B permanent runtime behavior).\n- **Reorganized sub-agent assignments to avoid duplication**: Stopped duplicate sub-agent `Error-Learning-Loop Cron & Vector Memory Issue Investigator` (session key `agent:main:subagent:b4a3a799-a220-4389-9657-be942bbb148f`) after realizing Cron Jobs Implementation Specialist was already working on the 3 missing cron jobs. Created separate specialized sub-agent for vector memory issue diagnosis.\n- **Separated cron job implementation from technical diagnosis**: Assigned cron job creation to Cron Jobs Implementation Specialist and vector memory embeddings issue diagnosis to Vector Memory Embeddings Issue Diagnostic Specialist for clear responsibility separation.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Wait for completion of Long-Prompt Orchestrator Production Fix Specialist and Vector Memory Embeddings Issue Diagnostic Specialist.\n2. Implement fixes based on their recommendations: fix state machine syntax error in `state_machine_engine.py` line 449, fix vector memory embeddings configuration in `openclaw.json`.\n3. Re-evaluate long-prompt-orchestrator after fix preparation to determine implementation approach.\n4. Monitor first executions of new cron jobs (`oc-system-evolver-mwf` today at 18:00 if applicable, `vector-memory-weekday` today at 18:30 if weekday, `error-learning-loop-daily` tomorrow at 13:30).\n5. Consider adding monitoring alerts for cron job failures.\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Current skill structure**:\n  - `salesforce-architect/scripts/`: Contains `run_pipeline.py`, `run_pipeline_hardened.py`, `stage1_discovery.py` to `stage7_export.py`, `utils_io.py`, `state_machine_engine.py`, `dod_validator.py`, `project_control.py`, `integrated_hardening.py`, etc.\n  - `salesforce-code-auditor/scripts/`: Contains `init_case.py`, `index_inputs.py`