.md`, `subagent_contract.yaml`, `WATCHDOG_INTEGRATION.md`, `ERROR_LEARNING_LOOP_INTEGRATION.md`.\n- **Cron jobs active suite (5 total)**:\n    1. `workspace-janitor-daily` - 13:00 Lunes-Viernes\n    2. `Twice-Weekly MEMORY.md Auto-Curation` - 14:00 Lunes y Viernes\n    3. `error-learning-loop-daily` - 13:30 Diario\n    4. `oc-system-evolver-mwf` - 18:00 Lunes/Miércoles/Viernes\n    5. `vector-memory-weekday` - 18:30 Lunes-Viernes\n- **Long-prompt-orchestrator certification status**: FAILED production certification. It is a simulation prototype (fake UUIDs, fabricated handoff reports, broken watchdog integration) not integrated with OpenClaw runtime.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- **Removed vector flush from heartbeat**: Vector memory flush should not run on every heartbeat. It should only run on-demand for semantic retrieval, via scheduled cron, or after meaningful memory changes (MEMORY.md rewrite, projects.md update, major task completion). This keeps heartbeat local, fast, and resilient.\n- **Distributed Salesforce integration work to 4 sub-agents**: Pipeline Integration Specialist, Architect ↔ Auditor Integration Specialist, Real Acceptance Test Specialist, Specialist Expectations Documenter (to run after integration).\n- **Corrected skill metadata for 3 skills**: Updated SKILL.md files for OC-respawner, OC-System-Evolver, OC-Intent-Governor to have proper YAML frontmatter with lowercase names.\n- **Split long\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- **Use subagent for diagnostics**: A subagent was tasked with diagnosing vector memory embeddings issues, identifying a configuration mismatch as the root cause.\n- **Fix configuration files**: Decision to update `openclaw.json` and `add_google_provider.py` to correct the model name from `\"embedding-001\"` to `\"gemini-embedding-001\"`.\n\n## Open TODOs\n1. Update `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` - Change `\"embedding-001\"` to `\"gemini-embedding-001\"` in `agents.defaults