{"type":"message","id":"945a637e","parentId":"35195923","timestamp":"2026-03-09T22:04:03.969Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_lKu1FoQ8z8w3o0jOViHOPz8e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-rw-rw-r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  1231 Mar  5 16:32 HANDOFF_REPORT.md\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  6603 Mar  9 15:11 RUNTIME_UPGRADE_SUMMARY.md\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 openclaw openclaw 11582 Mar  9 16:54 SKILL.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"-rw-rw-r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  1231 Mar  5 16:32 HANDOFF_REPORT.md\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 openclaw openclaw  6603 Mar  9 15:11 RUNTIME_UPGRADE_SUMMARY.md\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 openclaw openclaw 11582 Mar  9 16:54 SKILL.md","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773093843961}}
{"type":"message","id":"c5fdd817","parentId":"945a637e","timestamp":"2026-03-09T22:04:08.311Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ClSFJxjKU2gnF43EA2hnxHXI","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/long-prompt-orchestrator/SKILL.md","limit":150}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":143,"output":84,"cacheRead":68224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68451,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773093843967}}
{"type":"message","id":"12785aaf","parentId":"c5fdd817","timestamp":"2026-03-09T22:04:08.334Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ClSFJxjKU2gnF43EA2hnxHXI","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: long-prompt-orchestrator\ndescription: A production-ready Long Prompt Planner that automatically decomposes overly long/complex tasks into structured plans for main agent execution. Generates task DAGs with dependencies, resource estimates, and execution recommendations. Does NOT execute tasks or spawn sub-agents.\ncategory: planning\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"python\", \"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: false\n---\n\n# long-prompt-orchestrator\n\n## Purpose\nAutomatically detect overly long prompts or complex tasks, decompose them into smaller dependent tasks, and generate structured execution plans for the main agent. The skill provides comprehensive planning including task dependencies, resource estimates, skill recommendations, and execution strategies. Main agent uses these plans to spawn and coordinate sub-agents.\n\n## CORRECTED ARCHITECTURE (IMPORTANT)\n**This skill ONLY generates plans. It does NOT execute tasks or spawn sub-agents.**\n\n### Role Clarification:\n- ✅ **Skill Responsibility**: Planning, decomposition, resource estimation, dependency analysis\n- ✅ **Main Agent Responsibility**: Spawning sub-agents, execution coordination, validation, synthesis\n- ❌ **Skill DOES NOT**: Execute tasks, spawn sub-agents, track execution state, validate outputs\n\n### Key Changes:\n1. **Removed all spawning code** - Skill cannot spawn sub-agents from Python\n2. **Added plan generation** - Outputs structured JSON plans for main agent\n3. **Enhanced task analysis** - Better recommendations for skill/model selection\n4. **Updated documentation** - Clear separation of responsibilities\n\n## When to Use\n- When the main agent receives a prompt that is too long (estimated tokens > 4000)\n- When a task appears complex: expected steps > 5, multi‑file outputs, multi‑agent operations, long tool execution sequences\n- When you need to split a large task into manageable sub‑tasks with dependencies\n- When you need a structured execution plan for distributed workflow\n\n## When NOT to Use\n- For simple, short prompts (estimated tokens < 1000)\n- For tasks that require atomic, non‑decomposable execution\n- When the user explicitly wants a single‑step response\n- When the task is already being handled by another planning/orchestration skill\n- **When you need task execution** (use main agent with generated plan instead)\n\n## Inputs\n- Original prompt (string)\n- Optional configuration (MAX_PROMPT_TOKENS, MAX_MINI_TASKS, etc.)\n- Optional checkpoint/task_id for recovery\n\n## Outputs\n- **Structured Plan** (JSON format) containing:\n  - Task definitions with objectives, dependencies, acceptance criteria\n  - Resource estimates (tokens, runtime)\n  - Skill and model recommendations\n  - Dependency graph and execution order\n  - Validation protocol\n  - Distributed execution recommendations\n- Plan file saved to `<workspace>/.taskboards/<plan_id>.json`\n- Human-readable summary (optional)\n\n## Step-by-step Instructions\n\n### Step 0 — Setup\nEnsure the skill directory exists and scripts are executable. Create `.taskboards/` directory if missing.\n\n### Step 1 — Detection\nUse `scripts/decompose.py` to analyze the original prompt:\n- Estimate token count (rough heuristic)\n- Detect complexity heuristics (steps >5, multi‑file outputs, etc.)\n- If prompt is within limits, return simple plan with single task\n\n### Step 2 — Decomposition\nIf decomposition required:\n- Generate a DAG of mini‑tasks each with:\n  - `id`, `objective`, `description`\n  - `inputs`, `outputs`\n  - `dependencies` (list of task ids)\n  - `acceptance_criteria`\n  - `estimated_tokens`, `estimated_runtime`\n  - `complexity_score`\n  - `requires_subagent` (boolean)\n  - `recommended_skill`, `recommended_model` (optional)\n- Ensure total mini‑tasks ≤ MAX_MINI_TASKS (default 20)\n\n### Step 3 — Plan Generation\nUse `scripts/plan_generator.py` to create structured plan:\n- Generate unique `plan_id`\n- Build dependency graph with topological order\n- Calculate resource allocation recommendations\n- Generate validation protocol\n- Add distributed execution recommendations (if using distributed_orchestrate)\n\n### Step 4 — Output\nSave plan to JSON file and return to main agent:\n- Plan saved as `<workspace>/.taskboards/<plan_id>.json`\n- Human-readable summary available (optional)\n- Main agent parses plan and executes accordingly\n\n## Main Agent Integration\n\n### How Main Agent Uses This Skill:\n1. **Invoke skill** with long/complex prompt\n2. **Receive plan** in JSON format\n3. **Parse and validate** plan structure\n4. **Spawn sub-agents** according to plan recommendations\n5. **Coordinate execution** using dependency graph\n6. **Validate outputs** using acceptance criteria\n7. **Synthesize final result**\n\n### Example Main Agent Workflow:\n```python\n# Main agent detects long prompt\nif should_invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator(prompt):\n    # Invoke skill to get plan\n    plan = invoke_long_prompt_orchestrator_skill(prompt)\n    \n    # Validate plan\n    if validate_plan(plan):\n        # Execute plan\n        executor = PlanExecutor(plan)\n        result = executor.execute_plan()\n        \n        # Synthesize final result\n        final_output = synthesize_result(plan, result)\n        return final_output\n```\n\n## File Layout\n```\nskills/long-prompt-orchestrator/\n  SKILL.md                           (this file)\n  scripts/\n    orchestrate.py                   (main orchestration - generates plans)\n    decompose.py                     (detect & decompose prompts)\n    plan_generator.py                (generate structured plans)\n    todo.py                          (persistent checklist - for reference)\n    token_budget.py                  (token management - for reference)\n    validate.py                      (validation logic - for reference)\n    recovery.py                      (recovery logic - for reference)\n    learning_emit.py                 (incident emission)\n    context_monitor.py               (monitor context size)\n    context_archive.py               (archive reasoning artifacts)\n    semantic_index_builder.py        (build semantic index of artifacts)\n    semantic_context_search.py       (search semantic index)\n    task_state_manager.py            (persist task state across sessions)\n    session_manager.py               (session lifecycle management)\n    memory_router.py                 (dynamic agent memory routing)\n    context_cleanup.py               (orchestrate context cleanup)\n    distributed_orchestrate.py       (enhanced plans with distribution recommendations)\n  references/\n\n[157 more lines in file. Use offset=151 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773093848323}}
