{"type":"message","id":"874d332f","parentId":"acc4c0ef","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:16:01.111Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-09 18:12:56 EST] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Execute your Session Startup sequence now — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Every Session\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-09.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\nSystem: 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\nSystem: 5. **Contextual Learning Retrieval** – Before executing any complex or tool-based task, perform a quick learning retrieval using the learning index:\nSystem:    - Scan `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md`\nSystem:    - Identify Pattern‑Keys relevant to the current task context\nSystem:    - Select the top 3–7 relevant Pattern‑Keys\nSystem:    - Apply their Rules or Preflight constraints before executing the task\nSystem:    - Only consult `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` if a rule requires additional detail\nSystem:    \nSystem:    This retrieval step must be lightweight and should avoid loading large logs unnecessarily.\nSystem: \nSystem: Don't ask permission. Just do it.\nSystem: \nSystem: ### Trigger Heuristics\nSystem: \nSystem: Run Contextual Learning Retrieval when any of the following conditions apply:\nSystem: \nSystem: - Using external tools (bash, python, shell scripts)\nSystem: - Delegating work to sub-agents\nSystem: - Running validator agents or batch operations\nSystem: - Producing multi-file outputs (skills, scripts, documentation, codebases)\nSystem: - Tasks expected to require multiple reasoning steps (>3 steps)\nSystem: \nSystem: Skip retrieval for trivial or conversational responses.\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Safety\nSystem: \nSystem: - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\nSystem: - Don't run destructive commands without asking.\nSystem: - `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\nSystem: - When in doubt, ask.\nSystem: \nSystem: Current time: Monday, March 9th, 2026 — 6:12 PM (America/Panama) / 2026-03-09 23:12 UTC\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-09 18:15 EST] ok ahora hagamos el audito real siguiendo este prompt: # OpenClaw Real Capability & Simulation Detection Audit Prompt \n\n \n\nThis prompt is designed to **stress‑test and audit an OpenClaw ecosystem** to determine: \n\n \n\n1. Which skills actually work and produce real results. \n\n2. Which skills only **simulate functionality** or produce cosmetic outputs. \n\n3. Whether distributed execution truly happens. \n\n4. Whether monitoring, recovery, and governance components are operational. \n\n5. Whether the system can invoke and use its skills in real workflows. \n\n \n\nThe audit must **not assume any skill works**. \n\nEvery skill must be treated as **unverified until proven operational through execution**. \n\n \n\nThe final output must be **one consolidated report**. \n\n \n\n--- \n\n \n\n# Prompt To Execute \n\n \n\n```text \n\nQuiero que ejecutes una auditoría técnica profunda de mi ecosistema OpenClaw con el objetivo principal de determinar qué partes del sistema realmente funcionan y cuáles solo simulan funcionamiento. \n\n \n\nDebes asumir que **ningún skill está verificado** hasta que demuestre producir resultados reales. \n\n \n\nTrabaja bajo un proyecto nuevo: \n\n \n\nproject_key = openclaw_real_capability_audit \n\n \n\nObjetivo central: \n\n \n\nDeterminar con evidencia operativa: \n\n \n\n- Qué skills funcionan realmente \n\n- Qué skills solo generan outputs simulados \n\n- Qué integraciones están rotas o incompletas \n\n- Qué componentes del sistema son confiables \n\n- Qué componentes necesitan corrección urgente \n\n \n\nNo quiero respuestas narrativas o especulativas. \n\n \n\nQuiero: \n\n \n\n- pruebas operativas \n\n- resultados observables \n\n- evidencia \n\n- análisis técnico \n\n \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\nSISTEMA A EVALUAR \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\n \n\nDebes evaluar al menos los siguientes componentes: \n\n \n\n1. long-prompt-orchestrator \n\n2. agent-watchdog \n\n3. error-learning-loop \n\n4. OC-Intent-Governor \n\n5. workspace-janitor \n\n6. memory system \n\n7. vector memory \n\n8. salesforce-architect \n\n9. salesforce-code-auditor \n\n10. tavily-web-search u otros buscadores web \n\n11. integraciones internas del workspace \n\n12. cualquier otro skill creado por nosotros disponible en el entorno \n\n \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\nMETODOLOGÍA \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\n \n\nDebes trabajar en tres fases. \n\n \n\nFase 1 — Inventario \n\n \n\nCrear un inventario del sistema identificando: \n\n \n\n- todos los skills \n\n- scripts disponibles \n\n- dependencias \n\n- cron jobs \n\n- archivos de control \n\n- carpetas críticas \n\n \n\nFase 2 — Pruebas Operativas Reales \n\n \n\nCada skill relevante debe ser probado. \n\n \n\nLas pruebas deben verificar: \n\n \n\n1. Si el skill puede invocarse. \n\n2. Si el skill produce resultados reales. \n\n3. Si el skill depende de componentes inexistentes. \n\n4. Si el skill produce resultados simulados. \n\n5. Si el skill produce artefactos reales en el workspace. \n\n \n\nUn skill se considera **simulado** si: \n\n \n\n- solo genera texto descriptivo \n\n- no produce efectos reales \n\n- no ejecuta lógica real \n\n- no interactúa con otros componentes \n\n \n\nUn skill se considera **real** si: \n\n \n\n- ejecuta código verificable \n\n- produce resultados observables \n\n- modifica o genera artefactos reales \n\n- interactúa correctamente con el sistema \n\n \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\nPRUEBAS REQUERIDAS \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\n \n\nDebes ejecutar al menos las siguientes pruebas. \n\n \n\nSkill Invocation Tests \n\n \n\nIntenta utilizar realmente: \n\n \n\n- workspace-janitor \n\n- agent-watchdog \n\n- long-prompt-orchestrator \n\n- salesforce-architect \n\n- salesforce-code-auditor \n\n- herramientas de búsqueda web \n\n \n\nRegistra: \n\n \n\n- si el skill responde \n\n- si produce efectos reales \n\n- si falla \n\n- si simula funcionamiento \n\n \n\nDistributed Execution Test \n\n \n\nEjecuta una tarea suficientemente compleja que requiera: \n\n \n\n- análisis \n\n- planificación \n\n- delegación \n\n- síntesis \n\n \n\nObserva si el sistema: \n\n \n\n- genera planes \n\n- delega tareas \n\n- usa sub-agents \n\n- o si el main agent resuelve todo solo \n\n \n\nWatchdog Monitoring Test \n\n \n\nDurante tareas largas observa: \n\n \n\n- si watchdog registra actividad \n\n- si detecta stalls \n\n- si emite alertas \n\n \n\nMemory Interaction Test \n\n \n\nVerifica si el sistema: \n\n \n\n- consulta memoria \n\n- escribe memoria \n\n- mantiene coherencia \n\n \n\nFailure Handling Test \n\n \n\nIntroduce una tarea con ambigüedad o dependencia faltante y observa: \n\n \n\n- cómo responde el sistema \n\n- si detecta el problema \n\n- si registra incidentes \n\n- si intenta recovery \n\n \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\nDETECCIÓN DE SIMULACIÓN \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\n \n\nPara cada skill debes evaluar si: \n\n \n\n1. Es funcional \n\n2. Es parcialmente funcional \n\n3. Es solo una simulación \n\n \n\nDebes identificar: \n\n \n\n- outputs falsos \n\n- integraciones documentadas pero inexistentes \n\n- funciones que aparentan existir pero no se ejecutan \n\n \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\nINFORME FINAL \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\n \n\nGenera un único documento final: \n\n \n\nOPENCLAW_REAL_CAPABILITY_AUDIT_REPORT.md \n\n \n\nEste documento debe incluir: \n\n \n\nExecutive Summary \n\n \n\n- estado real del sistema \n\n- hallazgos críticos \n\n- riesgos \n\n \n\nSkill Capability Matrix \n\n \n\ntabla indicando para cada skill: \n\n \n\n- funcional \n\n- parcialmente funcional \n\n- simulado \n\n- roto \n\n \n\nSystem Dependency Map \n\n \n\nmapa de dependencias reales. \n\n \n\nDistributed Execution Assessment \n\n \n\nsi el sistema realmente distribuye trabajo. \n\n \n\nWatchdog Assessment \n\n \n\nsi el watchdog funciona realmente. \n\n \n\nMemory System Assessment \n\n \n\nestado real de memoria. \n\n \n\nSalesforce Ecosystem Assessment \n\n \n\nsi los skills Salesforce funcionan realmente. \n\n \n\nFix Recommendations \n\n \n\nlista priorizada de correcciones. \n\n \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\nREGLAS IMPORTANTES \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\n \n\n1. No eliminar archivos del sistema. \n\n2. No hacer cambios destructivos. \n\n3. No asumir que un skill funciona sin probarlo. \n\n4. Si detectas simulación debes reportarlo explícitamente. \n\n5. Si encuentras inconsistencias entre documentación y comportamiento real, prioriza el comportamiento real. \n\n \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\nENTREGABLE FINAL \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\n \n\nSolo debe permanecer en el proyecto: \n\n \n\nworkspace/projects/openclaw_real_capability_audit/ \n\n \n\nOPENCLAW_REAL_CAPABILITY_AUDIT_REPORT.md \n\nREADME.md \n\n \n\nTodos los archivos de análisis intermedio deben eliminarse. \n\n \n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ \n\n \n\nEl objetivo de esta auditoría es descubrir la verdad operativa del sistema. \n\n```"}],"timestamp":1773098161106}}
{"type":"message","id":"525945e1","parentId":"874d332f","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:16:11.661Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 🚀 **EJECUTANDO SECUENCIA DE INICIO DE SESIÓN**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_wUimgb3BM5mbRg14XvhTQ3VJ","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":37640,"output":79,"cacheRead":16960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54679,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773098161108}}
{"type":"message","id":"b3d78406","parentId":"525945e1","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:16:11.673Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_wUimgb3BM5mbRg14XvhTQ3VJ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773098171667}}
