{"type":"message","id":"7851308a","parentId":"6c0af482","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:16:30.779Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Pel7YzTCTC5e4pNTLLR8QM7K","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# INDEX.md – Lightweight Retrieval Index\n\n*Generated by error‑learning‑loop. Updated: 2026-03-09 15:57:10*\n\n---\n\n## tools\n\n- Pattern-Key: model|ERROR|deepseek_reasoner|missing_field|reasoning_content_required\n  Tags: deepseek, model, model-error, reasoning\n  Rule: For long multi‑step tasks, avoid DeepSeek reasoning mode; use standard completion mode or a different model.\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: model|STALL|deepseek-reasoner|no_response|runtime_stuck\n  Tags: deepseek-reasoner, model, response, runtime, stall, stuck\n  Rule: Register long‑running sub‑agents with agent‑watchdog; configure stall timeout (recommended: 120 seconds).\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: model|STALL|gpt-4|no_response|runtime_stuck\n  Tags: gpt-4, model, response, runtime, stall, stuck\n  Rule: Implement multi‑level recovery: Level 1 (nudge), Level 2 (cancel & restart), Level 3 (relaunch agent).\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n\n## planning\n\n- Pattern-Key: planning|OVERLOAD|decompose|prompt_too_long|required\n  Tags: decompose, long, overload, planning, prompt, too\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n\n## multi-agent\n\n- Pattern-Key: multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting\n  Tags: agents, deadlock, dependency_cycle, multi-agent, waiting\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: multi_agent|DEADLOCK|progress_starvation|agents_no_progress\n  Tags: agents, deadlock, multi-agent, progress, progress_starvation\n  Rule: Detect dependency cycles before execution; implement timeout per agent and deadlock resolution.\n  Promoted: AGENTS.md\n- Pattern-Key: multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced\n  Tags: handoff, multi-agent, report, subagent\n  Rule: Every sub‑agent must end its final response with a structured Handoff Report (Outcome + Incidents).\n  Promoted: AGENTS.md\n\n## validation\n\n- Pattern-Key: validation|FAILURE|validate|final_output|criteria_not_met|repair_failed\n  Tags: criteria, final, met, output, validate, validation\n  Rule: Implement adjustable validation thresholds and fallback repair strategies.\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: validation|FAILURE|validate|supervisor_orchestration|criteria_not_met\n  Tags: criteria, met, orchestration, supervisor, validate, validation\n- Pattern-Key: validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload\n  Tags: items, tool-failure, validation, validator\n  Rule: Never assign more than 5 items to a single validator agent. If more items need validation, spawn multiple validators each with a subset.\n  Promoted: AGENTS.md\n\n## other\n\n- Pattern-Key: checklist|FAILURE|todo|state_corrupt|rebuild_failed|manual_needed\n  Tags: checklist, corrupt, failed, rebuild, state, todo\n  Rule: Implement atomic writes and backup of checklist state; provide recovery scripts.\n- Pattern-Key: evidence|MISSING|salesforce_official|feature_unverified|blocked\n  Tags: blocked, evidence, feature, salesforce_official, unverified\n- Pattern-Key: fitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify|blocked\n  Tags: blocked, classify, fitgap, scope_missing\n  Rule: Validate input: require SOW document or provide default classification method.\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: handoff|INVALID|missing_report\n  Tags: handoff, invalid, missing_report\n- Pattern-Key: licensing|CONFLICT|feature_requires_license|not_available|alternate_needed\n  Tags: alternate, available, conflict, feature_requires_license, licensing, needed\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: memory|FAILURE|backup_creation|file_not_found|test_incident\n  Tags: backup_creation, file, found, incident, memory, test\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: recovery|FAILURE|recovery|resume|checkpoint_missing|cannot_continue\n  Tags: checkpoint, recovery, resume\n  Rule: Maintain checksum validation of checkpoint files; provide fallback recovery from logs.\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: security|FLS_MISSING|apex\n  Tags: apex, fls, security\n  Rule: Include FLS checks in Apex templates; validate generated code for security compliance.\n  Promoted: TOOLS.md\n- Pattern-Key: tokens|BUDGET|token_budget|input_overflow|truncate_required\n  Tags: budget, input, overflow, token_budget, tokens, truncate\n  Rule: Implement token counting per step and automatic truncation when near limit.\n\n---\n\n*Sections: tools, requirements, planning, multi-agent, validation, other*\n\n**Purpose**: Quick scanning of Pattern‑Keys, tags, rules, and promotion status.\nFor detailed analytics, see [REPORT.md](./REPORT.md)."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773098190776}}
{"type":"message","id":"94ff07c1","parentId":"7851308a","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:17:01.021Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 🎯 **CONTEXTUAL LEARNING RETRIEVAL APLICADO**\n\n### **Pattern‑Keys relevantes para esta auditoría:**\n1. **`multi_agent|DEADLOCK|progress_starvation|agents_no_progress`** - Detectar ciclos de dependencia\n2. **`validation|TOOL_FAILURE|openclaw_validator|timeout|excessive_workload`** - Límite de 5 items por validador\n3. **`multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced`** - Reportes de handoff obligatorios\n4. **`model|STALL|deepseek-reasoner|no_response|runtime_stuck`** - Registrar con watchdog tareas largas\n5. **`fitgap|FAILURE|scope_missing|cannot_classify|blocked`** - Validar inputs requeridos\n\n### **Reglas aplicables:**\n- ✅ **Distribuir trabajo**: Usar sub-agents para tareas especializadas\n- ✅ **Límite de validación**: ≤5 items por validador\n- ✅ **Reportes de handoff**: Obligatorios para todos los sub-agents\n- ✅ **Registro watchdog**: Para tareas >5 minutos\n- ✅ **Validación de inputs**: Verificar que todos los componentes existen\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 **AUDITORÍA TÉCNICA PROFUNDA - INICIANDO**\n\n### **📋 MI PLAN DE EJECUCIÓN:**\n\n#### **Fase 1: Configuración del proyecto**\n```bash\nmkdir -p /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/projects/openclaw_real_capability_audit\n```\n\n#### **Fase 2: Inventario del sistema**\n1. Listar todos los skills disponibles\n2. Identificar scripts y dependencias\n3. Verificar cron jobs activos\n4. Mapear carpetas críticas\n\n#### **Fase 3: Pruebas operativas REALES**\n- **Skill por skill**: Invocar y verificar funcionalidad real\n- **Validación**: ¿Produce efectos REALES o solo texto?\n- **Evidencia**: Archivos creados, modificaciones en filesystem\n- **Clasificación**: Funcional / Parcial / Simulado / Roto\n\n#### **Fase 4: Reporte consolidado**\n- **Matriz de capacidades**: Tabla con estado de cada skill\n- **Mapa de dependencias**: Componentes reales vs documentados\n- **Recomendaciones**: Correcciones priorizadas\n\n### **🎯 PRIMEROS PASOS INMEDIATOS:**\n\n#### **1. Crear proyecto de auditoría**\n```bash\nmkdir -p /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/projects/openclaw_real_capability_audit\n```\n\n#### **2. Guardar prompt de auditoría**\n```bash\ncat > /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/projects/openclaw_real_capability_audit/AUDIT_PROMPT.txt << 'EOF'\n[EL_PROMPT_COMPLETO]\nEOF\n```\n\n#### **3. Ejecutar inventario inicial**\n```bash\nfind /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills -type f -name \"SKILL.md\" | wc -l\n```\n\n### **🔍 MÉTODO DE VALIDACIÓN \"REAL vs SIMULADO\":**\n\n#### **Para cada skill probaré:**\n1. **Invocación**: ¿Se puede ejecutar el script principal?\n2. **Output**: ¿Es JSON/estructurado o solo texto descriptivo?\n3. **Efectos**: ¿Crea/modifica archivos REALES?\n4. **Interacciones**: ¿Llama a otros componentes REALES?\n5. **Errores**: ¿Falla con errores reales o \"simula\" éxito?\n\n### **📊 CRITERIOS DE CLASIFICACIÓN:**\n\n#### **✅ FUNCIONAL**: Ejecuta código, produce efectos reales, interactúa con sistema\n#### **⚠️ PARCIALMENTE FUNCIONAL**: Algunas funciones trabajan, otras simulan\n#### **❌ SIMULADO**: Solo genera texto descriptivo, sin efectos reales\n#### **💀 ROTO**: No se puede invocar, errores fatales\n\n### **🚀 EJECUCIÓN INMEDIATA:**\n\n**Procedo a crear el proyecto y comenzar la auditoría.**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fLqs8hrqx2G2yaADrr1975ZZ","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/projects/openclaw_real_capability_audit"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":1266,"output":1047,"cacheRead":57280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59593,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773098190778}}
