{"type":"message","id":"ef9388af","parentId":"4fdbeb94","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:57:37.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### **2. SKILL_REALITY_CRITERIA.md**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_IVvVLvrgRv3gVUzw2wP3ql1M","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/system_validation/SKILL_REALITY_CRITERIA.md","content":"# SKILL_REALITY_CRITERIA.md\n# Operational Reality Criteria for OpenClaw Skills\n# Last updated: 2026-03-09\n\n## PURPOSE\nDefine what counts as REAL vs SIMULATED functionality.\nEliminate ambiguity between documented capability and operational capability.\n\n## CRITICAL DISTINCTION: REAL vs SIMULATED\n\n### REAL FUNCTIONALITY (must demonstrate ALL):\n1. **Executable Code Path**: Script/function can be invoked and runs\n2. **Observable Effects**: Produces files, logs, state changes, or API calls\n3. **Usable Outputs**: Outputs can be consumed by other components or users\n4. **Integration Path**: Connects to other real components (not just documented)\n5. **Repeatable Behavior**: Works consistently across multiple invocations\n6. **Evidence Trail**: Leaves logs, artifacts, or observable runtime evidence\n\n### SIMULATED FUNCTIONALITY (any of these):\n1. **Descriptive Only**: Outputs describe what WOULD happen, not what DID happen\n2. **Placeholder Artifacts**: Files created but empty or containing placeholders\n3. **Fake IDs**: Generated UUIDs/session_ids without corresponding runtime objects\n4. **Documentation-Only Integration**: \"Can integrate with X\" but no actual integration\n5. **Manual Completion Required**: Human must \"fill in\" expected results\n6. **Architecture-Only**: Design/contract exists but no runtime implementation\n\n## SKILL-SPECIFIC REALITY CRITERIA\n\n### 1. LONG-PROMPT-ORCHESTRATOR\n**REAL (must demonstrate):**\n- Generates JSON plan from complex prompt\n- Plan contains executable instructions (not just abstract objectives)\n- Main agent can execute/delegate based on plan without manual translation\n- Tasks produce real artifacts when executed\n- Final synthesis based on real completed tasks\n\n**SIMULATED (if any):**\n- Plan contains only abstract task descriptions\n- Main agent must reinterpret plan to make it executable\n- No real task execution or artifact creation\n- \"Orchestration\" exists only in documentation\n\n### 2. AGENT-WATCHDOG\n**REAL (must demonstrate):**\n- Monitors real agent sessions or tasks\n- Creates observable monitoring logs/artifacts\n- Detects stalls or issues in real workflows\n- Triggers recovery actions when appropriate\n- Emits real incidents to error-learning-loop\n\n**SIMULATED (if any):**\n- Monitoring guides exist but no monitored objects\n- Recovery logic exists but never triggered\n- \"Integration ready\" but no real integration\n- Placeholder directories without actual monitoring\n\n### 3. SALESFORCE-CODE-AUDITOR\n**REAL (must demonstrate):**\n- Processes real Salesforce metadata (not placeholders)\n- Generates substantive technical findings\n- Creates usable audit reports\n- Outputs consumable by salesforce-architect\n- Real dependency graphs from real code\n\n**SIMULATED (if any):**\n- Processes only placeholder/empty inputs\n- Generates generic findings without technical substance\n- Reports created but empty or template-only\n- \"Works if user supplies real code later\"\n\n### 4. DISTRIBUTED EXECUTION (Cross-cutting)\n**REAL (must demonstrate):**\n- Main agent delegates tasks to sub-agents\n- Sub-agents produce real outputs\n- Handoff reports contain real completion evidence\n- Task dependencies are real, not just documented\n- Final synthesis based on real sub-agent outputs\n\n**SIMULATED (if any):**\n- Main agent does all work, sub-agents simulated\n- Fake handoff reports generated locally\n- UUIDs generated without corresponding runtime objects\n- \"Distributed\" exists only in architecture diagrams\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n\n### Minimum Evidence for FUNCTIONAL Classification:\n1. **Invocation Log**: Command executed and output captured\n2. **Artifact Creation**: File(s) created/modified with substantive content\n3. **Integration Proof**: Connection to another real component verified\n4. **Repeatability**: At least 2 successful invocations\n5. **Error Handling**: Basic failure cases handled appropriately\n\n### Minimum Evidence for PARTIAL Classification:\n1. **Some Real Functionality**: At least one real operational aspect\n2. **Clear Limitations**: Specific gaps documented\n3. **Not Misrepresented**: Not labeled as production-ready\n\n### Evidence that DOES NOT COUNT:\n1. Documentation changes alone\n2. Architectural designs/roadmaps\n3. Template files without runtime execution\n4. \"Works in theory\" statements\n5. Placeholder/Fake IDs\n\n## VALIDATION PROTOCOL\n\n### Step 1: Invocation Test\n- Execute skill with minimal valid inputs\n- Record success/failure\n- Capture outputs\n\n### Step 2: Output Substance Test\n- Inspect outputs for real content vs placeholders\n- Verify outputs are usable\n- Check for fake IDs or simulated artifacts\n\n### Step 3: Integration Test\n- Verify connections to dependent components\n- Test data flow between components\n- Confirm integration is real, not just documented\n\n### Step 4: Repeatability Test\n- Execute at least twice\n- Verify consistent behavior\n- Check for one-off artifacts vs repeatable results\n\n### Step 5: Failure Test (where safe)\n- Introduce controlled failure\n- Verify detection and handling\n- Check incident emission if applicable\n\n## PRODUCTION-READY THRESHOLD\n\nA skill is **PRODUCTION-READY** only if:\n1. Classified as FUNCTIONAL\n2. All critical integration paths verified\n3. Error handling tested and functional\n4. Performance acceptable for intended use\n5. Documentation matches actual behavior\n6. No known high-risk gaps\n\n## ANTI-SIMULATION RULES (Non-negotiable)\n\n1. **No success by documentation alone**\n2. **No success by architectural intent**  \n3. **No synthetic runtime evidence**\n4. **No \"works in theory\" acceptance**\n5. **No hidden manual completion**\n6. **No production label without certification evidence**\n\n## RECERTIFICATION SCHEDULE\n\n1. **High-priority skills**: Monthly operational verification\n2. **Medium-priority skills**: Quarterly verification  \n3. **Low-priority skills**: Biannual verification\n4. **After major changes**: Immediate re-verification\n5. **When simulation suspected**: Immediate deep audit"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":62873,"output":1426,"cacheRead":27776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92075,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773100602169}}
