{"type":"message","id":"5a934eba","parentId":"e7c4368d","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:58:29.118Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### **3. SKILL_CERTIFICATION_RULES.md**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_RWVH8YUv44Xb5IX4d5ubmc7d","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/system_validation/SKILL_CERTIFICATION_RULES.md","content":"# SKILL_CERTIFICATION_RULES.md\n# Certification Rules for OpenClaw Skill Production Readiness\n# Last updated: 2026-03-09\n\n## CERTIFICATION PURPOSE\nEstablish objective, repeatable criteria for determining when a skill is truly production-ready vs partially functional, simulated, or broken.\n\n## CERTIFICATION LEVELS\n\n### LEVEL 0: BROKEN\n- Invocation fails consistently\n- Critical dependencies missing\n- No usable outputs produced\n- Error handling absent for basic cases\n\n### LEVEL 1: SIMULATED\n- Outputs are descriptive only (what WOULD happen)\n- Fake IDs/UUIDs without runtime objects\n- Placeholder artifacts with no execution path\n- Integration exists only in documentation\n- \"Works if user supplies real data later\"\n\n### LEVEL 2: PARTIAL\n- Some real functionality exists\n- Clear, documented limitations\n- Not misrepresented as complete\n- May require manual steps or workarounds\n- Not suitable for production use without caveats\n\n### LEVEL 3: FUNCTIONAL (Development Ready)\n- All core functions work with real inputs\n- Produces usable outputs\n- Basic error handling present\n- Can be used for development/testing\n- Not yet proven for production workloads\n\n### LEVEL 4: PRODUCTION-READY\n- Meets all FUNCTIONAL criteria\n- All integration paths verified\n- Performance acceptable for production use\n- Comprehensive error handling\n- Documentation matches actual behavior\n- No known high-risk gaps\n- Proven with realistic workloads\n\n## CERTIFICATION PROCESS\n\n### Phase 1: Basic Invocation Test\n**Objective**: Verify skill can be invoked without fatal errors\n**Evidence Required**:\n- Command executed successfully (exit code 0)\n- Usage/help information available if applicable\n- No missing dependency errors\n\n### Phase 2: Core Functionality Test  \n**Objective**: Verify advertised core functions work\n**Evidence Required**:\n- Each core function tested with valid inputs\n- Real outputs produced (not placeholders)\n- Outputs are usable for intended purpose\n- No fake IDs or simulated artifacts\n\n### Phase 3: Integration Test\n**Objective**: Verify connections to dependent components\n**Evidence Required**:\n- Data flows between components verified\n- Integration is real, not just documented\n- Handoffs produce real artifacts\n- No manual translation required between components\n\n### Phase 4: Error Handling Test\n**Objective**: Verify graceful degradation and recovery\n**Evidence Required**:\n- Invalid inputs handled appropriately\n- Missing dependencies detected\n- Error messages are helpful\n- Incident emission works (if applicable)\n- Recovery actions exist (if applicable)\n\n### Phase 5: Performance Test\n**Objective**: Verify acceptable performance characteristics\n**Evidence Required**:\n- Execution time within acceptable limits\n- Resource usage (CPU, memory) reasonable\n- Scalability demonstrated for intended use\n- No memory leaks or resource exhaustion\n\n### Phase 6: Documentation Verification\n**Objective**: Verify documentation matches reality\n**Evidence Required**:\n- SKILL.md accurately describes actual behavior\n- Examples work as shown\n- Limitations documented honestly\n- No overstatement of capabilities\n\n## SKILL-SPECIFIC CERTIFICATION CHECKLISTS\n\n### Checklist: LONG-PROMPT-ORCHESTRATOR\n- [ ] Generates JSON plan from complex prompt\n- [ ] Plan contains executable instructions (not abstract objectives)\n- [ ] Tasks have clear execution_mode (main vs subagent)\n- [ ] Action_instructions are specific and actionable\n- [ ] Validation_method defined for each task\n- [ ] Main can execute plan without manual translation\n- [ ] Tasks produce real artifacts when executed\n- [ ] Final synthesis based on real completed tasks\n- [ ] Handoff reports contain real completion evidence\n- [ ] No fake UUIDs or simulated sub-agents\n\n### Checklist: AGENT-WATCHDOG\n- [ ] Can register real tasks/sessions for monitoring\n- [ ] Creates observable monitoring logs/artifacts\n- [ ] Monitors real runtime metrics\n- [ ] Detects stalls in real workflows\n- [ ] Triggers recovery actions when appropriate\n- [ ] Recovery actions have real effects\n- [ ] Emits real incidents to error-learning-loop\n- [ ] Monitoring directory exists with real data\n- [ ] No placeholder monitoring without real objects\n\n### Checklist: SALESFORCE-CODE-AUDITOR\n- [ ] Processes real Salesforce metadata (APEX, LWC, etc.)\n- [ ] Generates substantive technical findings\n- [ ] Findings include specific code locations\n- [ ] Creates usable audit reports\n- [ ] Reports contain actionable recommendations\n- [ ] Outputs consumable by salesforce-architect\n- [ ] Real dependency graphs from real code\n- [ ] No placeholder findings or empty reports\n- [ ] Works with realistic code samples\n\n### Checklist: DISTRIBUTED EXECUTION (Cross-cutting)\n- [ ] Main agent can delegate tasks to sub-agents\n- [ ] Sub-agents produce real outputs\n- [ ] Handoff reports contain real completion evidence\n- [ ] Task dependencies are real and enforced\n- [ ] Final synthesis based on real sub-agent outputs\n- [ ] No fake handoff reports generated locally\n- [ ] Real session IDs, not generated UUIDs\n- [ ] Monitoring tracks real distributed execution\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS BY LEVEL\n\n### For LEVEL 3 (FUNCTIONAL):\n- All Phase 1-3 tests PASSED\n- Real operational evidence for core functions\n- Basic integration paths verified\n- Development usability proven\n\n### For LEVEL 4 (PRODUCTION-READY):\n- All Phase 1-6 tests PASSED  \n- All integration paths verified\n- Performance acceptable for production\n- Comprehensive error handling\n- Documentation verified accurate\n- Realistic workload testing completed\n\n## CERTIFICATION AUTHORITY\n\n### Who can certify:\n- **Main Agent**: Initial certification based on operational testing\n- **System Owner**: Final approval for production readiness\n- **Validation Framework**: Automated checks where possible\n\n### Certification Records:\n- All certifications recorded in `SKILL_TEST_REGISTRY.yaml`\n- Evidence stored in project folders\n- Certification date and agent recorded\n- Re-certification schedule tracked\n\n## DECERTIFICATION CONDITIONS\n\nA skill may be **decertified** if:\n1. **Regression**: Previously working functionality breaks\n2. **Simulation Discovery**: Found to be simulating vs real operation\n3. **Integration Breakage**: Critical integration paths break\n4. **Performance Degradation**: No longer meets performance requirements\n5. **Documentation Drift**: Documentation no longer matches reality\n\n## RE-CERTIFICATION SCHEDULE\n\n1. **After any code changes**: Basic invocation test required\n2. **Monthly**: High-priority skills re-verified\n3. **Quarterly**: All skills operational check\n4. **When issues reported**: Immediate investigation and re-certification if needed\n\n## CERTIFICATION TEMPLATE\n\n```\nSkill: [skill-name]\nCertification Level: [0-4]\nCertification Date: YYYY-MM-DD\nCertifying Agent: [agent-id]\nEvidence Location: [path/to/evidence]\n\nCore Functions Verified:\n- [ ] Function 1: [evidence]\n- [ ] Function 2: [evidence]\n- [ ] Function 3: [evidence]\n\nIntegration Paths Verified:\n- [ ] Integration with [component]: [evidence]\n\nError Handling Verified:\n- [ ] Invalid input: [evidence]\n- [ ] Missing dependency: [evidence]\n- [ ] Timeout: [evidence]\n\nPerformance Verified:\n- [ ] Execution time: [evidence]\n- [ ] Resource usage: [evidence]\n\nDocumentation Verified:\n- [ ] SKILL.md accuracy: [evidence]\n- [ ] Examples work: [evidence]\n\nKnown Limitations:\n- [List any known limitations]\n\nProduction Readiness: [YES/NO with justification]\n```"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":94,"output":1711,"cacheRead":92032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93837,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773100657909}}
