{"type":"message","id":"5eb25efa","parentId":"f70b8a8b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:00:55.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### **5. EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS.md**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_U6iA4r40tgMxrQjMcOXuZ8a5","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/system_validation/EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS.md","content":"# EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS.md\n# Minimum Evidence Requirements for Skill Certification\n# Last updated: 2026-03-09\n\n## PURPOSE\nDefine the minimum evidence required to prove a skill is FUNCTIONAL vs SIMULATED.\nPrevent certification based on insufficient or fabricated evidence.\n\n## EVIDENCE CATEGORIES\n\n### Category 1: Invocation Evidence\n**Purpose**: Prove skill can be invoked and runs\n**Minimum Requirements**:\n- Command executed (copy-paste or screenshot)\n- Exit code 0 (success) or meaningful error\n- Usage/help information if applicable\n- No missing dependency errors\n\n**Examples of VALID evidence**:\n```\n$ python3 scripts/orchestrate.py --demo basic\n=== Running Basic Demo ===\nOriginal prompt length: 858 chars\nDecomposition fallback triggered.\nDecomposed into 4 mini-tasks.\n```\n\n**Examples of INVALID evidence**:\n- \"Script should work\" (no execution)\n- \"No errors reported\" (no execution shown)\n- Placeholder command without output\n\n### Category 2: Output Substance Evidence\n**Purpose**: Prove outputs are real and usable\n**Minimum Requirements**:\n- Output files created/modified\n- File contents shown (first/last lines)\n- Output is substantive (not placeholders)\n- Output matches expected format\n\n**Examples of VALID evidence**:\n```\nFile created: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/.taskboards/plan_1773098309_b48eced9.json\nFirst 3 lines:\n{\n  \"plan_id\": \"plan_1773098309_b48eced9\",\n  \"original_prompt\": \"Create a comprehensive report...\"\n```\n\n**Examples of INVALID evidence**:\n- \"File was created\" (no content shown)\n- Placeholder content: `{\"status\": \"TODO\"}`\n- Empty files or templates only\n\n### Category 3: Integration Evidence\n**Purpose**: Prove connections to other components are real\n**Minimum Requirements**:\n- Data flow between components shown\n- Integration artifacts created\n- Handoff evidence (not just documentation)\n- No manual translation required\n\n**Examples of VALID evidence**:\n```\n[INFO] Incident logged: test|TEST|audit|test_incident\nTriggering learning loop...\n```\n\n**Examples of INVALID evidence**:\n- \"Can integrate with X\" (no actual integration)\n- Documentation of integration only\n- Placeholder integration functions\n\n### Category 4: Repeatability Evidence\n**Purpose**: Prove behavior is consistent, not one-off\n**Minimum Requirements**:\n- At least 2 successful invocations\n- Consistent outputs across runs\n- No one-off artifacts or random behavior\n\n**Examples of VALID evidence**:\n```\nRun 1: Generated plan_1773098309_b48eced9.json\nRun 2: Generated plan_1773098375_a1b2c3d4.json\nBoth plans have same structure and field completeness.\n```\n\n**Examples of INVALID evidence**:\n- Single execution only\n- \"Should work every time\" (not tested)\n- Inconsistent behavior accepted\n\n### Category 5: Error Handling Evidence\n**Purpose**: Prove graceful degradation and recovery\n**Minimum Requirements**:\n- Invalid input handled appropriately\n- Missing dependency detected\n- Helpful error messages\n- Incident emission if applicable\n\n**Examples of VALID evidence**:\n```\n$ python3 scripts/orchestrate.py invalid arguments\nusage: orchestrate.py [-h] [--prompt PROMPT] [--demo {basic,complex,upgrade}]\nError: unrecognized arguments: invalid arguments\n```\n\n**Examples of INVALID evidence**:\n- Crash with stack trace (unless expected)\n- Silent failure\n- Generic \"something went wrong\" message\n\n## SKILL-SPECIFIC EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n\n### For LONG-PROMPT-ORCHESTRATOR:\n**Minimum Evidence Required**:\n1. **Invocation**: Plan generation from complex prompt\n2. **Output**: JSON plan file with complete structure\n3. **Executability**: Plan contains actionable instructions (not abstract)\n4. **Integration**: Main can execute/delegate based on plan\n5. **Repeatability**: Multiple plans generated consistently\n\n**Critical Evidence (must have)**:\n- Plan with `execution_mode`, `action_instructions`, `validation_method` fields\n- Real task execution evidence (not simulated)\n- Handoff to real sub-agents (not fake UUIDs)\n\n### For AGENT-WATCHDOG:\n**Minimum Evidence Required**:\n1. **Invocation**: Recovery scripts execute\n2. **Monitoring**: Real session/task registration\n3. **Observation**: Monitoring logs/artifacts created\n4. **Detection**: Stall detection in real workflow\n5. **Recovery**: Recovery actions triggered appropriately\n\n**Critical Evidence (must have)**:\n- Monitoring directory with real data\n- Real session IDs being monitored (not placeholders)\n- Recovery actions with observable effects\n\n### For SALESFORCE-CODE-AUDITOR:\n**Minimum Evidence Required**:\n1. **Invocation**: Scripts execute with valid inputs\n2. **Processing**: Real Salesforce metadata processed\n3. **Findings**: Substantive technical findings generated\n4. **Reports**: Usable audit reports created\n5. **Integration**: Outputs consumable by architect\n\n**Critical Evidence (must have)**:\n- Real code analysis (not placeholder findings)\n- Specific code locations in findings\n- Actionable recommendations in reports\n\n## EVIDENCE FORMAT REQUIREMENTS\n\n### Acceptable Formats:\n1. **Command output**: Copy-paste from terminal\n2. **File contents**: First/last lines with ellipsis for large files\n3. **Log snippets**: Relevant log entries with timestamps\n4. **Screenshots**: Only if text extraction not possible\n5. **JSON snippets**: Relevant fields from structured output\n\n### Unacceptable Formats:\n1. **Narrative only**: \"The script worked\"\n2. **Placeholders**: \"Output would be...\"\n3. **Theoretical**: \"Should produce...\"\n4. **Documentation references only**: \"See SKILL.md\"\n5. **Future promises**: \"Will work when...\"\n\n## EVIDENCE STORAGE AND TRACEABILITY\n\n### Storage Location:\n```\n<workspace>/projects/<project_key>/evidence/\n├── <skill_name>/\n│   ├── invocation_<timestamp>.txt\n│   ├── outputs_<timestamp>.json\n│   ├── integration_<timestamp>.log\n│   └── validation_<timestamp>.md\n```\n\n### Required Metadata per Evidence File:\n```\n# evidence_metadata.yaml (auto-generated)\nskill: <skill_name>\ntest_case: <test_id>\ntimestamp: YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS\nexecuting_agent: <agent_id>\ncommand: <executed_command>\nexit_code: <0|1|other>\nevidence_type: <invocation|output|integration|repeatability|error>\ncertification_level_target: <0-4>\n```\n\n## EVIDENCE VALIDATION RULES\n\n### Rule 1: No Fake IDs\n- Reject evidence with generated UUIDs without corresponding runtime objects\n- Require real session IDs, task IDs, run IDs\n\n### Rule 2: No Placeholder Content\n- Reject empty files or template-only outputs\n- Require substantive content matching skill purpose\n\n### Rule 3: No Manual Completion\n- Reject evidence where human \"filled in\" expected results\n- Require automated, repeatable outputs\n\n### Rule 4: No Documentation-Only\n- Reject evidence that only references documentation\n- Require runtime execution evidence\n\n### Rule 5: No One-Off Artifacts\n- Reject evidence from single execution only\n- Require repeatability demonstration\n\n## EVIDENCE REVIEW PROCESS\n\n### Step 1: Completeness Check\n- All required evidence categories present?\n- Minimum requirements met for each category?\n- Critical evidence present for skill type?\n\n### Step 2: Substance Check\n- Evidence shows real execution?\n- Outputs are substantive (not placeholders)?\n- No fake IDs or simulated artifacts?\n\n### Step 3: Integration Check\n- Integration evidence shows real data flow?\n- No manual translation between components?\n- Handoffs produce real artifacts?\n\n### Step 4: Repeatability Check\n- Evidence from multiple executions?\n- Consistent behavior across runs?\n- No one-off or random artifacts?\n\n### Step 5: Error Handling Check\n- Invalid inputs handled appropriately?\n- Helpful error messages?\n- Incident emission if applicable?\n\n## EVIDENCE REJECTION CRITERIA\n\n### Automatic Rejection (any of these):\n1. **No execution shown**: Only narrative description\n2. **Placeholder outputs**: Empty files or template content\n3. **Fake IDs**: Generated UUIDs without runtime objects\n4. **Documentation-only**: References to SKILL.md without runtime proof\n5. **Single execution**: No repeatability evidence\n6. **Manual completion**: Human filled in expected results\n\n### Conditional Acceptance:\n1. **Partial evidence**: Some categories missing but core functionality proven\n2. **Limited testing**: Basic functionality proven but edge cases not tested\n3. **Development evidence**: Works in development but not production-proven\n\n## EVIDENCE FOR CERTIFICATION LEVELS\n\n### For LEVEL 3 (FUNCTIONAL):\n- Categories 1-3: Complete evidence required\n- Category 4: At least 2 executions shown\n- Category 5: Basic error handling shown\n\n### For LEVEL 4 (PRODUCTION-READY):\n- Categories 1-5: Complete evidence required\n- Additional: Performance evidence, comprehensive error handling\n- Additional: Realistic workload testing evidence\n\n## EVIDENCE TEMPLATE\n\n```\n## Skill: [skill-name]\n## Test Case: [test-id]\n## Date: YYYY-MM-DD\n\n### 1. Invocation Evidence\nCommand: [command executed]\nOutput:\n```\n[command output]\n```\n\n### 2. Output Substance Evidence\nFiles created:\n- [file1]: [first/last lines]\n- [file2]: [first/last lines]\n\n### 3. Integration Evidence\nIntegration with [component]:\n```\n[integration output or log]\n```\n\n### 4. Repeatability Evidence\nExecution 1: [output summary]\nExecution 2: [output summary]\nConsistency: [yes/no with explanation]\n\n### 5. Error Handling Evidence\nInvalid input test:\n```\n[error handling output]\n```\n\n### Certification Recommendation: [LEVEL 0-4]\n### Justification: [brief explanation]\n```"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":73,"output":2292,"cacheRead":96576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98941,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773100784186}}
