{"type":"message","id":"152ac05d","parentId":"9768bc4d","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:02:48.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## ✅ **WORKSTREAM A COMPLETADO**\n\n### **Framework de Validación creado (6 archivos):**\n1. **`SKILL_TEST_REGISTRY.yaml`** - Registro de tests operacionales (9,505 bytes)\n2. **`SKILL_REALITY_CRITERIA.md`** - Criterios REAL vs SIMULATED (5,913 bytes)\n3. **`SKILL_CERTIFICATION_RULES.md`** - Reglas de certificación (7,406 bytes)\n4. **`PRODUCTION_CERTIFICATION_MATRIX.md`** - Matriz de estado actual (9,634 bytes)\n5. **`EVIDENCE_REQUIREMENTS.md`** - Requisitos de evidencia (9,336 bytes)\n6. **`ANTI_SIMULATION_RULES.md`** - Reglas anti-simulación (9,364 bytes)\n\n### **📊 Estado Actual del Sistema (según framework):**\n\n#### **✅ PRODUCTION-READY (6 skills):**\n- `salesforce-architect`\n- `workspace-janitor`\n- `error-learning-loop`\n- `vector-memory`\n- `tavily-web-search`\n- `OC-Intent-Governor`\n\n#### **❌ NOT READY (5 skills - críticos):**\n- `long-prompt-orchestrator` 🟠 PARTIAL (HIGH risk)\n- `agent-watchdog` 🟠 PARTIAL (HIGH risk)\n- `salesforce-code-auditor` 🟠 PARTIAL (MEDIUM risk)\n- `OC-Respawner` 🟠 PARTIAL (MEDIUM risk)\n- `OC-System-Evolver` 🟠 PARTIAL (MEDIUM risk)\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 **WORKSTREAM B: FIX `long-prompt-orchestrator`**\n\n### **Problema Identificado:**\nEl skill genera planes JSON pero **NO son ejecutables**. Main agent tiene que traducir manualmente.\n\n### **Solución Requerida:**\nConvertir planes de \"objetivos abstractos\" a \"instrucciones ejecutables\".\n\n### **Crear Sub-agent Especializado:**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_JInydKZc64Pu0P4gr3UagjWP","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"# TASK: Fix long-prompt-orchestrator for Real Usable Plans\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `long-prompt-orchestrator` skill is currently classified as PARTIAL because it generates plans that are not executable by the main agent. Plans contain abstract task descriptions instead of actionable instructions.\n\n## PROBLEM ANALYSIS\nCurrent plan format (defective):\n```json\n{\n  \"task_01\": \"Which skills actually work and produce real results.\",\n  \"task_02\": \"Which skills only simulate functionality...\"\n}\n```\n\nRequired plan format (functional):\n```json\n{\n  \"task_01\": {\n    \"objective\": \"Inventory all skills in workspace\",\n    \"execution_mode\": \"main\",\n    \"action_type\": \"exec\",\n    \"action_instructions\": \"find /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills -type f -name 'SKILL.md' | sort\",\n    \"expected_outputs\": \"list of SKILL.md files\",\n    \"validation_method\": \"output_lines > 0\",\n    \"artifact_destination\": \"projects/{project_key}/inventory_skills.txt\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nFix the `long-prompt-orchestrator` to generate **executable plans** that main agent can use without manual translation.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Update Plan Format\nModify the plan generation to include these REQUIRED fields per task:\n- `execution_mode`: \"main\" | \"subagent\" | \"mixed\"\n- `action_type`: \"exec\" | \"python\" | \"skill_invocation\" | \"file_operation\"\n- `action_instructions`: Specific, executable instructions\n- `required_inputs`: List of inputs needed\n- `expected_outputs`: What outputs should be produced\n- `validation_method`: How to validate task completion\n- `recommended_skill_or_role`: Which skill/sub-agent should handle this\n- `artifact_destination`: Where to store outputs\n\n### 2. Ensure Executability\n- Tasks must be specific enough for direct execution\n- No abstract objectives like \"analyze the system\"\n- Instead: \"Run command: find ... | wc -l\"\n- Include concrete validation criteria\n\n### 3. Preserve Architecture\n- Skill remains planner/decomposer only\n- Main agent remains executor/delegator\n- No spawning code added to skill\n- Only plan format improvements\n\n### 4. Testing Requirements\nCreate test that proves:\n- Generated plan is executable by main agent\n- Main can execute/delegate based on plan\n- Tasks produce real artifacts\n- Final synthesis based on real completed tasks\n\n## FILES TO MODIFY\n1. `scripts/orchestrate.py` - Main orchestration logic\n2. `scripts/plan_generator.py` - Plan generation logic\n3. `SKILL.md` - Update documentation to reflect new plan format\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Updated code** with executable plan format\n2. **Test evidence** showing:\n   - Old plan (abstract) vs new plan (executable)\n   - Main agent successfully using new plan\n   - Real artifacts produced from plan execution\n3. **Updated documentation** reflecting changes\n4. **Handoff report** with outcome and incidents\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS (Anti-simulation)\n- NO fake UUIDs or simulated sub-agents\n- NO placeholder artifacts\n- NO manual completion by you\n- REAL execution evidence required\n- REAL artifact creation shown\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 30 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\n`long-prompt-orchestrator` moves from PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL in certification matrix when:\n1. Plans are executable without manual translation\n2. Main agent can use plans directly\n3. Real distributed execution is enabled (when tasks marked for subagents)\n4. Evidence shows real artifact creation from plan execution\n\nProceed with surgical fixes to make plans truly usable.","label":"LPO Executable Plan Fix Specialist","runtime":"subagent","model":"deepseek-chat"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":52,"output":1405,"cacheRead":101056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":102513,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773100924343}}
{"type":"message","id":"193a30ee","parentId":"152ac05d","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:02:48.978Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_JInydKZc64Pu0P4gr3UagjWP","toolName":"sessions_spawn","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"accepted\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:e96b4060-87f4-4a0a-a343-69fd012a92b5\",\n  \"runId\": \"edb088fc-ff41-4aab-9a80-b6932f7b8c21\",\n  \"mode\": \"run\",\n  \"note\": \"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.\",\n  \"modelApplied\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"accepted","childSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:e96b4060-87f4-4a0a-a343-69fd012a92b5","runId":"edb088fc-ff41-4aab-9a80-b6932f7b8c21","mode":"run","note":"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.","modelApplied":true},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773100968968}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d211222","parentId":"193a30ee","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:03:22.382Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 🎯 **WORKSTREAM C: FIX `agent-watchdog`**\n\n### **Problema Identificado:**\nWatchdog tiene lógica de recovery pero **NO monitorea nada real**. No hay evidencia de observabilidad operacional.\n\n### **Solución Requerida:**\nImplementar monitoreo REAL de sesiones/tareas, crear directorio de monitoreo con logs reales.\n\n### **Crear Sub-agent Especializado:**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ZWdClH2nhW2EVZ5akH4LrTgy","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"# TASK: Fix agent-watchdog for Real Observability\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `agent-watchdog` skill is currently classified as PARTIAL because it has recovery logic but NO REAL MONITORING. There's no evidence of actual observability or monitoring activity.\n\n## PROBLEM ANALYSIS\nCurrent state (defective):\n- Recovery code exists but never triggered\n- No monitoring directory (`~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`)\n- No real session/task monitoring\n- No observable monitoring logs or artifacts\n- \"Monitoring\" exists only in documentation\n\nRequired state (functional):\n- Real monitoring of agent sessions/tasks\n- Observable monitoring logs/artifacts\n- Real session registration and tracking\n- Actual stall detection in real workflows\n- Recovery actions triggered when appropriate\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nConvert `agent-watchdog` from simulated monitoring to REAL observability.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Create Real Monitoring Infrastructure\n- Create directory: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n- Implement session registration system\n- Create monitoring logs with real data\n- Track actual runtime metrics\n\n### 2. Implement Real Session Monitoring\n- Monitor real OpenClaw agent sessions\n- Track session duration, activity, state\n- Detect stalls based on real metrics (not simulated)\n- Create observable monitoring artifacts\n\n### 3. Enable Real Recovery Triggers\n- Recovery logic should trigger based on REAL monitoring data\n- Not based on simulated or placeholder data\n- Recovery actions should have observable effects\n\n### 4. Integration with Real Workflows\n- Monitor actual sub-agent executions\n- Track real task progress\n- Detect real stalls in distributed execution\n- Emit real incidents to error-learning-loop\n\n## FILES TO MODIFY/CREATE\n1. `scripts/watchdog_monitor.py` - NEW: Real session monitoring\n2. `scripts/watchdog_recovery.py` - ENHANCE: Trigger based on real monitoring\n3. `scripts/watchdog_integration.py` - NEW: Integration with OpenClaw sessions\n4. `config/watchdog_config.yaml` - Configuration for monitoring\n5. `SKILL.md` - Update to reflect real capabilities\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Real monitoring infrastructure** (directory, logs, registration)\n2. **Updated recovery logic** triggered by real monitoring\n3. **Test evidence** showing:\n   - Real session monitoring (not simulated)\n   - Observable monitoring logs/artifacts\n   - Real stall detection (not simulated)\n   - Recovery triggered based on real data\n4. **Integration evidence** with error-learning-loop\n5. **Handoff report** with outcome and incidents\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS (Anti-simulation)\n- NO placeholder monitoring directories\n- NO fake session IDs or monitoring data\n- NO simulated stall detection\n- REAL monitoring logs with actual session data\n- REAL recovery triggers based on actual metrics\n- REAL incident emission when appropriate\n\n## TEST SCENARIOS TO PROVE\n1. **Monitoring Reality Test**: Show real session being monitored\n2. **Stall Detection Test**: Create real stall scenario, show detection\n3. **Recovery Trigger Test**: Show recovery triggered by real monitoring data\n4. **Integration Test**: Show incidents emitted to error-learning-loop\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 30 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\n`agent-watchdog` moves from PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL in certification matrix when:\n1. Real monitoring infrastructure exists and works\n2. Real sessions are being monitored (not simulated)\n3. Real stall detection occurs (not simulated)\n4. Recovery triggers based on real monitoring data\n5. Evidence shows real observability (logs, artifacts, metrics)\n\nFocus on making monitoring REAL, not just documenting it.","label":"Watchdog Reality Implementation Specialist","runtime":"subagent","model":"deepseek-chat"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":240,"output":996,"cacheRead":102464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103700,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773100968976}}
