{"type":"message","id":"4b6472c5","parentId":"ee1fd473","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:03:55.075Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 🎯 **WORKSTREAM D: PROBAR `salesforce-code-auditor` CON FIXTURES REALES**\n\n### **Problema Identificado:**\nAuditor tiene scripts pero **NO probado con datos reales**. \"Funciona si el usuario provee código real después\".\n\n### **Solución Requerida:**\nCrear fixtures de prueba REALES de Salesforce, probar procesamiento sustantivo.\n\n### **Crear Sub-agent Especializado:**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Lra4cXIMQIlHjFkekVlz30yg","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"# TASK: Test salesforce-code-auditor with Real Fixtures\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `salesforce-code-auditor` skill is currently classified as PARTIAL because it hasn't been tested with real Salesforce metadata. The claim \"works if user supplies real code later\" is not sufficient proof of functionality.\n\n## PROBLEM ANALYSIS\nCurrent state (unproven):\n- Scripts exist and can be invoked\n- Not tested with real Salesforce metadata\n- Unknown if generates substantive findings\n- Unknown if outputs are consumable by architect\n- Functionality is theoretical, not proven\n\nRequired state (proven):\n- Tested with real Salesforce code samples\n- Generates substantive technical findings\n- Creates usable audit reports\n- Outputs are consumable by salesforce-architect\n- Real dependency graphs from real code\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nProve `salesforce-code-auditor` functionality with REAL Salesforce fixtures, not placeholders.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Create Real Test Fixtures\n- Create realistic Salesforce metadata samples:\n  - APEX classes (with typical patterns)\n  - LWC components (JavaScript + HTML)\n  - Visualforce pages\n  - Triggers\n  - Flows\n- Include both \"good\" and \"bad\" patterns for testing\n- Make fixtures representative of real Salesforce projects\n\n### 2. Test Full Audit Pipeline\n- Intake: Process fixture files\n- Analysis: Generate substantive findings\n- Reporting: Create usable audit reports\n- Integration: Verify outputs consumable by architect\n\n### 3. Verify Output Substance\n- Findings must be specific and technical\n- Not generic or placeholder findings\n- Include code locations, severity, recommendations\n- Reports must be complete and actionable\n\n### 4. Test Integration Readiness\n- Verify output format matches architect expectations\n- Test handoff from auditor to architect\n- Ensure project routing preserved\n- Verify artifacts stay in project folder\n\n## FILES TO CREATE\n1. `fixtures/real_salesforce_samples/` - Directory with real code samples\n2. `tests/test_with_real_fixtures.py` - Test script using real fixtures\n3. `evidence/audit_outputs/` - Generated audit reports as evidence\n4. `integration_test_report.md` - Report on architect ↔ auditor integration\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Real Salesforce fixtures** (not placeholders)\n2. **Audit evidence** showing:\n   - Real code processed (not simulated)\n   - Substantive findings generated\n   - Complete audit reports\n   - Technical specificity in findings\n3. **Integration evidence** showing outputs consumable by architect\n4. **Classification evidence** for certification:\n   - FUNCTIONAL if all tests pass with real data\n   - PARTIAL if some functions work but limitations exist\n   - SIMULATED if outputs are placeholder/descriptive only\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS (Anti-simulation)\n- NO placeholder findings or empty reports\n- NO \"works with real code later\" claims\n- REAL code analysis with specific findings\n- REAL audit reports with actionable recommendations\n- REAL integration testing with architect\n\n## TEST SCENARIOS\n1. **APEX Analysis Test**: Process real APEX classes, find specific issues\n2. **LWC Analysis Test**: Process real Lightning Web Components\n3. **Dependency Graph Test**: Generate real dependency graphs\n4. **Integration Test**: Verify architect can consume audit outputs\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 30 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\n`salesforce-code-auditor` classification depends on results:\n- **FUNCTIONAL**: All tests pass with real data, substantive findings\n- **PARTIAL**: Some functions work but limitations found\n- **SIMULATED**: Only placeholder outputs, no real analysis\n\nFocus on proving REAL functionality, not theoretical capability.","label":"Salesforce Auditor Reality Tester","runtime":"subagent","model":"deepseek-chat"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":210,"output":1010,"cacheRead":103680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104900,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101002524}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4948e72","parentId":"4b6472c5","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:03:55.232Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_Lra4cXIMQIlHjFkekVlz30yg","toolName":"sessions_spawn","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"accepted\",\n  \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:71f6ae19-15fd-4b6c-a446-3af75a427b2d\",\n  \"runId\": \"70d47996-4c12-4e03-ba12-6a8503dbd294\",\n  \"mode\": \"run\",\n  \"note\": \"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.\",\n  \"modelApplied\": true\n}"}],"details":{"status":"accepted","childSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:71f6ae19-15fd-4b6c-a446-3af75a427b2d","runId":"70d47996-4c12-4e03-ba12-6a8503dbd294","mode":"run","note":"Auto-announce is push-based. After spawning children, do NOT call sessions_list, sessions_history, exec sleep, or any polling tool. Wait for completion events to arrive as user messages, track expected child session keys, and only send your final answer after ALL expected completions arrive. If a child completion event arrives AFTER your final answer, reply ONLY with NO_REPLY.","modelApplied":true},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773101035226}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e7d043c","parentId":"d4948e72","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:04:27.115Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 🎯 **WORKSTREAM E: VALIDAR INTEGRACIÓN SALESFORCE**\n\n### **Problema Identificado:**\nIntegración architect ↔ auditor **documentada pero no verificada**. No hay evidencia de flujo real de datos.\n\n### **Solución Requerida:**\nProbar cadena REAL: architect llama auditor → auditor devuelve outputs → architect consume findings.\n\n### **Crear Sub-agent Especializado:**"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Xbh7PJOyvpFzX5JUEzLcHBPU","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"# TASK: Validate Salesforce Architect ↔ Auditor Real Integration\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe integration between `salesforce-architect` and `salesforce-code-auditor` is documented but NOT VERIFIED with real data flow. There's no evidence that architect can actually call auditor and consume its outputs.\n\n## PROBLEM ANALYSIS\nCurrent state (unverified):\n- Integration documented in SKILL.md files\n- No evidence of real data flow between components\n- Unknown if architect can actually call auditor\n- Unknown if auditor outputs are consumable by architect\n- Unknown if project routing is preserved\n- Unknown if artifacts stay in project folder\n\nRequired state (verified):\n- Architect can call auditor with real project data\n- Auditor returns outputs architect can consume\n- Project routing preserved through integration\n- Artifacts stay in project folder\n- Architect can use audit findings in architectural reasoning\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nProve the REAL integration between salesforce-architect and salesforce-code-auditor.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Test Real Integration Flow\n- Create test project with real Salesforce requirements\n- Architect initiates audit via real integration (not simulated)\n- Auditor processes real code samples\n- Architect consumes audit findings\n- Verify complete data flow end-to-end\n\n### 2. Verify Integration Points\n- Architect → Auditor: Call with real project context\n- Auditor → Architect: Return consumable findings\n- Project context preserved through handoff\n- Artifact containment verified\n\n### 3. Test Integration in Real Scenarios\n- Use real project from architect pipeline\n- Trigger audit as part of architectural process\n- Verify findings influence architectural decisions\n- Ensure integration doesn't break existing functionality\n\n### 4. Validate Output Usability\n- Architect can parse and use audit findings\n- Findings integrated into architectural artifacts\n- Audit results influence DoD validation\n- Integration supports real decision-making\n\n## TEST APPROACH\n1. **Create Real Test Project**: Use architect to create project with audit requirement\n2. **Trigger Real Audit**: Architect calls auditor with real project data\n3. **Process Real Code**: Auditor analyzes real Salesforce samples\n4. **Consume Findings**: Architect uses findings in architectural process\n5. **Verify Integration**: Check data flow, artifact containment, routing\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Integration evidence** showing:\n   - Real architect → auditor call (not simulated)\n   - Real auditor → architect data flow\n   - Project context preserved\n   - Artifact containment verified\n2. **Usability evidence** showing:\n   - Architect can parse and use audit findings\n   - Findings influence architectural artifacts\n   - Integration supports real decision-making\n3. **Classification evidence**:\n   - INTEGRATION FUNCTIONAL: All tests pass, real data flow\n   - INTEGRATION PARTIAL: Some integration works but limitations\n   - INTEGRATION SIMULATED: No real data flow, only documentation\n\n## EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS (Anti-simulation)\n- NO simulated integration calls\n- NO placeholder data flow\n- REAL architect invoking real auditor\n- REAL data flowing between components\n- REAL artifact creation and consumption\n\n## TEST SCENARIOS\n1. **Basic Integration Test**: Architect calls auditor, gets findings\n2. **Project Context Test**: Project routing preserved through integration\n3. **Artifact Containment Test**: All artifacts stay in project folder\n4. **Decision Influence Test**: Audit findings influence architectural decisions\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 30 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\nIntegration classification:\n- **FUNCTIONAL**: Real data flow, architect consumes findings, project routing preserved\n- **PARTIAL**: Some integration works but gaps exist\n- **SIMULATED**: No real data flow, integration exists only in documentation\n\nFocus on proving REAL integration, not documented integration.","label":"Salesforce Integration Validator","runtime":"subagent","model":"deepseek-chat"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":195,"output":993,"cacheRead":104896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106084,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773101035230}}
