{"type":"message","id":"ca5f5730","parentId":"855863ff","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:17:05.463Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 🔍 **Resultado de Prueba: `salesforce-code-auditor` con Fixtures Reales**\n\n### **📋 Hallazgos Clave:**\n\n**El skill `salesforce-code-auditor` está clasificado como: 🟠 PARCIAL (no SIMULADO)**\n\n### **✅ Lo que SÍ funciona (REAL, no simulado):**\n\n#### **1. Análisis de Código REAL:**\n- **Parsing de APEX**: Extrae SOQL objects, operaciones DML, llamadas a métodos\n- **Detección de LWC**: Identifica imports desde Apex (`@salesforce/apex/ClassName.method`)\n- **Relaciones Visualforce**: Detecta páginas → controladores\n- **Gráficos de dependencia**: Construye relaciones reales entre componentes\n\n#### **2. Evidencia Concreta de Funcionalidad REAL:**\n```\nAccountController: SOQL=['Contact','Account','Opportunity'], DML=['contacts','opps','insert']\nAccountService: extends=Exception, SOQL=['Contact','Account'], DML=['contactsToUpdate','acc']\n```\n\n#### **3. Fixtures REALES creados:**\n- **9 archivos Salesforce** (1,091 líneas)\n- Patrones buenos y malos intencionalmente\n- APEX, LWC, Visualforce, Triggers, Flows\n\n### **❌ Lo que NO funciona (incompleto):**\n\n#### **1. Capa de Reporting Incompleta:**\n- **Análisis**: ✅ Funciona (parsing real)\n- **Reporting**: ❌ Incompleto (templates sin hallazgos llenados)\n\n#### **2. Síntesis de Hallazgos Faltante:**\n- Dependencias parseadas → no convertidas a hallazgos específicos\n- Sin evaluación de riesgo (CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)\n- Sin recomendaciones de fixes\n\n#### **3. Integración No Lista:**\n- Reports son templates, no llenados con análisis\n- Sin formato consumible por architect\n- Sin mecanismo de handoff implementado\n\n### **🎯 Arquitectura Identificada:**\n\n#### **Capa 1 (✅ FUNCIONAL):** Análisis de código\n- Parsing, extracción de dependencias, detección de entrypoints\n\n#### **Capa 2 (❌ INCOMPLETA):** Reporting\n- Templates sin hallazgos llenados\n- Sin síntesis de findings\n- Sin formato para integración\n\n### **📊 Clasificación Justificada:**\n\n**🟠 PARCIAL (no SIMULADO, no FUNCTIONAL):**\n- ✅ **NO es simulado**: Realiza análisis de código REAL\n- ❌ **NO es completamente funcional**: Falta capa de reporting\n- ⚠️ **Es parcial**: Funciona para análisis, incompleto para reporting\n\n### **🚨 Recomendaciones para Completar el Skill:**\n\n#### **Para hacerlo FUNCTIONAL:**\n1. **Agregar síntesis de hallazgos**: Convertir dependencias parseadas → hallazgos específicos\n2. **Implementar evaluación de riesgo**: Clasificar hallazgos (CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)\n3. **Generar recomendaciones**: Sugerir fixes para patrones malos\n4. **Formatear para architect**: Seguir `CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md`\n5. **Agregar emisión de incidentes**: Integrar con error-learning-loop\n\n### **💡 Conclusión:**\n\n**El skill tiene valor técnico REAL como motor de análisis de código**, pero necesita completar la capa de reporting para ser una solución de auditoría completa.\n\n**¿Quieres que asigne otro sub-agent para completar la capa de reporting y hacer el skill completamente FUNCTIONAL?**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":77084,"output":829,"cacheRead":30400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108313,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773101783314}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"727108ae","parentId":"ca5f5730","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:18:48.708Z","summary":"## Goal\nExecute a deep technical audit of the OpenClaw ecosystem to determine which components are truly functional and which only simulate functionality, producing a single consolidated report. Additionally, incorporate post-audit analysis revealing a critical defect in `long-prompt-orchestrator`.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Do not assume any skill works; treat all as unverified until proven operational.\n- No narrative or speculative answers; require operational tests, observable results, evidence, and technical analysis.\n- Do not delete system files.\n- Do not make destructive changes.\n- If simulation is detected, report it explicitly.\n- Prioritize real behavior over documentation inconsistencies.\n- Final deliverables must only remain in the project workspace: `workspace/projects/openclaw_real_capability_audit/` (specifically `OPENCLAW_REAL_CAPABILITY_AUDIT_REPORT.md` and `README.md`).\n- **Post-audit**: Evaluate skills by their operational purpose, not just technical output.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] **Session startup sequence executed**: Read `SOUL.md`, `USER.md`, `memory/2026-03-09.md`, `MEMORY.md`, `.learnings/INDEX.md` per AGENTS.md rules.\n- [x] **Contextual Learning Retrieval applied**: Identified 5 relevant Pattern-Keys from `.learnings/INDEX.md` for complex task execution.\n- [x] **Project setup**: Created `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/projects/openclaw_real_capability_audit/` and saved audit prompt.\n- [x] **Phase 1: Inventory completed**: Cataloged 11 skills, 6 active cron jobs, critical folders, and control files.\n- [x] **Phase 2: Operational Tests completed**: Tested 11 skills individually. Verified 6 as functional, 4 as partially functional, 0 simulated, 0 broken.\n- [x] **Integration Tests completed**: Distributed execution planning verified (but plans defective), watchdog monitoring partially verified, memory interaction verified, failure handling partially verified.\n- [x] **Phase 3: Report Generation completed**: Created `OPENCLAW_REAL_CAPABILITY_AUDIT_REPORT.md` (9,619 bytes) and `README.md` (3,899 bytes) in the project folder.\n- [x] **Post-audit analysis and report update**: Identified critical defect in `long-prompt-orchestrator` (generates plans but not executable for true distributed execution). Updated report and README to reflect corrected statistics: 5 functional (45%), 5 partially functional (45%).\n\n### In Progress\n- (none)\n\n### Blocked\n- (none)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Project Setup**: Created new project `openclaw_real_capability_audit`.\n- **Audit Methodology**: Proceeded in three phases: Inventory, Operational Testing, Report Generation.\n- **Skill Classification**: Classified as \"real\" (produces verifiable results/artifacts) or \"simulated\" (only descriptive text).\n- **Direct Execution by Main Agent**: Chose to execute all tests directly (no sub-agents) because the audit itself was testing system capabilities.\n- **Initial LPO Evaluation Correction**: Initially classified `long-prompt-orchestrator` as \"FUNCIONAL\" based on technical output (JSON generation). Post-audit analysis reclassified it as \"PARCIALMENTE FUNCIONAL / DEFECTUOSO\" because it fails its core purpose: generating executable plans for true distributed execution.\n- **Report Honesty**: Updated final audit report with post-audit findings, correcting statistics and adding detailed analysis of the LPO defect.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Address high-priority fixes from recommendations (verify `agent-watchdog` integration, complete testing of partially functional skills).\n2. Schedule follow-up audit in 30 days.\n3. Implement monitoring for critical components.\n4. Create regression tests to prevent capability loss.\n\n## Critical Context\n- System evaluated: 11 skills including `long-prompt-orchestrator`, `agent-watchdog`, `error-learning-loop`, `OC-Intent-Governor`, `workspace-janitor`, memory system, `vector-memory`, `salesforce-architect`, `salesforce-code-auditor`, `tavily-web-search`, internal integrations.\n- **Critical Finding**: `long-prompt-orchestrator` has a fundamental defect. It generates JSON plans but they are not executable (tasks are abstract objectives, not concrete instructions). It simulates orchestration without enabling true distributed execution.\n- **Overall Verdict**: OpenClaw is a real, operational system (not a simulation) but with specific critical defects. Production-ready with areas for improvement.\n- Audit evidence includes real generated files: `plan_1773098309_b48eced9.json`, `workspace_inventory.json`, `MEMORY_2026-03-09_181922.md.bak`.\n\n## Decisions\n- To test system capabilities authentically, the main agent executed all audit tests directly without spawning sub-agents.\n- The audit prompt (5,772 chars) was recognized as a candidate for `long-prompt-orchestrator`. The skill was invoked and generated a plan (`plan_1773095868_c9021beb.json`), but the plan was deemed technically flawed (overly granular tasks, dependency graph causing deadlock, incorrect skill recommendations). The main agent exercised technical judgment to create a simplified execution plan instead.\n- Post-audit, the evaluation of `long-prompt-orchestrator` was corrected from \"FUNCIONAL\" to \"PARCIALMENTE FUNCIONAL / DEFECTUOSO\" based on its failure to fulfill its operational purpose.\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Verify `agent-watchdog` integration (create monitoring directory, test task registration, verify stall detection).\n- Complete testing of partially functional skills (`OC-Respawner`, `OC-System-Evolver`, `salesforce-code-auditor` with test data).\n- Improve failure handling and automatic recovery.\n- Optimize distributed execution parameters in `long-prompt-orchestrator`.\n- Update dependency documentation.\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Skills must be proven operational through execution; none are assumed to work.\n- Final output must be a single cons