{"type":"message","id":"7a8dc2a8","parentId":"8d2cd077","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:21:37.033Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_X3Do6V4Vxus6BvmE6z9HesJW","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: oc-respawner\ndescription: A self-documenting migration system that analyzes, documents, tracks, and reconstructs the OpenClaw environment on a new machine through non-destructive observation, host-aware migration logic, and deterministic reconstruction.\ncategory: system\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"python\", \"bash\"]\noptional_requires: [\"postgresql\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: false\n---\n\n# OC-Respawner Skill\n\n## Purpose\nA self-documenting migration system that analyzes, documents, tracks, and reconstructs the OpenClaw environment on a new machine (target: macOS / Mac Mini).\n\n## Design Principles\n1. **Non‑destructive observation** - Only observe, never modify existing systems\n2. **Host‑aware migration logic** - Detect current OS (Linux) vs target OS (macOS)\n3. **Security‑first** - Never store API keys or secrets in knowledge base\n4. **Deterministic reconstruction** - Same input should produce same output\n5. **Incremental maintenance** - Support daily updates to knowledge base\n6. **Structured data first** - Use JSON + Markdown for knowledge base\n\n## Skill Structure\n```\nskills/OC-Respawner/\n├── SKILL.md (this file)\n├── scripts/\n\n[121 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773105697024}}
