{"type":"compaction","id":"ad91f0df","parentId":"b62214a6","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:39:08.790Z","summary":"## Goal\nExecute a strict operational reinforcement initiative over the OpenClaw ecosystem to eliminate gaps between documented, claimed, and real operational capability. Focus on moving critical components to either FUNCTIONAL (real, repeatable behavior) or EXPLICITLY PARTIAL (honestly classified) states. Highest priority: fix `long-prompt-orchestrator`, `agent-watchdog`, `salesforce-code-auditor`, and build a real operational validation framework. Subsequently, execute a continuous operational audit loop (Cycle 1) to validate all components against strict anti-simulation rules until SYSTEM_PRODUCTION_READY criteria are met.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- No cosmetic improvements, conceptual redesigns, placeholder implementations, or documentation-only \"fixes\".\n- Treat every component as untrusted until operationally proven.\n- Reject simulations, fabricated outputs, placeholders, architecture-only upgrades, prototypes presented as production-ready, partial implementations reported as complete, narrative-only evidence, and success by documentation changes.\n- Must produce immediate executable fixes where safe (FIX_NOW, DEFER_WITH_REASON, NOT_FIXABLE_NOW).\n- Distribute fixes intelligently to sub-agents; main acts as supervisor/validator/integrator.\n- Do not destabilize stable areas unnecessarily (memory system, error-learning-loop, workspace-janitor, tavily-web-search/firecrawl if functional, salesforce-architect, OC-Intent-Governor unless a real defect is found).\n- No destructive refactors unless absolutely necessary; prefer surgical fixes.\n- All responses and final report must be concise, direct, low-redundancy, token-efficient.\n- Final output must include an Immediate Fix Plan, Fix Distribution Plan, and Skill Capability Matrix with classifications (FUNCTIONAL, PARTIAL, SIMULATED, BROKEN, NOT_YET_VERIFIED) justified by real evidence.\n- Work in