{"type":"message","id":"4dad19ea","parentId":"bf92b16d","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:39:27.827Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 🔧 **LPO Simulation Defect Fix - Progress Update**\n\nEl sub-agente que estaba trabajando en arreglar el defecto de simulación en `long-prompt-orchestrator` ha completado su trabajo con resultados mixtos:\n\n### **✅ Lo que SÍ se arregló:**\n- **Defecto principal corregido**: Los \"echo statements\" para tareas complejas ya no se generan\n- **Instrucciones específicas**: Ahora genera instrucciones ejecutables reales en lugar de placeholders\n\n### **⚠️ Lo que NO se arregló completamente:**\n- **Dashboard Creation**: Algunas tareas de creación de dashboard todavía fallan\n- **Report Generation**: La generación de reportes no tiene instrucciones específicas suficientes\n- **Skill invocation**: Algunas tareas todavía dependen de invocación de skills en lugar de instrucciones directas\n\n### **📊 Estado actual:**\nEl defecto de simulación principal (echo statements) está **corregido**, pero hay áreas que necesitan más trabajo para ser completamente funcionales.\n\n**Nota importante**: Este sub-agente fue terminado prematuramente como parte del reinicio completo del audit, pero al menos logró corregir el defecto crítico de simulación.\n\n---\n\n**Continuando con el audit completo desde cero** como solicitaste. Ya tengo clasificaciones honestas para 3 skills basadas en evidencia REAL (no simulada). \n\n¿Quieres que continúe con el audit de los otros 8 skills, o prefieres que primero me enfoque en los fixes para los problemas ya identificados?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":33877,"output":352,"cacheRead":15232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49461,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773106749061}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f327e43","parentId":"4dad19ea","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:46:58.382Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-09 20:39:09 EST] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Execute your Session Startup sequence now — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Every Session\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-09.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\nSystem: 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\nSystem: 5. **Contextual Learning Retrieval** – Before executing any complex or tool-based task, perform a quick learning retrieval using the learning index:\nSystem:    - Scan `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md`\nSystem:    - Identify Pattern‑Keys relevant to the current task context\nSystem:    - Select the top 3–7 relevant Pattern‑Keys\nSystem:    - Apply their Rules or Preflight constraints before executing the task\nSystem:    - Only consult `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` if a rule requires additional detail\nSystem:    \nSystem:    This retrieval step must be lightweight and should avoid loading large logs unnecessarily.\nSystem: \nSystem: Don't ask permission. Just do it.\nSystem: \nSystem: ### Trigger Heuristics\nSystem: \nSystem: Run Contextual Learning Retrieval when any of the following conditions apply:\nSystem: \nSystem: - Using external tools (bash, python, shell scripts)\nSystem: - Delegating work to sub-agents\nSystem: - Running validator agents or batch operations\nSystem: - Producing multi-file outputs (skills, scripts, documentation, codebases)\nSystem: - Tasks expected to require multiple reasoning steps (>3 steps)\nSystem: \nSystem: Skip retrieval for trivial or conversational responses.\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Safety\nSystem: \nSystem: - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\nSystem: - Don't run destructive commands without asking.\nSystem: - `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\nSystem: - When in doubt, ask.\nSystem: \nSystem: Current time: Monday, March 9th, 2026 — 8:39 PM (America/Panama) / 2026-03-10 01:39 UTC\n\nRead HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 9th, 2026 — 8:46 PM (America/Panama) / 2026-03-10 01:46 UTC"}],"timestamp":1773107218375}}
