{"type":"message","id":"00343d53","parentId":"e0ee2342","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:10:58.744Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### **🎯 ¡PERFECTO! DASHBOARD FUNCIONANDO CON DATOS REALES:**\n\n1. ✅ **1 sesión activa**: La sesión principal (`agent:main:main`)\n2. ✅ **Sub-agent detectado**: `Integration Procedures Researcher` con `age_seconds: 561.83` (9.3 minutos)\n3. ✅ **15 sesiones totales**: Todas de fuente `openclaw_sessions_json`\n4. ✅ **Datos REALES**: No demo, no simulation\n\n### **Paso 6: Verificar que el sub-agent está trabajando REALMENTE**\n\nVamos a verificar el estado del sub-agent:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_0hCAe0Aohr6ekLwTQYXMztw4","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:c44a34cb-1719-4046-a79f-39a9217b5fe7","limit":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":440,"output":233,"cacheRead":90112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90785,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773108647901}}
{"type":"message","id":"53c6db41","parentId":"00343d53","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:10:58.795Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_0hCAe0Aohr6ekLwTQYXMztw4","toolName":"sessions_history","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:c44a34cb-1719-4046-a79f-39a9217b5fe7\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Excellent! Now let me create a best practices document based on my findings:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_04MsecCzt5HhClFQPn4PKE8g\",\n          \"name\": \"write\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skill_integration_best_practices.md\",\n            \"content\": \"# OpenClaw Skill Integration Best Practices\\n\\n**Version**: 1.0  \\n**Date**: 2026-03-09  \\n**Based on Research**: Integration Procedures Investigation\\n\\n## 1. Integration Patterns\\n\\n### 1.1 File-Based Integration (Recommended)\\nUse shared files for loose coupling and reliability.\\n\\n```python\\n# ✅ Recommended: Write structured data to shared directories\\nimport json\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\n\\nworkspace = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'\\n\\ndef emit_incident(pattern_key, severity, description, evidence):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Emit incident to error-learning-loop.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    incident = {\\n        \\\"pattern_key\\\": pattern_key,\\n        \\\"timestamp\\\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\\n        \\\"severity\\\": severity,\\n        \\\"description\\\": description,\\n        \\\"evidence\\\": evidence,\\n        \\\"source_skill\\\": __name__\\n    }\\n    \\n    # Write to .learnings directory\\n    incident_file = workspace / '.learnings' / f'incident_{datetime.now().strftime(\\\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\\\")}.json'\\n    \\n    with open(incident_file, 'w') as f:\\n        json.dump(incident, f, indent=2)\\n    \\n    return incident_file\\n```\\n\\n**Advantages**:\\n- Loose coupling between skills\\n- Asynchronous processing\\n- Reliable (file system is stable)\\n- Easy to debug (files are inspectable)\\n\\n### 1.2 Subprocess Integration (For Script Execution)\\nCall other skill scripts via subprocess with proper error handling.\\n\\n```python\\n# ✅ Recommended: Subprocess with timeout and error handling\\nimport subprocess\\nimport sys\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\\ndef call_skill_script(script_path, args, timeout=30):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Call a skill script with proper error handling.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    script_path = Path(script_path)\\n    \\n    if not script_path.exists():\\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\\\"Script not found: {script_path}\\\")\\n    \\n    cmd = [sys.executable, str(script_path)] + args\\n    \\n    try:\\n        result = subprocess.run(\\n            cmd,\\n            capture_output=True,\\n            text=True,\\n            timeout=timeout\\n        )\\n        \\n        if result.returncode == 0:\\n            return {\\n                \\\"success\\\": True,\\n                \\\"stdout\\\": result.stdout,\\n                \\\"stderr\\\": result.stderr\\n            }\\n        else:\\n            return {\\n                \\\"success\\\": False,\\n                \\\"returncode\\\": result.returncode,\\n                \\\"stdout\\\": result.stdout,\\n                \\\"stderr\\\": result.stderr\\n            }\\n            \\n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\\n        return {\\n            \\\"success\\\": False,\\n            \\\"error\\\": \\\"timeout\\\",\\n            \\\"timeout_seconds\\\": timeout\\n        }\\n    except Exception as e:\\n        return {\\n            \\\"success\\\": False,\\n            \\\"error\\\": str(e)\\n        }\\n```\\n\\n**Advantages**:\\n- Isolated execution environments\\n- Clear success/failure signals\\n- Timeout protection\\n- Output capture\\n\\n### 1.3 Module Import Integration (For Code Reuse)\\nImport modules from other skills with path management.\\n\\n```python\\n# ✅ Recommended: Dynamic path management with fallbacks\\nimport sys\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\\nworkspace = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'\\n\\ndef import_skill_module(skill_name, module_name):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Import a module from another skill with fallback.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    skill_path = workspace / 'skills' / skill_name / 'scripts'\\n    \\n    if not skill_path.exists():\\n        raise ImportError(f\\\"Skill not found: {skill_name}\\\")\\n    \\n    # Save original path\\n    original_path = sys.path.copy()\\n    \\n    try:\\n        # Add skill path temporarily\\n        sys.path.insert(0, str(skill_path))\\n        \\n        # Import the module\\n        module = __import__(module_name)\\n        return module\\n        \\n    except ImportError as e:\\n        # Fallback: try alternative import methods\\n        print(f\\\"Warning: Could not import {module_name} from {skill_name}: {e}\\\")\\n        return None\\n        \\n    finally:\\n        # Restore original path\\n        sys.path = original_path\\n```\\n\\n**Advantages**:\\n- Direct code reuse\\n- Type checking and IDE support\\n- Efficient for frequent calls\\n\\n## 2. Error Handling Between Skills\\n\\n### 2.1 Graceful Degradation\\nSkills should continue operation even if integration fails.\\n\\n```python\\ndef integrate_with_watchdog(task_description, expected_minutes):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Integrate with watchdog with graceful degradation.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    try:\\n        # Try primary integration method\\n        result = call_watchdog_direct(task_description, expected_minutes)\\n        \\n        if result[\\\"success\\\"]:\\n            return result\\n        \\n        # Fallback to file-based integration\\n        print(\\\"Watchdog direct call failed, using file-based fallback\\\")\\n        return register_with_watchdog_via_file(task_description, expected_minutes)\\n        \\n    except Exception as e:\\n        # Ultimate fallback: log and continue\\n        print(f\\\"All watchdog integration failed: {e}\\\")\\n        emit_incident(\\n            pattern_key=\\\"integration|FAILURE|watchdog|all_methods_failed\\\",\\n            severity=\\\"S3\\\",\\n            description=f\\\"Watchdog integration failed: {e}\\\",\\n            evidence={\\\"task\\\": task_description}\\n        )\\n        return {\\\"success\\\": False, \\\"degraded\\\": True}\\n```\\n\\n### 2.2 Circuit Breakers\\nPrevent cascade failures with circuit breakers.\\n\\n```python\\nclass CircuitBreaker:\\n    def __init__(self, failure_threshold=3, reset_timeout=60):\\n        self.failure_count = 0\\n        self.last_failure = None\\n        self.failure_threshold = failure_threshold\\n        self.reset_timeout = reset_timeout\\n        self.state = \\\"CLOSED\\\"  # CLOSED, OPEN, HALF_OPEN\\n    \\n    def call(self, func, *args, **kwargs):\\n        if self.state == \\\"OPEN\\\":\\n            # Check if timeout has passed\\n            if self.last_failure and (time.time() - self.last_failure) > self.reset_timeout:\\n                self.state = \\\"HALF_OPEN\\\"\\n            else:\\n                raise CircuitBreakerOpen(\\\"Circuit breaker is open\\\")\\n        \\n        try:\\n            result = func(*args, **kwargs)\\n            # Success - reset circuit breaker\\n            if self.state == \\\"HALF_OPEN\\\":\\n                self.state = \\\"CLOSED\\\"\\n            self.failure_count = 0\\n            return result\\n            \\n        except Exception as e:\\n            self.failure_count += 1\\n            self.last_failure = time.time()\\n            \\n            if self.failure_count >= self.failure_threshold:\\n                self.state = \\\"OPEN\\\"\\n            \\n            raise e\\n```\\n\\n### 2.3 Retry Logic\\nImplement retry with exponential backoff.\\n\\n```python\\nimport time\\nimport random\\n\\ndef retry_with_backoff(func, max_retries=3, base_delay=1, max_delay=10):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Retry function with exponential backoff.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    for attempt in range(max_retries + 1):\\n        try:\\n            return func()\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            if attempt == max_retries:\\n                raise e\\n            \\n            # Calculate delay with jitter\\n            delay = min(base_delay * (2 ** attempt), max_delay)\\n            jitter = random.uniform(0, delay * 0.1)\\n            total_delay = delay + jitter\\n            \\n            print(f\\\"Attempt {attempt + 1} failed, retrying in {total_delay:.2f}s: {e}\\\")\\n            time.sleep(total_delay)\\n```\\n\\n## 3. Data Passing and State Management\\n\\n### 3.1 Structured Payloads\\nUse consistent data schemas for integration.\\n\\n```python\\nfrom typing import TypedDict, Optional\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\n\\nclass IntegrationPayload(TypedDict):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Standard payload for skill integration.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    version: str\\n    timestamp: str\\n    source_skill: str\\n    target_skill: str\\n    action: str\\n    payload: dict\\n    metadata: Optional[dict]\\n    correlation_id: Optional[str]\\n\\ndef create_payload(source_skill, target_skill, action, data):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Create standardized integration payload.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    return IntegrationPayload(\\n        version=\\\"1.0\\\",\\n        timestamp=datetime.now().isoformat(),\\n        source_skill=source_skill,\\n        target_skill=target_skill,\\n        action=action,\\n        payload=data,\\n        metadata={\\n            \\\"workspace\\\": str(Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'),\\n            \\\"python_version\\\": sys.version\\n        },\\n        correlation_id=f\\\"corr_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}\\\"\\n    )\\n```\\n\\n### 3.2 State Management\\nManage integration state consistently.\\n\\n```python\\nimport json\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom enum import Enum\\n\\nclass IntegrationState(Enum):\\n    PENDING = \\\"pending\\\"\\n    IN_PROGRESS = \\\"in_progress\\\"\\n    COMPLETED = \\\"completed\\\"\\n    FAILED = \\\"failed\\\"\\n    DEGRADED = \\\"degraded\\\"\\n\\nclass IntegrationStateManager:\\n    def __init__(self, state_file):\\n        self.state_file = Path(state_file)\\n        self.state = self.load_state()\\n    \\n    def load_state(self):\\n        if self.state_file.exists():\\n            with open(self.state_file, 'r') as f:\\n                return json.load(f)\\n        return {\\\"integrations\\\": {}}\\n    \\n    def update_state(self, integration_id, state, details=None):\\n        self.state[\\\"integrations\\\"][integration_id] = {\\n            \\\"state\\\": state.value if isinstance(state, IntegrationState) else state,\\n            \\\"timestamp\\\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\\n            \\\"details\\\": details or {}\\n        }\\n        self.save_state()\\n    \\n    def save_state(self):\\n        with open(self.state_file, 'w') as f:\\n            json.dump(self.state, f, indent=2)\\n```\\n\\n## 4. Integration Testing\\n\\n### 4.1 Test Patterns\\nTest integration points systematically.\\n\\n```python\\nimport pytest\\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\\nclass TestSkillIntegration:\\n    def test_file_based_integration(self, tmp_path):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Test file-based integration.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        test_file = tmp_path / \\\"test_incident.json\\\"\\n        \\n        # Write test data\\n        data = {\\\"test\\\": True}\\n        with open(test_file, 'w') as f:\\n            json.dump(data, f)\\n        \\n        # Verify\\n        assert test_file.exists()\\n        with open(test_file, 'r') as f:\\n            loaded = json.load(f)\\n        assert loaded[\\\"test\\\"] is True\\n    \\n    def test_subprocess_integration(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Test subprocess integration.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        with patch('subprocess.run') as mock_run:\\n            mock_run.return_value.returncode = 0\\n            mock_run.return_value.stdout = \\\"success\\\"\\n            \\n            result = call_skill_script(\\\"/fake/script.py\\\", [\\\"--test\\\"])\\n            \\n            assert result[\\\"success\\\"] is True\\n            mock_run.assert_called_once()\\n    \\n    def test_module_import_fallback(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Test module import with fallback.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        with patch('sys.path.insert'):\\n            with patch('__import__', side_effect=ImportError(\\\"Test error\\\")):\\n                result = import_skill_module(\\\"fake-skill\\\", \\\"fake_module\\\")\\n                \\n                assert result is None  # Should return None on failure\\n```\\n\\n### 4.2 Integration Test Suite\\nCreate comprehensive integration tests.\\n\\n```python\\n# integration_test_suite.py\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nComprehensive integration test suite.\\nRun with: python -m pytest integration_test_suite.py -v\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\ndef test_end_to_end_integration():\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Test complete integration flow.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # 1. Start with skill A\\n    # 2. Integrate with skill B\\n    # 3. Verify data flow\\n    # 4. Check error handling\\n    # 5. Validate final state\\n    pass\\n\\ndef test_error_recovery():\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Test integration error recovery.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # 1. Simulate skill failure\\n    # 2. Verify graceful degradation\\n    # 3. Check incident emission\\n    # 4. Validate circuit breaker\\n    pass\\n\\ndef test_performance_under_load():\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Test integration performance.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # 1. Simulate high load\\n    # 2. Measure response times\\n    # 3. Check for timeouts\\n    # 4. Verify stability\\n    pass\\n```\\n\\n## 5. Monitoring and Observability\\n\\n### 5.1 Integration Metrics\\nTrack integration performance.\\n\\n```python\\nimport time\\nfrom collections import defaultdict\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\\nfrom typing import Dict, List\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass IntegrationMetrics:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Metrics for skill integration.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    call_count: int = 0\\n    success_count: int = 0\\n    failure_count: int = 0\\n    total_duration: float = 0.0\\n    last_call_time: float = 0.0\\n    \\n    @property\\n    def success_rate(self):\\n        if self.call_count == 0:\\n            return 0.0\\n        return self.success_count / self.call_count\\n    \\n    @property\\n    def average_duration(self):\\n        if self.call_count == 0:\\n            return 0.0\\n        return self.total_duration / self.call_count\\n\\nclass IntegrationMonitor:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.metrics: Dict[str, IntegrationMetrics] = defaultdict(IntegrationMetrics)\\n    \\n    def track_call(self, integration_point, duration, success):\\n        metrics = self.metrics[integration_point]\\n        metrics.call_count += 1\\n        metrics.total_duration += duration\\n        metrics.last_call_time = time.time()\\n        \\n        if success:\\n            metrics.success_count += 1\\n        else:\\n            metrics.failure_count += 1\\n    \\n    def get_report(self):\\n        return {\\n            point: {\\n                \\\"call_count\\\": metrics.call_count,\\n                \\\"success_rate\\\": metrics.success_rate,\\n                \\\"average_duration\\\": metrics.average_duration,\\n                \\\"failure_count\\\": metrics.failure_count\\n            }\\n            for point, metrics in self.metrics.items()\\n        }\\n```\\n\\n### 5.2 Health Checks\\nImplement health checks for integrated skills.\\n\\n```python\\ndef check_skill_health(skill_name):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Check if a skill is healthy and available.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    skill_path = workspace / 'skills' / skill_name\\n    \\n    checks = {\\n        \\\"skill_exists\\\": skill_path.exists(),\\n        \\\"has_skill_md\\\": (skill_path / \\\"SKILL.md\\\").exists(),\\n        \\\"has_scripts\\\": (skill_path / \\\"scripts\\\").exists(),\\n    }\\n    \\n    # Try to run a simple test if scripts exist\\n    if checks[\\\"has_scripts\\\"]:\\n        test_script = skill_path / \\\"scripts\\\" / \\\"test_health.py\\\"\\n        if test_script.exists():\\n            try:\\n                result = subprocess.run(\\n                    [sys.executable, str(test_script)],\\n                    capture_output=True,\\n                    timeout=5\\n                )\\n                checks[\\\"health_test_passes\\\"] = result.returncode == 0\\n            except:\\n                checks[\\\"health_test_passes\\\"] = False\\n    \\n    health_status = all(checks.values())\\n    \\n    return {\\n        \\\"healthy\\\": health_status,\\n        \\\"checks\\\": checks,\\n        \\\"skill_path\\\": str(skill_path)\\n    }\\n```\\n\\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\\n\\n### For New Skills:\\n- [ ] Implement file-based integration for incidents\\n- [ ] Add subprocess integration for script calls\\n- [ ] Include module import with fallbacks\\n- [ ] Implement graceful degradation\\n- [ ] Add circuit breaker pattern\\n- [ ] Include retry logic with backoff\\n- [ ] Use structured payloads\\n- [ ] Implement state management\\n- [ ] Create integration tests\\n- [ ] Add health checks\\n- [ ] Document integration points\\n\\n### For Existing Skills:\\n- [ ] Audit current integration patterns\\n- [ ] Add missing error handling\\n- [ ] Implement graceful degradation\\n- [ ] Add circuit breakers where needed\\n- [ ] Create integration tests\\n- [ ] Update documentation\\n\\n## 7. Real-World Examples\\n\\n### Example 1: Tavily Web Search Integration\\n```python\\n# From tavily-web-search/scripts/tavily_integrations.py\\ndef register_with_watchdog(session_id, task_desc, expected_time):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Register search operation with watchdog.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    watchdog_script = workspace / 'skills' / 'agent-watchdog' / 'scripts' / 'watchdog_orchestrator.py'\\n    \\n    if not watchdog_script.exists():\\n        # Graceful degradation\\n        print(\\\"Watchdog not available, continuing without monitoring\\\")\\n        return False\\n    \\n    # Subprocess integration with timeout\\n    result = call_skill_script(watchdog_script, [\\n        \\\"--register\\\",\\n        \\\"--session-id\\\", session_id,\\n        \\\"--task\\\", task_desc,\\n        \\\"--expected-runtime\\\", str(expected_time)\\n    ], timeout=10)\\n    \\n    return result[\\\"success\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n### Example 2: Salesforce Architect ↔ Auditor Integration\\n```python\\n# From salesforce-architect/scripts/auditor_integration.py\\nclass AuditorIntegration:\\n    def __init__(self, project_root):\\n        # Module import integration\\n        self.project_root = Path(project_root)\\n        \\n        # Verify skill exists\\n        CODE_AUDITOR_DIR = workspace / 'skills' / 'salesforce-code-auditor'\\n        if not CODE_AUDITOR_DIR.exists():\\n            raise FileNotFoundError(f\\\"Code auditor skill not found\\\")\\n        \\n        # Dynamic import with fallback\\n        self.auditor_module = self._import_auditor_module()\\n    \\n    def _import_auditor_module(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Import auditor module with fallback.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            sys.path.insert(0, str(CODE_AUDITOR_DIR / 'scripts'))\\n            import auditor_core\\n            return auditor_core\\n        except ImportError:\\n            # Fallback to simulated auditor\\n            print(\\\"Using simulated auditor (real auditor not available)\\\")\\n            return SimulatedAuditor()\\n```\\n\\n## 8. Troubleshooting Guide\\n\\n### Common Issues and Solutions:\\n\\n1. **Skill not found**\\n   - Check skill path exists\\n   - Verify skill directory structure\\n   - Use graceful degradation\\n\\n2. **Import errors**\\n   - Check Python path\\n   - Verify module names\\n   - Implement fallback imports\\n\\n3. **Subprocess timeouts**\\n   - Increase timeout values\\n   - Add retry logic\\n   - Implement circuit breakers\\n\\n4. **File permission errors**\\n   - Check directory permissions\\n   - Use workspace-relative paths\\n   - Implement error recovery\\n\\n5. **Data format mismatches**\\n   - Use structured payloads\\n   - Validate data schemas\\n   - Implement versioning\\n\\n## 9. Conclusion\\n\\nEffective skill integration requires:\\n1. **Multiple integration methods** for flexibility\\n2. **Robust error handling** for reliability\\n3. **Graceful\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-chat\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"length\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1773108323154\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": [\n        {\n          \"type\": \"text\",\n          \"text\": \"Now let me create a summary of real integration examples:\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n          \"id\": \"call_00_cMOUfaKRAQHr8HqjvyuOOpYC\",\n          \"name\": \"write\",\n          \"arguments\": {\n            \"path\": \"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/real_integration_examples.md\",\n            \"content\": \"# Real Integration Examples in OpenClaw Workspace\\n\\n**Date**: 2026-03-09  \\n**Based on Analysis**: Examination of actual skill code and integration patterns\\n\\n## 1. Salesforce Architect ↔ Code Auditor Integration\\n\\n### Location\\n- `salesforce-architect/scripts/auditor_integration.py`\\n- `salesforce-architect/scripts/dod_auditor_validator.py`\\n- `salesforce-architect/INTEGRATION_SUMMARY.md`\\n\\n### Integration Pattern: Module Import + Project Control\\n\\n#### Code Example:\\n```python\\n# From auditor_integration.py\\nimport sys\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\n\\n# Add script directory to path\\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).parent))\\n\\nfrom project_control import ProjectControl\\nfrom state_machine_engine import State, StateMachineEngine\\nfrom dod_validator import DoDValidator\\n\\n# Workspace root\\nWORKSPACE_ROOT = Path(os.environ.get('WORKSPACE', '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace'))\\nCODE_AUDITOR_DIR = WORKSPACE_ROOT / 'skills' / 'salesforce-code-auditor'\\n\\nclass AuditorIntegration:\\n    def __init__(self, project_root):\\n        self.project_root = Path(project_root)\\n        \\n        # Verify code auditor skill exists\\n        if not CODE_AUDITOR_DIR.exists():\\n            raise FileNotFoundError(f\\\"Code auditor skill not found at {CODE_AUDITOR_DIR}\\\")\\n```\\n\\n#### Data Flow:\\n1. **Architect creates audit request** with mode (A, B, C)\\n2. **Automatic project control registration** via `project_control.add_code_audit()`\\n3. **Audit execution** (simulated or real auditor)\\n4. **DoD validation** via `dod_auditor_validator.py`\\n5. **Blocking condition check** based on validation results\\n6. **Project control update** with validation status\\n7. **Incident generation** for failed audits\\n\\n#### Integration Features:\\n- ✅ Automatic project control registration\\n- ✅ Mode-specific audit requests (A, B, C)\\n- ✅ DoD validation integration\\n- ✅ Blocking condition detection\\n- ✅ Incident generation for failures\\n- ✅ Backward compatibility maintained\\n\\n## 2. Error-Learning-Loop Integration\\n\\n### Location\\n- Multiple skills integrate via `.learnings/` directory\\n- Incident files: `.learnings/watchdog_incident_*.json`\\n- Index: `.learnings/INDEX.md`\\n\\n### Integration Pattern: File-Based Event Emission\\n\\n#### Real Incident Example:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"pattern_key\\\": \\\"model|STALL|unknown|no_response|runtime_stuck\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-03-10T00:15:06.568465\\\",\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"d13a23e6-d7e4-4d0f-8d9e-660ebca4a175\\\",\\n  \\\"recovery_level\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"nudge_continue\\\",\\n  \\\"success\\\": true,\\n  \\\"inactivity_seconds\\\": 221.642611,\\n  \\\"evidence\\\": {\\n    \\\"metrics_file\\\": \\\"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/metrics.json\\\",\\n    \\\"registry_file\\\": \\\"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/session_registry.json\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### Integration Points:\\n1. **Agent-Watchdog**: Emits stall incidents\\n2. **Salesforce-Code-Auditor**: Emits audit failures\\n3. **Tavily-Web-Search**: Emits API errors\\n4. **Vector-Memory**: Emits database errors\\n\\n#### Code Example (from salesforce-code-auditor):\\n```python\\n# From generate_reports.py\\nscript_path = WORKSPACE_ROOT / 'skills' / 'error-learning-loop' / 'scripts' / 'emit_incident.py'\\n\\nif os.path.exists(script_path):\\n    subprocess.run([\\n        'python3', script_path,\\n        'salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|validation_failed|security_issues',\\n        'S2',\\n        'salesforce-code-auditor',\\n        'Security validation failed in audit',\\n        f'Found {critical_count} critical issues',\\n        '--type', 'SECURITY'\\n    ])\\n```\\n\\n## 3. Agent-Watchdog Integration\\n\\n### Location\\n- `tavily-web-search/scripts/tavily_integrations.py`\\n- `vector-memory/scripts/watchdog_integration.py`\\n- `agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py`\\n\\n### Integration Pattern: Subprocess Registration\\n\\n#### Code Example (Tavily):\\n```python\\n# From tavily_integrations.py\\ndef register_with_watchdog(session_id: str, run_id: str, task_desc: str, \\n                          expected_time: int, model: str = \\\"tavily-search\\\",\\n                          runtime_type: str = \\\"search\\\") -> bool:\\n    \\n    # Check if watchdog skill exists\\n    watchdog_script = Path.home() / \\\".openclaw\\\" / \\\"workspace\\\" / \\\"skills\\\" / \\\"agent-watchdog\\\"\\n    \\n    if not watchdog_script.exists():\\n        print(f\\\"[WATCHDOG] Watchdog skill not found at {watchdog_script}\\\")\\n        return False\\n    \\n    # Try to use watchdog orchestrator script\\n    orchestrator_path = watchdog_script / \\\"scripts\\\" / \\\"watchdog_orchestrator.py\\\"\\n    \\n    if orchestrator_path.exists():\\n        cmd = [\\n            \\\"python3\\\", str(orchestrator_path),\\n            \\\"--register\\\",\\n            \\\"--session-id\\\", session_id,\\n            \\\"--run-id\\\", run_id,\\n            \\\"--task\\\", task_desc,\\n            \\\"--expected-runtime\\\", str(expected_time),\\n            \\\"--model\\\", model,\\n            \\\"--runtime-type\\\", runtime_type\\n        ]\\n        \\n        try:\\n            result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10)\\n            return result.returncode == 0\\n        except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\\n            print(\\\"[WATCHDOG] Registration timeout\\\")\\n            return False\\n```\\n\\n#### Code Example (Vector Memory):\\n```python\\n# From vector-memory/scripts/watchdog_integration.py\\ndef register_with_watchdog(task_description, expected_runtime_minutes, \\n                          model=\\\"custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-chat\\\", \\n                          runtime_type=\\\"subagent\\\"):\\n    \\n    if not WATCHDOG_SCRIPT.exists():\\n        print(f\\\"[WATCHDOG] Warning: Watchdog script not found at {WATCHDOG_SCRIPT}\\\")\\n        return None, None\\n    \\n    # Generate unique IDs\\n    session_id = f\\\"memory_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}_{uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]}\\\"\\n    run_id = f\\\"run_{uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]}\\\"\\n    \\n    # Build command\\n    cmd = [\\n        sys.executable, str(WATCHDOG_SCRIPT),\\n        \\\"--register\\\",\\n        \\\"--session-id\\\", session_id,\\n        \\\"--run-id\\\", run_id,\\n        \\\"--task\\\", task_description,\\n        \\\"--expected-runtime\\\", str(expected_runtime_minutes),\\n        \\\"--model\\\", model,\\n        \\\"--runtime-type\\\", runtime_type\\n    ]\\n```\\n\\n## 4. Tavily Web Search Ecosystem Integration\\n\\n### Location\\n- `tavily-web-search/scripts/tavily_integrations.py`\\n- `tavily-web-search/config/tavily_config.json`\\n\\n### Integration Pattern: Comprehensive Ecosystem Integration\\n\\n#### Configuration Example:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"watchdog\\\": {\\n    \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n    \\\"long_search_threshold_seconds\\\": 30,\\n    \\\"registration_timeout_seconds\\\": 10\\n  },\\n  \\\"error_handling\\\": {\\n    \\\"max_retries\\\": 3,\\n    \\\"retry_delay_seconds\\\": 2,\\n    \\\"exponential_backoff\\\": true,\\n    \\\"rate_limit_wait_seconds\\\": 60,\\n    \\\"degraded_mode_enabled\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"janitor\\\": {\\n    \\\"cache_cleanup_days\\\": 7,\\n    \\\"max_cache_size_mb\\\": 100\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### Integration Features:\\n1. **Watchdog Registration**: Automatic for searches >30 seconds\\n2. **Error Learning Loop**: Structured incident emission\\n3. **Workspace Janitor**: Cache cleanup integration\\n4. **Graceful Degradation**: Fallback to cached results\\n\\n## 5. Workspace Janitor Integration\\n\\n### Location\\n- Multiple skills create temp files with cleanup patterns\\n- `tavily-web-search` config includes janitor settings\\n\\n### Integration Pattern: File Pattern Cleanup\\n\\n#### Temp File Patterns:\\n- `*.tmp` - Temporary files\\n- `temp_*` - Temporary data\\n- `*_cache.json` - Cache files\\n- `search_results_*.json` - Search results\\n\\n#### Cleanup Configuration:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"janitor\\\": {\\n    \\\"cache_cleanup_days\\\": 7,\\n    \\\"max_cache_size_mb\\\": 100,\\n    \\\"patterns\\\": [\\n      \\\"*.tmp\\\",\\n      \\\"temp_*\\\", \\n      \\\"*_cache.json\\\",\\n      \\\"search_results_*.json\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## 6. Vector Memory Integration\\n\\n### Location\\n- `vector-memory/scripts/watchdog_integration.py`\\n- `vector-memory/scripts/test_incident_emission.py`\\n\\n### Integration Pattern: Watchdog + Error-Loop\\n\\n#### Test Example:\\n```python\\n# From test_incident_emission.py\\ndef test_emit_incident():\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Test incident emission to error-learning-loop.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    error_loop_script = WORKSPACE / 'skills' / 'error-learning-loop' / 'scripts' / 'emit_incident.py'\\n    \\n    if not error_loop_script.exists():\\n        print(\\\"Error-learning-loop script not found, skipping test\\\")\\n        return\\n    \\n    # Test incident emission\\n    cmd = [\\n        sys.executable, str(error_loop_script),\\n        'memory|TEST|incident_emission|success',\\n        'S4',\\n        'vector-memory',\\n        'Test incident emission',\\n        'This is a test incident from vector-memory',\\n        '--type', 'TEST'\\n    ]\\n```\\n\\n## 7. Integration Success Metrics\\n\\n### Based on Analysis:\\n\\n| Integration Type | Success Rate | Reliability | Examples |\\n|-----------------|--------------|-------------|----------|\\n| File-Based | 100% | High | Error-learning-loop incidents |\\n| Subprocess | 90% | Medium-High | Watchdog registration |\\n| Module Import | 85% | Medium | Salesforce architect-auditor |\\n| Event-Driven | 95% | High | Watchdog stall detection |\\n\\n### Key Success Factors:\\n1. **File-based integration**: Most reliable (100% success)\\n2. **Graceful degradation**: Skills continue when integration fails\\n3. **Error emission**: Failed integrations generate incidents\\n4. **Health checks**: Skills verify other skills before integration\\n\\n## 8. Lessons Learned\\n\\n### What Works Well:\\n1. **File-based integration** is the most reliable pattern\\n2. **Graceful degradation** prevents cascade failures\\n3. **Structured incident emission** enables learning\\n4. **Configuration-driven integration** is maintainable\\n\\n### Areas for Improvement:\\n1. **Standardized integration protocol** needed\\n2. **Skill registry** for dynamic discovery\\n3. **Better error recovery** between skills\\n4. **Integration testing framework**\\n\\n## 9. Recommendations for Future Skills\\n\\n### Must-Have Integration Points:\\n1. **Error-learning-loop**: Emit incidents for failures\\n2. **Agent-watchdog**: Register long-running tasks\\n3. **Workspace janitor**: Follow cleanup patterns\\n4. **File-based communication**: Use shared directories\\n\\n### Implementation Checklist:\\n- [ ] Implement file-based incident emission\\n- [ ] Add watchdog registration for long tasks\\n- [ ] Follow janitor cleanup patterns\\n- [ ] Use graceful degradation\\n- [ ] Create integration tests\\n- [ ] Document integration points\\n\\n## 10. Conclusion\\n\\nReal integration examples show that OpenClaw skills successfully integrate using:\\n1. **Multiple patterns**: File-based, subprocess, module import\\n2. **Ecosystem integration**: Watchdog, error-loop, janitor\\n3. **Graceful degradation**: Skills continue when integration fails\\n4. **Learning from failures**: Incidents feed into error-learning-loop\\n\\nThe most successful integrations use **file-based communication** with **graceful degradation** and **structured error handling**.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"provider\": \"custom-api-deepseek-com\",\n      \"model\": \"deepseek-chat\",\n      \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n      \"timestamp\": 1773108486330\n    }\n  ],\n  \"truncated\": false,\n  \"droppedMessages\": false,\n  \"contentTruncated\": false,\n  \"contentRedacted\": false,\n  \"bytes\": 30411\n}"}],"details":{"sessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:c44a34cb-1719-4046-a79f-39a9217b5fe7","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a best practices document based on my findings:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_04MsecCzt5HhClFQPn4PKE8g","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skill_integration_best_practices.md","content":"# OpenClaw Skill Integration Best Practices\n\n**Version**: 1.0  \n**Date**: 2026-03-09  \n**Based on Research**: Integration Procedures Investigation\n\n## 1. Integration Patterns\n\n### 1.1 File-Based Integration (Recommended)\nUse shared files for loose coupling and reliability.\n\n```python\n# ✅ Recommended: Write structured data to shared directories\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nworkspace = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'\n\ndef emit_incident(pattern_key, severity, description, evidence):\n    \"\"\"Emit incident to error-learning-loop.\"\"\"\n    incident = {\n        \"pattern_key\": pattern_key,\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n        \"severity\": severity,\n        \"description\": description,\n        \"evidence\": evidence,\n        \"source_skill\": __name__\n    }\n    \n    # Write to .learnings directory\n    incident_file = workspace / '.learnings' / f'incident_{datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\")}.json'\n    \n    with open(incident_file, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(incident, f, indent=2)\n    \n    return incident_file\n```\n\n**Advantages**:\n- Loose coupling between skills\n- Asynchronous processing\n- Reliable (file system is stable)\n- Easy to debug (files are inspectable)\n\n### 1.2 Subprocess Integration (For Script Execution)\nCall other skill scripts via subprocess with proper error handling.\n\n```python\n# ✅ Recommended: Subprocess with timeout and error handling\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ndef call_skill_script(script_path, args, timeout=30):\n    \"\"\"Call a skill script with proper error handling.\"\"\"\n    script_path = Path(script_path)\n    \n    if not script_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Script not found: {script_path}\")\n    \n    cmd = [sys.executable, str(script_path)] + args\n    \n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            cmd,\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n            timeout=timeout\n        )\n        \n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            return {\n                \"success\": True,\n                \"stdout\": result.stdout,\n                \"stderr\": result.stderr\n            }\n        else:\n            return {\n                \"success\": False,\n                \"returncode\": result.returncode,\n                \"stdout\": result.stdout,\n                \"stderr\": result.stderr\n            }\n            \n    except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"error\": \"timeout\",\n            \"timeout_seconds\": timeout\n        }\n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"error\": str(e)\n        }\n```\n\n**Advantages**:\n- Isolated execution environments\n- Clear success/failure signals\n- Timeout protection\n- Output capture\n\n### 1.3 Module Import Integration (For Code Reuse)\nImport modules from other skills with path management.\n\n```python\n# ✅ Recommended: Dynamic path management with fallbacks\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nworkspace = Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'\n\ndef import_skill_module(skill_name, module_name):\n    \"\"\"Import a module from another skill with fallback.\"\"\"\n    skill_path = workspace / 'skills' / skill_name / 'scripts'\n    \n    if not skill_path.exists():\n        raise ImportError(f\"Skill not found: {skill_name}\")\n    \n    # Save original path\n    original_path = sys.path.copy()\n    \n    try:\n        # Add skill path temporarily\n        sys.path.insert(0, str(skill_path))\n        \n        # Import the module\n        module = __import__(module_name)\n        return module\n        \n    except ImportError as e:\n        # Fallback: try alternative import methods\n        print(f\"Warning: Could not import {module_name} from {skill_name}: {e}\")\n        return None\n        \n    finally:\n        # Restore original path\n        sys.path = original_path\n```\n\n**Advantages**:\n- Direct code reuse\n- Type checking and IDE support\n- Efficient for frequent calls\n\n## 2. Error Handling Between Skills\n\n### 2.1 Graceful Degradation\nSkills should continue operation even if integration fails.\n\n```python\ndef integrate_with_watchdog(task_description, expected_minutes):\n    \"\"\"Integrate with watchdog with graceful degradation.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        # Try primary integration method\n        result = call_watchdog_direct(task_description, expected_minutes)\n        \n        if result[\"success\"]:\n            return result\n        \n        # Fallback to file-based integration\n        print(\"Watchdog direct call failed, using file-based fallback\")\n        return register_with_watchdog_via_file(task_description, expected_minutes)\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        # Ultimate fallback: log and continue\n        print(f\"All watchdog integration failed: {e}\")\n        emit_incident(\n            pattern_key=\"integration|FAILURE|watchdog|all_methods_failed\",\n            severity=\"S3\",\n            description=f\"Watchdog integration failed: {e}\",\n            evidence={\"task\": task_description}\n        )\n        return {\"success\": False, \"degraded\": True}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Circuit Breakers\nPrevent cascade failures with circuit breakers.\n\n```python\nclass CircuitBreaker:\n    def __init__(self, failure_threshold=3, reset_timeout=60):\n        self.failure_count = 0\n        self.last_failure = None\n        self.failure_threshold = failure_threshold\n        self.reset_timeout = reset_timeout\n        self.state = \"CLOSED\"  # CLOSED, OPEN, HALF_OPEN\n    \n    def call(self, func, *args, **kwargs):\n        if self.state == \"OPEN\":\n            # Check if timeout has passed\n            if self.last_failure and (time.time() - self.last_failure) > self.reset_timeout:\n                self.state = \"HALF_OPEN\"\n            else:\n                raise CircuitBreakerOpen(\"Circuit breaker is open\")\n        \n        try:\n            result = func(*args, **kwargs)\n            # Success - reset circuit breaker\n            if self.state == \"HALF_OPEN\":\n                self.state = \"CLOSED\"\n            self.failure_count = 0\n            return result\n            \n        except Exception as e:\n            self.failure_count += 1\n            self.last_failure = time.time()\n            \n            if self.failure_count >= self.failure_threshold:\n                self.state = \"OPEN\"\n            \n            raise e\n```\n\n### 2.3 Retry Logic\nImplement retry with exponential backoff.\n\n```python\nimport time\nimport random\n\ndef retry_with_backoff(func, max_retries=3, base_delay=1, max_delay=10):\n    \"\"\"Retry function with exponential backoff.\"\"\"\n    for attempt in range(max_retries + 1):\n        try:\n            return func()\n        except Exception as e:\n            if attempt == max_retries:\n                raise e\n            \n            # Calculate delay with jitter\n            delay = min(base_delay * (2 ** attempt), max_delay)\n            jitter = random.uniform(0, delay * 0.1)\n            total_delay = delay + jitter\n            \n            print(f\"Attempt {attempt + 1} failed, retrying in {total_delay:.2f}s: {e}\")\n            time.sleep(total_delay)\n```\n\n## 3. Data Passing and State Management\n\n### 3.1 Structured Payloads\nUse consistent data schemas for integration.\n\n```python\nfrom typing import TypedDict, Optional\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nclass IntegrationPayload(TypedDict):\n    \"\"\"Standard payload for skill integration.\"\"\"\n    version: str\n    timestamp: str\n    source_skill: str\n    target_skill: str\n    action: str\n    payload: dict\n    metadata: Optional[dict]\n    correlation_id: Optional[str]\n\ndef create_payload(source_skill, target_skill, action, data):\n    \"\"\"Create standardized integration payload.\"\"\"\n    return IntegrationPayload(\n        version=\"1.0\",\n        timestamp=datetime.now().isoformat(),\n        source_skill=source_skill,\n        target_skill=target_skill,\n        action=action,\n        payload=data,\n        metadata={\n            \"workspace\": str(Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'),\n            \"python_version\": sys.version\n        },\n        correlation_id=f\"corr_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}\"\n    )\n```\n\n### 3.2 State Management\nManage integration state consistently.\n\n```python\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom enum import Enum\n\nclass IntegrationState(Enum):\n    PENDING = \"pending\"\n    IN_PROGRESS = \"in_progress\"\n    COMPLETED = \"completed\"\n    FAILED = \"failed\"\n    DEGRADED = \"degraded\"\n\nclass IntegrationStateManager:\n    def __init__(self, state_file):\n        self.state_file = Path(state_file)\n        self.state = self.load_state()\n    \n    def load_state(self):\n        if self.state_file.exists():\n            with open(self.state_file, 'r') as f:\n                return json.load(f)\n        return {\"integrations\": {}}\n    \n    def update_state(self, integration_id, state, details=None):\n        self.state[\"integrations\"][integration_id] = {\n            \"state\": state.value if isinstance(state, IntegrationState) else state,\n            \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n            \"details\": details or {}\n        }\n        self.save_state()\n    \n    def save_state(self):\n        with open(self.state_file, 'w') as f:\n            json.dump(self.state, f, indent=2)\n```\n\n## 4. Integration Testing\n\n### 4.1 Test Patterns\nTest integration points systematically.\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nclass TestSkillIntegration:\n    def test_file_based_integration(self, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test file-based integration.\"\"\"\n        test_file = tmp_path / \"test_incident.json\"\n        \n        # Write test data\n        data = {\"test\": True}\n        with open(test_file, 'w') as f:\n            json.dump(data, f)\n        \n        # Verify\n        assert test_file.exists()\n        with open(test_file, 'r') as f:\n            loaded = json.load(f)\n        assert loaded[\"test\"] is True\n    \n    def test_subprocess_integration(self):\n        \"\"\"Test subprocess integration.\"\"\"\n        with patch('subprocess.run') as mock_run:\n            mock_run.return_value.returncode = 0\n            mock_run.return_value.stdout = \"success\"\n            \n            result = call_skill_script(\"/fake/script.py\", [\"--test\"])\n            \n            assert result[\"success\"] is True\n            mock_run.assert_called_once()\n    \n    def test_module_import_fallback(self):\n        \"\"\"Test module import with fallback.\"\"\"\n        with patch('sys.path.insert'):\n            with patch('__import__', side_effect=ImportError(\"Test error\")):\n                result = import_skill_module(\"fake-skill\", \"fake_module\")\n                \n                assert result is None  # Should return None on failure\n```\n\n### 4.2 Integration Test Suite\nCreate comprehensive integration tests.\n\n```python\n# integration_test_suite.py\n\"\"\"\nComprehensive integration test suite.\nRun with: python -m pytest integration_test_suite.py -v\n\"\"\"\n\ndef test_end_to_end_integration():\n    \"\"\"Test complete integration flow.\"\"\"\n    # 1. Start with skill A\n    # 2. Integrate with skill B\n    # 3. Verify data flow\n    # 4. Check error handling\n    # 5. Validate final state\n    pass\n\ndef test_error_recovery():\n    \"\"\"Test integration error recovery.\"\"\"\n    # 1. Simulate skill failure\n    # 2. Verify graceful degradation\n    # 3. Check incident emission\n    # 4. Validate circuit breaker\n    pass\n\ndef test_performance_under_load():\n    \"\"\"Test integration performance.\"\"\"\n    # 1. Simulate high load\n    # 2. Measure response times\n    # 3. Check for timeouts\n    # 4. Verify stability\n    pass\n```\n\n## 5. Monitoring and Observability\n\n### 5.1 Integration Metrics\nTrack integration performance.\n\n```python\nimport time\nfrom collections import defaultdict\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Dict, List\n\n@dataclass\nclass IntegrationMetrics:\n    \"\"\"Metrics for skill integration.\"\"\"\n    call_count: int = 0\n    success_count: int = 0\n    failure_count: int = 0\n    total_duration: float = 0.0\n    last_call_time: float = 0.0\n    \n    @property\n    def success_rate(self):\n        if self.call_count == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return self.success_count / self.call_count\n    \n    @property\n    def average_duration(self):\n        if self.call_count == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return self.total_duration / self.call_count\n\nclass IntegrationMonitor:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.metrics: Dict[str, IntegrationMetrics] = defaultdict(IntegrationMetrics)\n    \n    def track_call(self, integration_point, duration, success):\n        metrics = self.metrics[integration_point]\n        metrics.call_count += 1\n        metrics.total_duration += duration\n        metrics.last_call_time = time.time()\n        \n        if success:\n            metrics.success_count += 1\n        else:\n            metrics.failure_count += 1\n    \n    def get_report(self):\n        return {\n            point: {\n                \"call_count\": metrics.call_count,\n                \"success_rate\": metrics.success_rate,\n                \"average_duration\": metrics.average_duration,\n                \"failure_count\": metrics.failure_count\n            }\n            for point, metrics in self.metrics.items()\n        }\n```\n\n### 5.2 Health Checks\nImplement health checks for integrated skills.\n\n```python\ndef check_skill_health(skill_name):\n    \"\"\"Check if a skill is healthy and available.\"\"\"\n    skill_path = workspace / 'skills' / skill_name\n    \n    checks = {\n        \"skill_exists\": skill_path.exists(),\n        \"has_skill_md\": (skill_path / \"SKILL.md\").exists(),\n        \"has_scripts\": (skill_path / \"scripts\").exists(),\n    }\n    \n    # Try to run a simple test if scripts exist\n    if checks[\"has_scripts\"]:\n        test_script = skill_path / \"scripts\" / \"test_health.py\"\n        if test_script.exists():\n            try:\n                result = subprocess.run(\n                    [sys.executable, str(test_script)],\n                    capture_output=True,\n                    timeout=5\n                )\n                checks[\"health_test_passes\"] = result.returncode == 0\n            except:\n                checks[\"health_test_passes\"] = False\n    \n    health_status = all(checks.values())\n    \n    return {\n        \"healthy\": health_status,\n        \"checks\": checks,\n        \"skill_path\": str(skill_path)\n    }\n```\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n### For New Skills:\n- [ ] Implement file-based integration for incidents\n- [ ] Add subprocess integration for script calls\n- [ ] Include module import with fallbacks\n- [ ] Implement graceful degradation\n- [ ] Add circuit breaker pattern\n- [ ] Include retry logic with backoff\n- [ ] Use structured payloads\n- [ ] Implement state management\n- [ ] Create integration tests\n- [ ] Add health checks\n- [ ] Document integration points\n\n### For Existing Skills:\n- [ ] Audit current integration patterns\n- [ ] Add missing error handling\n- [ ] Implement graceful degradation\n- [ ] Add circuit breakers where needed\n- [ ] Create integration tests\n- [ ] Update documentation\n\n## 7. Real-World Examples\n\n### Example 1: Tavily Web Search Integration\n```python\n# From tavily-web-search/scripts/tavily_integrations.py\ndef register_with_watchdog(session_id, task_desc, expected_time):\n    \"\"\"Register search operation with watchdog.\"\"\"\n    watchdog_script = workspace / 'skills' / 'agent-watchdog' / 'scripts' / 'watchdog_orchestrator.py'\n    \n    if not watchdog_script.exists():\n        # Graceful degradation\n        print(\"Watchdog not available, continuing without monitoring\")\n        return False\n    \n    # Subprocess integration with timeout\n    result = call_skill_script(watchdog_script, [\n        \"--register\",\n        \"--session-id\", session_id,\n        \"--task\", task_desc,\n        \"--expected-runtime\", str(expected_time)\n    ], timeout=10)\n    \n    return result[\"success\"]\n```\n\n### Example 2: Salesforce Architect ↔ Auditor Integration\n```python\n# From salesforce-architect/scripts/auditor_integration.py\nclass AuditorIntegration:\n    def __init__(self, project_root):\n        # Module import integration\n        self.project_root = Path(project_root)\n        \n        # Verify skill exists\n        CODE_AUDITOR_DIR = workspace / 'skills' / 'salesforce-code-auditor'\n        if not CODE_AUDITOR_DIR.exists():\n            raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Code auditor skill not found\")\n        \n        # Dynamic import with fallback\n        self.auditor_module = self._import_auditor_module()\n    \n    def _import_auditor_module(self):\n        \"\"\"Import auditor module with fallback.\"\"\"\n        try:\n            sys.path.insert(0, str(CODE_AUDITOR_DIR / 'scripts'))\n            import auditor_core\n            return auditor_core\n        except ImportError:\n            # Fallback to simulated auditor\n            print(\"Using simulated auditor (real auditor not available)\")\n            return SimulatedAuditor()\n```\n\n## 8. Troubleshooting Guide\n\n### Common Issues and Solutions:\n\n1. **Skill not found**\n   - Check skill path exists\n   - Verify skill directory structure\n   - Use graceful degradation\n\n2. **Import errors**\n   - Check Python path\n   - Verify module names\n   - Implement fallback imports\n\n3. **Subprocess timeouts**\n   - Increase timeout values\n   - Add retry logic\n   - Implement circuit breakers\n\n4. **File permission errors**\n   - Check directory permissions\n   - Use workspace-relative paths\n   - Implement error recovery\n\n5. **Data format mismatches**\n   - Use structured payloads\n   - Validate data schemas\n   - Implement versioning\n\n## 9. Conclusion\n\nEffective skill integration requires:\n1. **Multiple integration methods** for flexibility\n2. **Robust error handling** for reliability\n3. **Graceful"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","stopReason":"length","timestamp":1773108323154},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a summary of real integration examples:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cMOUfaKRAQHr8HqjvyuOOpYC","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/real_integration_examples.md","content":"# Real Integration Examples in OpenClaw Workspace\n\n**Date**: 2026-03-09  \n**Based on Analysis**: Examination of actual skill code and integration patterns\n\n## 1. Salesforce Architect ↔ Code Auditor Integration\n\n### Location\n- `salesforce-architect/scripts/auditor_integration.py`\n- `salesforce-architect/scripts/dod_auditor_validator.py`\n- `salesforce-architect/INTEGRATION_SUMMARY.md`\n\n### Integration Pattern: Module Import + Project Control\n\n#### Code Example:\n```python\n# From auditor_integration.py\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add script directory to path\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path(__file__).parent))\n\nfrom project_control import ProjectControl\nfrom state_machine_engine import State, StateMachineEngine\nfrom dod_validator import DoDValidator\n\n# Workspace root\nWORKSPACE_ROOT = Path(os.environ.get('WORKSPACE', '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace'))\nCODE_AUDITOR_DIR = WORKSPACE_ROOT / 'skills' / 'salesforce-code-auditor'\n\nclass AuditorIntegration:\n    def __init__(self, project_root):\n        self.project_root = Path(project_root)\n        \n        # Verify code auditor skill exists\n        if not CODE_AUDITOR_DIR.exists():\n            raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Code auditor skill not found at {CODE_AUDITOR_DIR}\")\n```\n\n#### Data Flow:\n1. **Architect creates audit request** with mode (A, B, C)\n2. **Automatic project control registration** via `project_control.add_code_audit()`\n3. **Audit execution** (simulated or real auditor)\n4. **DoD validation** via `dod_auditor_validator.py`\n5. **Blocking condition check** based on validation results\n6. **Project control update** with validation status\n7. **Incident generation** for failed audits\n\n#### Integration Features:\n- ✅ Automatic project control registration\n- ✅ Mode-specific audit requests (A, B, C)\n- ✅ DoD validation integration\n- ✅ Blocking condition detection\n- ✅ Incident generation for failures\n- ✅ Backward compatibility maintained\n\n## 2. Error-Learning-Loop Integration\n\n### Location\n- Multiple skills integrate via `.learnings/` directory\n- Incident files: `.learnings/watchdog_incident_*.json`\n- Index: `.learnings/INDEX.md`\n\n### Integration Pattern: File-Based Event Emission\n\n#### Real Incident Example:\n```json\n{\n  \"pattern_key\": \"model|STALL|unknown|no_response|runtime_stuck\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-10T00:15:06.568465\",\n  \"session_id\": \"d13a23e6-d7e4-4d0f-8d9e-660ebca4a175\",\n  \"recovery_level\": 1,\n  \"action\": \"nudge_continue\",\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"inactivity_seconds\": 221.642611,\n  \"evidence\": {\n    \"metrics_file\": \"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/metrics.json\",\n    \"registry_file\": \"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/session_registry.json\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### Integration Points:\n1. **Agent-Watchdog**: Emits stall incidents\n2. **Salesforce-Code-Auditor**: Emits audit failures\n3. **Tavily-Web-Search**: Emits API errors\n4. **Vector-Memory**: Emits database errors\n\n#### Code Example (from salesforce-code-auditor):\n```python\n# From generate_reports.py\nscript_path = WORKSPACE_ROOT / 'skills' / 'error-learning-loop' / 'scripts' / 'emit_incident.py'\n\nif os.path.exists(script_path):\n    subprocess.run([\n        'python3', script_path,\n        'salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|validation_failed|security_issues',\n        'S2',\n        'salesforce-code-auditor',\n        'Security validation failed in audit',\n        f'Found {critical_count} critical issues',\n        '--type', 'SECURITY'\n    ])\n```\n\n## 3. Agent-Watchdog Integration\n\n### Location\n- `tavily-web-search/scripts/tavily_integrations.py`\n- `vector-memory/scripts/watchdog_integration.py`\n- `agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_orchestrator.py`\n\n### Integration Pattern: Subprocess Registration\n\n#### Code Example (Tavily):\n```python\n# From tavily_integrations.py\ndef register_with_watchdog(session_id: str, run_id: str, task_desc: str, \n                          expected_time: int, model: str = \"tavily-search\",\n                          runtime_type: str = \"search\") -> bool:\n    \n    # Check if watchdog skill exists\n    watchdog_script = Path.home() / \".openclaw\" / \"workspace\" / \"skills\" / \"agent-watchdog\"\n    \n    if not watchdog_script.exists():\n        print(f\"[WATCHDOG] Watchdog skill not found at {watchdog_script}\")\n        return False\n    \n    # Try to use watchdog orchestrator script\n    orchestrator_path = watchdog_script / \"scripts\" / \"watchdog_orchestrator.py\"\n    \n    if orchestrator_path.exists():\n        cmd = [\n            \"python3\", str(orchestrator_path),\n            \"--register\",\n            \"--session-id\", session_id,\n            \"--run-id\", run_id,\n            \"--task\", task_desc,\n            \"--expected-runtime\", str(expected_time),\n            \"--model\", model,\n            \"--runtime-type\", runtime_type\n        ]\n        \n        try:\n            result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10)\n            return result.returncode == 0\n        except subprocess.TimeoutExpired:\n            print(\"[WATCHDOG] Registration timeout\")\n            return False\n```\n\n#### Code Example (Vector Memory):\n```python\n# From vector-memory/scripts/watchdog_integration.py\ndef register_with_watchdog(task_description, expected_runtime_minutes, \n                          model=\"custom-api-deepseek-com/deepseek-chat\", \n                          runtime_type=\"subagent\"):\n    \n    if not WATCHDOG_SCRIPT.exists():\n        print(f\"[WATCHDOG] Warning: Watchdog script not found at {WATCHDOG_SCRIPT}\")\n        return None, None\n    \n    # Generate unique IDs\n    session_id = f\"memory_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}_{uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]}\"\n    run_id = f\"run_{uuid.uuid4().hex[:8]}\"\n    \n    # Build command\n    cmd = [\n        sys.executable, str(WATCHDOG_SCRIPT),\n        \"--register\",\n        \"--session-id\", session_id,\n        \"--run-id\", run_id,\n        \"--task\", task_description,\n        \"--expected-runtime\", str(expected_runtime_minutes),\n        \"--model\", model,\n        \"--runtime-type\", runtime_type\n    ]\n```\n\n## 4. Tavily Web Search Ecosystem Integration\n\n### Location\n- `tavily-web-search/scripts/tavily_integrations.py`\n- `tavily-web-search/config/tavily_config.json`\n\n### Integration Pattern: Comprehensive Ecosystem Integration\n\n#### Configuration Example:\n```json\n{\n  \"watchdog\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"long_search_threshold_seconds\": 30,\n    \"registration_timeout_seconds\": 10\n  },\n  \"error_handling\": {\n    \"max_retries\": 3,\n    \"retry_delay_seconds\": 2,\n    \"exponential_backoff\": true,\n    \"rate_limit_wait_seconds\": 60,\n    \"degraded_mode_enabled\": true\n  },\n  \"janitor\": {\n    \"cache_cleanup_days\": 7,\n    \"max_cache_size_mb\": 100\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### Integration Features:\n1. **Watchdog Registration**: Automatic for searches >30 seconds\n2. **Error Learning Loop**: Structured incident emission\n3. **Workspace Janitor**: Cache cleanup integration\n4. **Graceful Degradation**: Fallback to cached results\n\n## 5. Workspace Janitor Integration\n\n### Location\n- Multiple skills create temp files with cleanup patterns\n- `tavily-web-search` config includes janitor settings\n\n### Integration Pattern: File Pattern Cleanup\n\n#### Temp File Patterns:\n- `*.tmp` - Temporary files\n- `temp_*` - Temporary data\n- `*_cache.json` - Cache files\n- `search_results_*.json` - Search results\n\n#### Cleanup Configuration:\n```json\n{\n  \"janitor\": {\n    \"cache_cleanup_days\": 7,\n    \"max_cache_size_mb\": 100,\n    \"patterns\": [\n      \"*.tmp\",\n      \"temp_*\", \n      \"*_cache.json\",\n      \"search_results_*.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## 6. Vector Memory Integration\n\n### Location\n- `vector-memory/scripts/watchdog_integration.py`\n- `vector-memory/scripts/test_incident_emission.py`\n\n### Integration Pattern: Watchdog + Error-Loop\n\n#### Test Example:\n```python\n# From test_incident_emission.py\ndef test_emit_incident():\n    \"\"\"Test incident emission to error-learning-loop.\"\"\"\n    error_loop_script = WORKSPACE / 'skills' / 'error-learning-loop' / 'scripts' / 'emit_incident.py'\n    \n    if not error_loop_script.exists():\n        print(\"Error-learning-loop script not found, skipping test\")\n        return\n    \n    # Test incident emission\n    cmd = [\n        sys.executable, str(error_loop_script),\n        'memory|TEST|incident_emission|success',\n        'S4',\n        'vector-memory',\n        'Test incident emission',\n        'This is a test incident from vector-memory',\n        '--type', 'TEST'\n    ]\n```\n\n## 7. Integration Success Metrics\n\n### Based on Analysis:\n\n| Integration Type | Success Rate | Reliability | Examples |\n|-----------------|--------------|-------------|----------|\n| File-Based | 100% | High | Error-learning-loop incidents |\n| Subprocess | 90% | Medium-High | Watchdog registration |\n| Module Import | 85% | Medium | Salesforce architect-auditor |\n| Event-Driven | 95% | High | Watchdog stall detection |\n\n### Key Success Factors:\n1. **File-based integration**: Most reliable (100% success)\n2. **Graceful degradation**: Skills continue when integration fails\n3. **Error emission**: Failed integrations generate incidents\n4. **Health checks**: Skills verify other skills before integration\n\n## 8. Lessons Learned\n\n### What Works Well:\n1. **File-based integration** is the most reliable pattern\n2. **Graceful degradation** prevents cascade failures\n3. **Structured incident emission** enables learning\n4. **Configuration-driven integration** is maintainable\n\n### Areas for Improvement:\n1. **Standardized integration protocol** needed\n2. **Skill registry** for dynamic discovery\n3. **Better error recovery** between skills\n4. **Integration testing framework**\n\n## 9. Recommendations for Future Skills\n\n### Must-Have Integration Points:\n1. **Error-learning-loop**: Emit incidents for failures\n2. **Agent-watchdog**: Register long-running tasks\n3. **Workspace janitor**: Follow cleanup patterns\n4. **File-based communication**: Use shared directories\n\n### Implementation Checklist:\n- [ ] Implement file-based incident emission\n- [ ] Add watchdog registration for long tasks\n- [ ] Follow janitor cleanup patterns\n- [ ] Use graceful degradation\n- [ ] Create integration tests\n- [ ] Document integration points\n\n## 10. Conclusion\n\nReal integration examples show that OpenClaw skills successfully integrate using:\n1. **Multiple patterns**: File-based, subprocess, module import\n2. **Ecosystem integration**: Watchdog, error-loop, janitor\n3. **Graceful degradation**: Skills continue when integration fails\n4. **Learning from failures**: Incidents feed into error-learning-loop\n\nThe most successful integrations use **file-based communication** with **graceful degradation** and **structured error handling**."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773108486330}],"truncated":false,"droppedMessages":false,"contentTruncated":false,"contentRedacted":false,"bytes":30411},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773108658788}}
