{"type":"message","id":"e7c358c6","parentId":"662d09f0","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:15:32.999Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Veo el problema. El dashboard muestra TODAS las sesiones como \"stalled\", incluyendo la sesión principal que debería estar \"active\". El problema está en cómo se calcula el estado.\n\nMirando los datos:\n- **Sesión principal**: `age_seconds: 114.902233` (menos de 2 minutos)\n- **Estado**: `\"stalled\"` ❌ **INCORRECTO**\n\nEl problema es que el script de monitoring está usando `updated_at_ms` del archivo `sessions.json`, pero ese timestamp NO se actualiza cuando la sesión está activa. Solo se actualiza cuando hay cambios en la sesión. Para sesiones activas, necesitamos una lógica diferente.\n\nVoy a revisar el script de monitoring para ver cómo está calculando el estado:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_jE9N4kiD8h6niDzYktjg9nt5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"stall_threshold\\|check_for_stalls\\|status.*stalled\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real_simple.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":62374,"output":260,"cacheRead":35520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98154,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773108908681}}
{"type":"message","id":"e84e0c40","parentId":"e7c358c6","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:15:33.039Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_jE9N4kiD8h6niDzYktjg9nt5","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"41:        self.stall_threshold = 300  # 5 minutes in seconds\n100:                if age_seconds and age_seconds > self.stall_threshold:\n101:                    status = \"stalled\"\n137:    def check_for_stalls(self):\n148:                    if time_diff > self.stall_threshold and session[\"status\"] == \"active\":\n156:                        session[\"status\"] = \"stalled\"\n216:        stalls = self.check_for_stalls()\n226:        stalled_count = sum(1 for s in self.sessions.get(\"sessions\", []) if s.get(\"status\") == \"stalled\")\n251:    logger.info(f\"Stall threshold: {monitor.stall_threshold} seconds\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":19,"aggregated":"41:        self.stall_threshold = 300  # 5 minutes in seconds\n100:                if age_seconds and age_seconds > self.stall_threshold:\n101:                    status = \"stalled\"\n137:    def check_for_stalls(self):\n148:                    if time_diff > self.stall_threshold and session[\"status\"] == \"active\":\n156:                        session[\"status\"] = \"stalled\"\n216:        stalls = self.check_for_stalls()\n226:        stalled_count = sum(1 for s in self.sessions.get(\"sessions\", []) if s.get(\"status\") == \"stalled\")\n251:    logger.info(f\"Stall threshold: {monitor.stall_threshold} seconds\")","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773108933020}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4dcfa66","parentId":"e84e0c40","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:16:16.264Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"El problema está en las líneas 100-101. El script está calculando `age_seconds` basado en `updated_at_ms`, y si es mayor a 300 segundos (5 minutos), marca como \"stalled\". Pero `updated_at_ms` NO es el último heartbeat de la sesión, es la última vez que se actualizó el archivo `sessions.json`.\n\nPara la sesión principal (`agent:main:main`), `updated_at_ms: 1773108438100` que es `2026-03-10T02:07:18.100Z`. Eso fue hace ~7 minutos, por eso la marca como \"stalled\".\n\n**El problema es conceptual:** No podemos usar `updated_at_ms` del archivo `sessions.json` para determinar si una sesión está activa. Necesitamos una fuente diferente de \"última actividad\".\n\nPara sesiones REALMENTE activas (como ESTA sesión), necesitamos:\n1. **Heartbeats REALES**: La sesión debería emitir heartbeats\n2. **Otra fuente de actividad**: Procesos en ejecución, logs recientes, etc.\n\nPero para el propósito de este fix, podemos ajustar la lógica:\n\n1. **Sesiones \"main\"** deberían considerarse siempre \"active\" si existen en `sessions.json`\n2. **Sesiones \"subagent\"** que han completado (`status: completed`) deberían ser \"completed\", no \"stalled\"\n3. **Sesiones cron antiguas** sí pueden ser \"stalled\"\n\nVoy a actualizar el script para tener una lógica más inteligente:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_kojGmrVc2YBsF3dangNBRgwP","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real_simple.py","oldText":"                # Determine status\n                status = \"active\"\n                if age_seconds and age_seconds > self.stall_threshold:\n                    status = \"stalled\"","newText":"                # Determine status with smarter logic\n                status = \"active\"\n                \n                # Special handling for different session types\n                if \"cron\" in session_key:\n                    # Cron jobs are one-shot, mark as completed if old\n                    if age_seconds and age_seconds > 3600:  # 1 hour\n                        status = \"completed\"\n                    elif age_seconds and age_seconds > self.stall_threshold:\n                        status = \"stalled\"\n                \n                elif \"subagent\" in session_key:\n                    # Sub-agents: check if they're likely completed\n                    # Sub-agents that completed recently should be \"completed\", not \"stalled\"\n                    if age_seconds and age_seconds > 3600:  # 1 hour\n                        status = \"completed\"\n                    elif age_seconds and age_seconds > self.stall_threshold:\n                        # Check if sub-agent might still be running\n                        # For now, mark as stalled if > 5 minutes\n                        status = \"stalled\"\n                \n                else:\n                    # Main sessions: more lenient threshold\n                    if age_seconds and age_seconds > 1800:  # 30 minutes for main sessions\n                        status = \"stalled\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":61383,"output":749,"cacheRead":36480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98612,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773108933034}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba8484de","parentId":"b4dcfa66","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:16:16.278Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_kojGmrVc2YBsF3dangNBRgwP","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real_simple.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  94                     # updatedAt is in milliseconds\n  95                     updated_time = datetime.fromtimestamp(updated_at / 1000, timezone.utc)\n  96                     age_seconds = (now - updated_time).total_seconds()\n  97                 \n- 98                 # Determine status\n+ 98                 # Determine status with smarter logic\n  99                 status = \"active\"\n-100                 if age_seconds and age_seconds > self.stall_threshold:\n-101                     status = \"stalled\"\n 102                 \n+101                 # Special handling for different session types\n+102                 if \"cron\" in session_key:\n+103                     # Cron jobs are one-shot, mark as completed if old\n+104                     if age_seconds and age_seconds > 3600:  # 1 hour\n+105                         status = \"completed\"\n+106                     elif age_seconds and age_seconds > self.stall_threshold:\n+107                         status = \"stalled\"\n+108                 \n+109                 elif \"subagent\" in session_key:\n+110                     # Sub-agents: check if they're likely completed\n+111                     # Sub-agents that completed recently should be \"completed\", not \"stalled\"\n+112                     if age_seconds and age_seconds > 3600:  # 1 hour\n+113                         status = \"completed\"\n+114                     elif age_seconds and age_seconds > self.stall_threshold:\n+115                         # Check if sub-agent might still be running\n+116                         # For now, mark as stalled if > 5 minutes\n+117                         status = \"stalled\"\n+118                 \n+119                 else:\n+120                     # Main sessions: more lenient threshold\n+121                     if age_seconds and age_seconds > 1800:  # 30 minutes for main sessions\n+122                         status = \"stalled\"\n+123                 \n 103                 session_obj = {\n 104                     \"session_id\": session_id,\n 105                     \"session_key\": session_key,\n 106                     \"agent_id\": session_type,\n     ...","firstChangedLine":98},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773108976271}}
{"type":"message","id":"1723fbd8","parentId":"ba8484de","timestamp":"2026-03-10T02:16:56.594Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora necesito también actualizar la función `check_for_stalls` para que use la misma lógica:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_hHZbVp6ElgCt1eohpEpc8W86","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real_simple.py","oldText":"    def check_for_stalls(self):\n        \"\"\"Check for stalled sessions\"\"\"\n        stalls = []\n        now = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n        \n        for session in self.sessions.get(\"sessions\", []):\n            if \"last_activity\" in session:\n                try:\n                    last_activity = datetime.fromisoformat(session[\"last_activity\"].replace('Z', '+00:00'))\n                    time_diff = (now - last_activity).total_seconds()\n                    \n                    if time_diff > self.stall_threshold and session[\"status\"] == \"active\":\n                        stalls.append({\n                            \"session_id\": session[\"session_id\"],\n                            \"session_key\": session[\"session_key\"],\n                            \"stall_duration\": time_diff,\n                            \"last_activity\": session[\"last_activity\"],\n                            \"description\": session.get(\"description\", \"Unknown session\")\n                        })\n                        session[\"status\"] = \"stalled\"\n                except (ValueError, KeyError) as e:\n                    logger.warning(f\"Error parsing date for session {session.get('session_id')}: {e}\")\n        \n        return stalls","newText":"    def check_for_stalls(self):\n        \"\"\"Check for stalled sessions with type-aware logic\"\"\"\n        stalls = []\n        now = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n        \n        for session in self.sessions.get(\"sessions\", []):\n            if \"last_activity\" in session:\n                try:\n                    last_activity = datetime.fromisoformat(session[\"last_activity\"].replace('Z', '+00:00'))\n                    time_diff = (now - last_activity).total_seconds()\n                    \n                    session_key = session.get(\"session_key\", \"\")\n                    \n                    # Determine appropriate threshold based on session type\n                    if \"cron\" in session_key:\n                        threshold = 3600  # 1 hour for cron jobs\n                    elif \"subagent\" in session_key:\n                        threshold = 1800  # 30 minutes for sub-agents\n                    else:\n                        threshold = 1800  # 30 minutes for main sessions\n                    \n                    if time_diff > threshold and session[\"status\"] == \"active\":\n                        stalls.append({\n                            \"session_id\": session[\"session_id\"],\n                            \"session_key\": session[\"session_key\"],\n                            \"stall_duration\": time_diff,\n                            \"last_activity\": session[\"last_activity\"],\n                            \"description\": session.get(\"description\", \"Unknown session\"),\n                            \"threshold_used\": threshold\n                        })\n                        session[\"status\"] = \"stalled\"\n                except (ValueError, KeyError) as e:\n                    logger.warning(f\"Error parsing date for session {session.get('session_id')}: {e}\")\n        \n        return stalls"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":58542,"output":679,"cacheRead":39104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98325,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773108976276}}
